v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

139ShouldThrow GetShouldThrow(Isolate* isolate, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
140 if (should_throw.IsJust()) return should_throw.FromJust();
141
142 LanguageMode mode = isolate->context()->scope_info()->language_mode();
143 if (mode == LanguageMode::kStrict) return kThrowOnError;
144
145 for (StackFrameIterator it(isolate, isolate->thread_local_top(),
146 StackFrameIterator::NoHandles{});
147 !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
148 if (!it.frame()->is_javascript()) continue;
149
150 // Get the language mode from closure.
151 JavaScriptFrame* js_frame = static_cast<JavaScriptFrame*>(it.frame());
152 std::vector<Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo>> functions;
153 js_frame->GetFunctions(&functions);
154 LanguageMode closure_language_mode = functions.back()->language_mode();
155 if (closure_language_mode > mode) {
156 mode = closure_language_mode;
157 }
158 break;
159 }
160
161 return is_sloppy(mode) ? kDontThrow : kThrowOnError;
162}
163
164bool ComparisonResultToBool(Operation op, ComparisonResult result) {
165 switch (op) {
166 case Operation::kLessThan:
167 return result == ComparisonResult::kLessThan;
168 case Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
169 return result == ComparisonResult::kLessThan ||
170 result == ComparisonResult::kEqual;
171 case Operation::kGreaterThan:
172 return result == ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan;
173 case Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
174 return result == ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan ||
175 result == ComparisonResult::kEqual;
176 default:
177 break;
178 }
179 UNREACHABLE();
180}
181
182std::string ToString(InstanceType instance_type) {
183 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(instance_type)) {
184 std::stringstream ss;
185 ss << "[api object] "
186 << static_cast<int16_t>(instance_type) -
187 i::Internals::kFirstJSApiObjectType;
188 return ss.str();
189 }
190 switch (instance_type) {
191#define WRITE_TYPE(TYPE) \
192 case TYPE: \
193 return #TYPE;
194 INSTANCE_TYPE_LIST(WRITE_TYPE)
195#undef WRITE_TYPE
196 }
197
198 std::stringstream ss;
199 ss << "[unknown instance type " << static_cast<int16_t>(instance_type) << "]";
200 return ss.str();
201}
202
203std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, InstanceType instance_type) {
204 return os << ToString(instance_type);
205}
206
207std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, PropertyCellType type) {
208 switch (type) {
209 case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
210 return os << "Undefined";
211 case PropertyCellType::kConstant:
212 return os << "Constant";
213 case PropertyCellType::kConstantType:
214 return os << "ConstantType";
215 case PropertyCellType::kMutable:
216 return os << "Mutable";
217 case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
218 return os << "InTransition";
219 }
220 UNREACHABLE();
221}

223// static
224Handle<FieldType> Object::OptimalType(Tagged<Object> obj, Isolate* isolate,
225 Representation representation) {
226 if (representation.IsNone()) return FieldType::None(isolate);
227 if (v8_flags.track_field_types) {
228 if (representation.IsHeapObject() && IsHeapObject(obj)) {
229 // We can track only JavaScript objects with stable maps.
230 DirectHandle<Map> map(Cast<HeapObject>(obj)->map(), isolate);
231 if (map->is_stable() && IsJSReceiverMap(*map)) {
232 return FieldType::Class(map, isolate);
233 }
234 }
235 }
236 return FieldType::Any(isolate);
237}
238
239Handle<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>> Object::NewStorageFor(
240 Isolate* isolate, Handle<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>> object,
241 Representation representation) {
242 if (!representation.IsDouble()) return object;
243 Handle<HeapNumber> result = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
244 if (IsUninitialized(*object, isolate)) {
245 result->set_value_as_bits(kHoleNanInt64);
246 } else if (IsHeapNumber(*object)) {
247 // Ensure that all bits of the double value are preserved.
248 result->set_value_as_bits(Cast<HeapNumber>(*object)->value_as_bits());
249 } else {
250 result->set_value(Cast<Smi>(*object).value());
251 }
252 return result;
253}
254
255template <AllocationType allocation_type, typename IsolateT>
256Handle<JSAny> Object::WrapForRead(IsolateT* isolate, Handle<JSAny> object,
257 Representation representation) {
258 DCHECK(!IsUninitialized(*object, isolate));
259 if (!representation.IsDouble()) {
260 DCHECK(Object::FitsRepresentation(*object, representation));
261 return object;
262 }
263 return isolate->factory()->template NewHeapNumberFromBits<allocation_type>(
264 Cast<HeapNumber>(*object)->value_as_bits());
265}

267template Handle<JSAny> Object::WrapForRead<AllocationType::kYoung>(
268 Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSAny> object, Representation representation);
269template Handle<JSAny> Object::WrapForRead<AllocationType::kOld>(
270 LocalIsolate* isolate, Handle<JSAny> object, Representation representation);

272MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> Object::ToObjectImpl(Isolate* isolate,
273 DirectHandle<Object> object,
274 const char* method_name) {
275 DCHECK(!IsJSReceiver(*object)); // Use ToObject() for fast path.
276 DirectHandle<Context> native_context = isolate->native_context();
277 DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor;
278 if (IsSmi(*object)) {
279 constructor = direct_handle(native_context->number_function(), isolate);
280 } else {
281 int constructor_function_index =
282 Cast<HeapObject>(object)->map()->GetConstructorFunctionIndex();
283 if (constructor_function_index == Map::kNoConstructorFunctionIndex) {
284 if (method_name != nullptr) {
285 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
286 isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNullOrUndefined,
287 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
288 method_name)));
289 }
290 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
291 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kUndefinedOrNullToObject));
292 }
293 constructor = direct_handle(
294 Cast<JSFunction>(native_context->get(constructor_function_index)),
295 isolate);
296 }
297 Handle<JSObject> result = isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(constructor);
298 Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(result)->set_value(Cast<JSAny>(*object));
299 return result;
300}
301
302// ES6 section 9.2.1.2, OrdinaryCallBindThis for sloppy callee.
303// static
304MaybeDirectHandle<JSReceiver> Object::ConvertReceiver(
305 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
306 if (IsJSReceiver(*object)) return Cast<JSReceiver>(object);
307 if (IsNullOrUndefined(*object, isolate)) {
308 return isolate->global_proxy();
309 }
310 return Object::ToObject(isolate, object);
311}

313// static
314
315template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
316 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
317typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToNumber(
318 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
319 while (true) {
320 if (IsNumber(*input)) {
321 return Cast<Number>(input);
322 }
323 if (IsString(*input)) {
324 return String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(input));
325 }
326 if (IsOddball(*input)) {
327 return Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(input));
328 }
329 if (IsSymbol(*input)) {
330 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSymbolToNumber));
331 }
332 if (IsBigInt(*input)) {
333 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kBigIntToNumber));
334 }
335 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
336 isolate, input,
337 JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(input),
338 ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber));
339 }
340}

344template V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MaybeIndirectHandle<Number> Object::ConvertToNumber(

347// static
348template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
349 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
350typename HandleType<Numeric>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToNumeric(
351 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
352 while (true) {
353 if (IsNumber(*input)) {
354 return Cast<Number>(input);
355 }
356 if (IsString(*input)) {
357 return String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(input));
358 }
359 if (IsOddball(*input)) {
360 return Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(input));
361 }
362 if (IsSymbol(*input)) {
363 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSymbolToNumber));
364 }
365 if (IsBigInt(*input)) {
366 return Cast<BigInt>(input);
367 }
368 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
369 isolate, input,
370 JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(input),
371 ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber));
372 }
373}

381template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
382 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
383typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToInteger(
384 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
385 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, input, ConvertToNumber(isolate, input));
386 if (IsSmi(*input)) return Cast<Smi>(input);
387 return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(
388 DoubleToInteger(Cast<HeapNumber>(*input)->value()));
389}

413template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
414 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
415typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToUint32(
416 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
417 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, input, ConvertToNumber(isolate, input));
418 if (IsSmi(*input))
419 return typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType(
420 Smi::ToUint32Smi(Cast<Smi>(*input)), isolate);
421 return isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(
422 DoubleToUint32(Cast<HeapNumber>(*input)->value()));
423}

433typename HandleType<Name>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToName(
434 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
435 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
436 isolate, input,
437 Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, input, ToPrimitiveHint::kString));
438 if (IsName(*input)) return Cast<Name>(input);

447// ES6 7.1.14
448// static
449template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
450 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
451typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToPropertyKey(
452 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> value) {
453 // 1. Let key be ToPrimitive(argument, hint String).
454 typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType maybe_key =
455 Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, value, ToPrimitiveHint::kString);
456 // 2. ReturnIfAbrupt(key).
457 HandleType<Object> key;
458 if (!maybe_key.ToHandle(&key)) return key;
459 // 3. If Type(key) is Symbol, then return key.
460 if (IsSymbol(*key)) return key;
461 // 4. Return ToString(key).
462 // Extending spec'ed behavior, we'd be happy to return an element index.
463 if (IsSmi(*key)) return key;
464 if (IsHeapNumber(*key)) {
465 uint32_t uint_value;
466 if (Object::ToArrayLength(*value, &uint_value) &&
467 uint_value <= static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::kMaxValue)) {
468 return HandleType<Object>(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(uint_value)),
469 isolate);
470 }
471 }
472 return Object::ToString(isolate, key);
473}

480// static
481template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
482 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
483typename HandleType<String>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToString(
484 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input) {
485 while (true) {
486 if (IsOddball(*input)) {
487 HandleType<String> result(Cast<Oddball>(input)->to_string(), isolate);
488 return result;
489 }
490 if (IsNumber(*input)) {
491 return isolate->factory()->NumberToString(input);
492 }
493 if (IsSymbol(*input)) {
494 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSymbolToString));
495 }
496 if (IsBigInt(*input)) {
497 return BigInt::ToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(input));
498 }
499#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
500 // We generally don't let the WasmNull escape into the JavaScript world,
501 // but some builtins may encounter it when called directly from Wasm code.
502 if (IsWasmNull(*input)) {
503 return isolate->factory()->null_string();
504 }
505#endif
506 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
507 isolate, input,
508 JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(input),
509 ToPrimitiveHint::kString));
510 // The previous isString() check happened in Object::ToString and thus we
511 // put it at the end of the loop in this helper.
512 if (IsString(*input)) {
513 return Cast<String>(input);
514 }
515 }
516}

520template V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MaybeIndirectHandle<String> Object::ConvertToString(

525bool IsErrorObject(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
526 if (!IsJSObject(*object)) return false;
527 return ErrorUtils::HasErrorStackSymbolOwnProperty(isolate,
528 Cast<JSObject>(object));
529}
530
531DirectHandle<String> AsStringOrEmpty(Isolate* isolate,
532 DirectHandle<Object> object) {
533 return IsString(*object) ? Cast<String>(object)
534 : isolate->factory()->empty_string();
535}
536
537DirectHandle<String> NoSideEffectsErrorToString(
538 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> error) {
539 DirectHandle<Name> name_key = isolate->factory()->name_string();
540 DirectHandle<Object> name =
541 JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(isolate, error, name_key);
542 DirectHandle<String> name_str = AsStringOrEmpty(isolate, name);
543
544 DirectHandle<Name> msg_key = isolate->factory()->message_string();
545 DirectHandle<Object> msg =
546 JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(isolate, error, msg_key);
547 DirectHandle<String> msg_str = AsStringOrEmpty(isolate, msg);
548
549 if (name_str->length() == 0) return msg_str;
550 if (msg_str->length() == 0) return name_str;
551
552 constexpr const char error_suffix[] = "<a very large string>";
553 constexpr uint32_t error_suffix_size = sizeof(error_suffix);
554 uint32_t suffix_size = std::min(error_suffix_size, msg_str->length());
555
556 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
557 if (name_str->length() + suffix_size + 2 /* ": " */ > String::kMaxLength) {
558 constexpr const char connector[] = "... : ";
559 int connector_size = sizeof(connector);
560 DirectHandle<String> truncated_name =
561 isolate->factory()->NewProperSubString(
562 name_str, 0,
563 name_str->length() - error_suffix_size - connector_size);
564 builder.AppendString(truncated_name);
565 builder.AppendCStringLiteral(connector);
566 builder.AppendCStringLiteral(error_suffix);
567 } else {
568 builder.AppendString(name_str);
569 builder.AppendCStringLiteral(": ");
570 if (builder.Length() + msg_str->length() <= String::kMaxLength) {
571 builder.AppendString(msg_str);
572 } else {
573 builder.AppendCStringLiteral(error_suffix);
574 }
575 }
576
577 return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
578}

582// static
583MaybeDirectHandle<String> Object::NoSideEffectsToMaybeString(
584 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> input) {
585 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
586
587 if (IsString(*input) || IsNumber(*input) || IsOddball(*input)) {
588 return Object::ToString(isolate, input).ToHandleChecked();
589 } else if (IsJSProxy(*input)) {
590 DirectHandle<Object> currInput = input;
591 do {
592 Tagged<HeapObject> target = Cast<JSProxy>(currInput)->target(isolate);
593 currInput = direct_handle(target, isolate);
594 } while (IsJSProxy(*currInput));
595 return NoSideEffectsToString(isolate, currInput);
596 } else if (IsBigInt(*input)) {
597 return BigInt::NoSideEffectsToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(input));
598 } else if (IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(*input)) {
599 // -- F u n c t i o n
600 DirectHandle<String> fun_str;
601 if (IsJSBoundFunction(*input)) {
602 fun_str = JSBoundFunction::ToString(Cast<JSBoundFunction>(input));
603 } else if (IsJSWrappedFunction(*input)) {
604 fun_str = JSWrappedFunction::ToString(Cast<JSWrappedFunction>(input));
605 } else {
606 DCHECK(IsJSFunction(*input));
607 fun_str = JSFunction::ToString(Cast<JSFunction>(input));
608 }
609
610 if (fun_str->length() > 128) {
611 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
612 builder.AppendString(isolate->factory()->NewSubString(fun_str, 0, 111));
613 builder.AppendCStringLiteral("...<omitted>...");
614 builder.AppendString(isolate->factory()->NewSubString(
615 fun_str, fun_str->length() - 2, fun_str->length()));
616
617 return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
618 }
619 return fun_str;
620 } else if (IsSymbol(*input)) {
621 // -- S y m b o l
622 DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol = Cast<Symbol>(input);
623
624 if (symbol->is_private_name()) {
625 return DirectHandle<String>(Cast<String>(symbol->description()), isolate);
626 }
627
628 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
629 builder.AppendCStringLiteral("Symbol(");
630 if (IsString(symbol->description())) {
631 DirectHandle<String> description(Cast<String>(symbol->description()),
632 isolate);
633 if (description->length() > 128) {
634 builder.AppendString(
635 isolate->factory()->NewSubString(description, 0, 56));
636 builder.AppendCStringLiteral("...<omitted>...");
637 builder.AppendString(isolate->factory()->NewSubString(
638 description, description->length() - 56, description->length()));
639 } else {
640 builder.AppendString(description);
641 }
642 }
643 builder.AppendCharacter(')');
644
645 return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
646 } else if (IsJSReceiver(*input)) {
647 // -- J S R e c e i v e r
648 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(input);
649 DirectHandle<Object> to_string = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
650 isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->toString_string());
651
652 if (IsErrorObject(isolate, input) ||
653 *to_string == *isolate->error_to_string()) {
654 // When internally formatting error objects, use a side-effects-free
655 // version of Error.prototype.toString independent of the actually
656 // installed toString method.
657 return NoSideEffectsErrorToString(isolate, receiver);
658 } else if (*to_string == *isolate->object_to_string()) {
659 DirectHandle<Object> ctor = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
660 isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->constructor_string());
661 if (IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(*ctor)) {
662 DirectHandle<String> ctor_name;
663 if (IsJSBoundFunction(*ctor)) {
664 ctor_name =
665 JSBoundFunction::GetName(isolate, Cast<JSBoundFunction>(ctor))
666 .ToHandleChecked();
667 } else if (IsJSFunction(*ctor)) {
668 ctor_name = JSFunction::GetName(isolate, Cast<JSFunction>(ctor));
669 }
670
671 if (ctor_name->length() != 0) {
672 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
673 builder.AppendCStringLiteral("#<");
674 builder.AppendString(ctor_name);
675 builder.AppendCharacter('>');
676
677 return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
678 }
679 }
680 }
681 }
682 return {};
683}
684
685// static
686DirectHandle<String> Object::NoSideEffectsToString(Isolate* isolate,
687 DirectHandle<Object> input) {
688 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
689
690 // Try to convert input to a meaningful string.
691 MaybeDirectHandle<String> maybe_string =
692 NoSideEffectsToMaybeString(isolate, input);
693 DirectHandle<String> string_handle;
694 if (maybe_string.ToHandle(&string_handle)) {
695 return string_handle;
696 }
697
698 // At this point, input is either none of the above or a JSReceiver.
699
700 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver;
701 if (IsJSReceiver(*input)) {
702 receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(input);
703 } else {
704 // This is the only case where Object::ToObject throws.
705 DCHECK(!IsSmi(*input));
706 int constructor_function_index =
707 Cast<HeapObject>(input)->map()->GetConstructorFunctionIndex();
708 if (constructor_function_index == Map::kNoConstructorFunctionIndex) {
709 return isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked("[object Unknown]");
710 }
711
712 receiver = Object::ToObjectImpl(isolate, input).ToHandleChecked();
713 }
714
715 DirectHandle<String> builtin_tag =
716 direct_handle(receiver->class_name(), isolate);
717 DirectHandle<Object> tag_obj = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
718 isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->to_string_tag_symbol());
719 DirectHandle<String> tag =
720 IsString(*tag_obj) ? Cast<String>(tag_obj) : builtin_tag;
721
722 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
723 builder.AppendCStringLiteral("[object ");
724 builder.AppendString(tag);
725 builder.AppendCharacter(']');
726
727 return builder.Finish().ToHandleChecked();
728}
729
730// static
731MaybeHandle<Number> Object::ConvertToLength(Isolate* isolate,
732 DirectHandle<Object> input) {
733 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, input, ToNumber(isolate, input));
734 if (IsSmi(*input)) {
735 int value = std::max(Smi::ToInt(*input), 0);
736 return handle(Smi::FromInt(value), isolate);
737 }
738 double len = DoubleToInteger(Cast<HeapNumber>(*input)->value());
739 if (len <= 0.0) {
740 return handle(Smi::zero(), isolate);
741 } else if (len >= kMaxSafeInteger) {
742 len = kMaxSafeInteger;
743 }
744 return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(len);
745}
746
747// static
748template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
749 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
750typename HandleType<Number>::MaybeType Object::ConvertToIndex(
751 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Object> input, MessageTemplate error_index) {
752 if (IsUndefined(*input, isolate))
753 return HandleType<Number>(Smi::zero(), isolate);
754 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, input, ToNumber(isolate, input));
755 if (IsSmi(*input) && Smi::ToInt(*input) >= 0) return Cast<Smi>(input);
756 double len = DoubleToInteger(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*input)));
757 HandleType<Number> js_len = isolate->factory()->NewNumber(len);
758 if (len < 0.0 || len > kMaxSafeInteger) {
759 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewRangeError(error_index, js_len));
760 }
761 return js_len;
762}
763
764template V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MaybeDirectHandle<Number> Object::ConvertToIndex(
765 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> input, MessageTemplate error_index);
766template V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MaybeIndirectHandle<Number> Object::ConvertToIndex(
767 Isolate* isolate, IndirectHandle<Object> input,
768 MessageTemplate error_index);
769
770template <typename IsolateT>
771// static
772bool Object::BooleanValue(Tagged<Object> obj, IsolateT* isolate) {
773 if (IsSmi(obj)) return Smi::ToInt(obj) != 0;
774 DCHECK(IsHeapObject(obj));
775 if (IsBoolean(obj)) return IsTrue(obj, isolate);
776 if (IsNullOrUndefined(obj, isolate)) return false;
777#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
778 if (IsWasmNull(obj)) return false;
779#endif
780 if (IsUndetectable(obj)) return false; // Undetectable object is false.
781 if (IsString(obj)) return Cast<String>(obj)->length() != 0;
782 if (IsHeapNumber(obj)) return DoubleToBoolean(Cast<HeapNumber>(obj)->value());
783 if (IsBigInt(obj)) return Cast<BigInt>(obj)->ToBoolean();
784 return true;
785}
786template bool Object::BooleanValue(Tagged<Object>, Isolate*);
787template bool Object::BooleanValue(Tagged<Object>, LocalIsolate*);
788
789// static
790Tagged<Object> Object::ToBoolean(Tagged<Object> obj, Isolate* isolate) {
791 if (IsBoolean(obj)) return obj;
792 return isolate->heap()->ToBoolean(Object::BooleanValue(obj, isolate));
793}
794
795namespace {
796
797// TODO(bmeurer): Maybe we should introduce a marker interface Number,
798// where we put all these methods at some point?
799ComparisonResult StrictNumberCompare(double x, double y) {
800 if (std::isnan(x) || std::isnan(y)) {
801 return ComparisonResult::kUndefined;
802 } else if (x < y) {
803 return ComparisonResult::kLessThan;
804 } else if (x > y) {
805 return ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan;
806 } else {
807 return ComparisonResult::kEqual;
808 }
809}
810
811// See Number case of ES6#sec-strict-equality-comparison
812// Returns false if x or y is NaN, treats -0.0 as equal to 0.0.
813bool StrictNumberEquals(double x, double y) {
814 // Must check explicitly for NaN's on Windows, but -0 works fine.
815 if (std::isnan(x) || std::isnan(y)) return false;
816 return x == y;
817}
818
819bool StrictNumberEquals(const Tagged<Number> x, const Tagged<Number> y) {
820 return StrictNumberEquals(Object::NumberValue(x), Object::NumberValue(y));
821}
822
823bool StrictNumberEquals(DirectHandle<Number> x, DirectHandle<Number> y) {
824 return StrictNumberEquals(*x, *y);
825}
826
827ComparisonResult Reverse(ComparisonResult result) {
828 if (result == ComparisonResult::kLessThan) {
829 return ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan;
830 }
831 if (result == ComparisonResult::kGreaterThan) {
832 return ComparisonResult::kLessThan;
833 }
834 return result;
835}
836
837} // anonymous namespace
838
839// static
840Maybe<ComparisonResult> Object::Compare(Isolate* isolate,
841 DirectHandle<Object> x,
842 DirectHandle<Object> y) {
843 // ES6 section 7.2.11 Abstract Relational Comparison step 3 and 4.
844 if (!Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, x, ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber).ToHandle(&x) ||
845 !Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, y, ToPrimitiveHint::kNumber).ToHandle(&y)) {
846 return Nothing<ComparisonResult>();
847 }
848 if (IsString(*x) && IsString(*y)) {
849 // ES6 section 7.2.11 Abstract Relational Comparison step 5.
850 return Just(String::Compare(isolate, Cast<String>(x), Cast<String>(y)));
851 }
852 if (IsBigInt(*x) && IsString(*y)) {
853 return BigInt::CompareToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(x), Cast<String>(y));
854 }
855 if (IsString(*x) && IsBigInt(*y)) {
856 Maybe<ComparisonResult> maybe_result =
857 BigInt::CompareToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(y), Cast<String>(x));
858 ComparisonResult result;
859 if (maybe_result.To(&result)) {
860 return Just(Reverse(result));
861 } else {
862 return Nothing<ComparisonResult>();
863 }
864 }
865 // ES6 section 7.2.11 Abstract Relational Comparison step 6.
866 if (!Object::ToNumeric(isolate, x).ToHandle(&x) ||
867 !Object::ToNumeric(isolate, y).ToHandle(&y)) {
868 return Nothing<ComparisonResult>();
869 }
870
871 bool x_is_number = IsNumber(*x);
872 bool y_is_number = IsNumber(*y);
873 if (x_is_number && y_is_number) {
874 return Just(
875 StrictNumberCompare(Object::NumberValue(*x), Object::NumberValue(*y)));
876 } else if (!x_is_number && !y_is_number) {
877 return Just(BigInt::CompareToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(x), Cast<BigInt>(y)));
878 } else if (x_is_number) {
879 return Just(Reverse(BigInt::CompareToNumber(Cast<BigInt>(y), x)));
880 } else {
881 return Just(BigInt::CompareToNumber(Cast<BigInt>(x), y));
882 }
883}
884
885Maybe<bool> Object::Equals(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> x,
886 DirectHandle<Object> y) {
887 // This is the generic version of Abstract Equality Comparison. Must be in
888 // sync with CodeStubAssembler::Equal.
889 while (true) {
890 if (IsNumber(*x)) {
891 if (IsNumber(*y)) {
892 return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(*x), Cast<Number>(*y)));
893 } else if (IsBoolean(*y)) {
894 return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(*x),
895 Cast<Oddball>(y)->to_number()));
896 } else if (IsString(*y)) {
897 return Just(StrictNumberEquals(
898 Cast<Number>(x), String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(y))));
899 } else if (IsBigInt(*y)) {
900 return Just(BigInt::EqualToNumber(Cast<BigInt>(y), Cast<Number>(x)));
901 } else if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
902 if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(y))
903 .ToHandle(&y)) {
904 return Nothing<bool>();
905 }
906 } else {
907 return Just(false);
908 }
909 } else if (IsString(*x)) {
910 if (IsString(*y)) {
911 return Just(String::Equals(isolate, Cast<String>(x), Cast<String>(y)));
912 } else if (IsNumber(*y)) {
913 x = String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(x));
914 return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(*x), Cast<Number>(*y)));
915 } else if (IsBoolean(*y)) {
916 x = String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(x));
917 return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(*x),
918 Cast<Oddball>(y)->to_number()));
919 } else if (IsBigInt(*y)) {
920 return BigInt::EqualToString(isolate, Cast<BigInt>(y), Cast<String>(x));
921 } else if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
922 if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(y))
923 .ToHandle(&y)) {
924 return Nothing<bool>();
925 }
926 } else {
927 return Just(false);
928 }
929 } else if (IsBoolean(*x)) {
930 if (IsOddball(*y)) {
931 return Just(x.is_identical_to(y));
932 } else if (IsNumber(*y)) {
933 return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Oddball>(x)->to_number(),
934 Cast<Number>(*y)));
935 } else if (IsString(*y)) {
936 y = String::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<String>(y));
937 return Just(StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Oddball>(x)->to_number(),
938 Cast<Number>(*y)));
939 } else if (IsBigInt(*y)) {
940 x = Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(x));
941 return Just(BigInt::EqualToNumber(Cast<BigInt>(y), x));
942 } else if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
943 if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(y))
944 .ToHandle(&y)) {
945 return Nothing<bool>();
946 }
947 x = Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(x));
948 } else {
949 return Just(false);
950 }
951 } else if (IsSymbol(*x)) {
952 if (IsSymbol(*y)) {
953 return Just(x.is_identical_to(y));
954 } else if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
955 if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(y))
956 .ToHandle(&y)) {
957 return Nothing<bool>();
958 }
959 } else {
960 return Just(false);
961 }
962 } else if (IsBigInt(*x)) {
963 if (IsBigInt(*y)) {
964 return Just(BigInt::EqualToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(*x), Cast<BigInt>(*y)));
965 }
966 return Equals(isolate, y, x);
967 } else if (IsJSReceiver(*x)) {
968 if (IsJSReceiver(*y)) {
969 return Just(x.is_identical_to(y));
970 } else if (IsUndetectable(*y)) {
971 return Just(IsUndetectable(*x));
972 } else if (IsBoolean(*y)) {
973 y = Oddball::ToNumber(isolate, Cast<Oddball>(y));
974 } else if (!JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(x))
975 .ToHandle(&x)) {
976 return Nothing<bool>();
977 }
978 } else {
979 return Just(IsUndetectable(*x) && IsUndetectable(*y));
980 }
981 }
982}
983
984// static
985bool Object::StrictEquals(Tagged<Object> obj, Tagged<Object> that) {
986 if (IsNumber(obj)) {
987 if (!IsNumber(that)) return false;
988 return StrictNumberEquals(Cast<Number>(obj), Cast<Number>(that));
989 } else if (IsString(obj)) {
990 if (!IsString(that)) return false;
991 return Cast<String>(obj)->Equals(Cast<String>(that));
992 } else if (IsBigInt(obj)) {
993 if (!IsBigInt(that)) return false;
994 return BigInt::EqualToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(obj), Cast<BigInt>(that));
995 }
996 return obj == that;
997}
998
999// static
1000Handle<String> Object::TypeOf(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object) {
1001 if (IsNumber(*object)) return isolate->factory()->number_string();
1002 if (IsOddball(*object))
1003 return handle(Cast<Oddball>(*object)->type_of(), isolate);
1004 if (IsUndetectable(*object)) {
1005 return isolate->factory()->undefined_string();
1006 }
1007 if (IsString(*object)) return isolate->factory()->string_string();
1008 if (IsSymbol(*object)) return isolate->factory()->symbol_string();
1009 if (IsBigInt(*object)) return isolate->factory()->bigint_string();
1010 if (IsCallable(*object)) return isolate->factory()->function_string();
1011 return isolate->factory()->object_string();
1012}
1013
1014// static
1015MaybeHandle<Object> Object::Add(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> lhs,
1016 Handle<Object> rhs) {
1017 if (IsNumber(*lhs) && IsNumber(*rhs)) {
1018 return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(
1019 Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*lhs)) +
1020 Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(*rhs)));
1021 } else if (IsString(*lhs) && IsString(*rhs)) {
1022 return isolate->factory()->NewConsString(Cast<String>(lhs),
1023 Cast<String>(rhs));
1024 }
1025 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, lhs, Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, lhs));
1026 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, rhs, Object::ToPrimitive(isolate, rhs));
1027 if (IsString(*lhs) || IsString(*rhs)) {
1028 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, rhs, Object::ToString(isolate, rhs));
1029 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, lhs, Object::ToString(isolate, lhs));
1030 return isolate->factory()->NewConsString(Cast<String>(lhs),
1031 Cast<String>(rhs));
1032 }
1033 DirectHandle<Number> lhs_number;
1034 DirectHandle<Number> rhs_number;
1035 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, rhs_number,
1036 Object::ToNumber(isolate, rhs));
1037 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, lhs_number,
1038 Object::ToNumber(isolate, lhs));
1039 return isolate->factory()->NewNumber(Object::NumberValue(*lhs_number) +
1040 Object::NumberValue(*rhs_number));
1041}
1042
1043// static
1044MaybeHandle<Object> Object::OrdinaryHasInstance(Isolate* isolate,
1045 DirectHandle<JSAny> callable,
1046 DirectHandle<JSAny> object) {
1047 // The {callable} must have a [[Call]] internal method.
1048 if (!IsCallable(*callable)) return isolate->factory()->false_value();
1049
1050 // Check if {callable} is a bound function, and if so retrieve its
1051 // [[BoundTargetFunction]] and use that instead of {callable}.
1052 if (IsJSBoundFunction(*callable)) {
1053 // Since there is a mutual recursion here, we might run out of stack
1054 // space for long chains of bound functions.
1055 STACK_CHECK(isolate, MaybeHandle<Object>());
1056 DirectHandle<JSCallable> bound_callable(
1057 Cast<JSBoundFunction>(callable)->bound_target_function(), isolate);
1058 return Object::InstanceOf(isolate, object, bound_callable);
1059 }
1060
1061 // If {object} is not a receiver, return false.
1062 if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) return isolate->factory()->false_value();
1063
1064 // Get the "prototype" of {callable}; raise an error if it's not a receiver.
1065 DirectHandle<Object> prototype;
1066 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1067 isolate, prototype,
1068 Object::GetProperty(isolate, callable,
1069 isolate->factory()->prototype_string()));
1070 if (!IsJSReceiver(*prototype)) {
1071 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1072 isolate,
1073 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInstanceofNonobjectProto, prototype));
1074 }
1075
1076 // Return whether or not {prototype} is in the prototype chain of {object}.
1077 Maybe<bool> result = JSReceiver::HasInPrototypeChain(
1078 isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object), prototype);
1079 if (result.IsNothing()) return MaybeHandle<Object>();
1080 return isolate->factory()->ToBoolean(result.FromJust());
1081}
1082
1083// static
1084MaybeHandle<Object> Object::InstanceOf(Isolate* isolate,
1085 DirectHandle<JSAny> object,
1086 DirectHandle<JSAny> callable) {
1087 // The {callable} must be a receiver.
1088 if (!IsJSReceiver(*callable)) {
1089 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1090 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonObjectInInstanceOfCheck));
1091 }
1092
1093 // Lookup the @@hasInstance method on {callable}.
1094 DirectHandle<Object> inst_of_handler;
1095 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1096 isolate, inst_of_handler,
1097 Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(callable),
1098 isolate->factory()->has_instance_symbol()));
1099 if (!IsUndefined(*inst_of_handler, isolate)) {
1100 // Call the {inst_of_handler} on the {callable}.
1101 DirectHandle<Object> result;
1102 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {object};
1103 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result,
1104 Execution::Call(isolate, inst_of_handler,
1105 callable, base::VectorOf(args)));
1106 return isolate->factory()->ToBoolean(
1107 Object::BooleanValue(*result, isolate));
1108 }
1109
1110 // The {callable} must have a [[Call]] internal method.
1111 if (!IsCallable(*callable)) {
1112 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1113 isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonCallableInInstanceOfCheck));
1114 }
1115
1116 // Fall back to OrdinaryHasInstance with {callable} and {object}.
1117 Handle<Object> result;
1118 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1119 isolate, result, Object::OrdinaryHasInstance(isolate, callable, object));
1120 return result;
1121}
1122
1123// static
1124MaybeHandle<Object> Object::GetMethod(Isolate* isolate,
1125 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
1126 DirectHandle<Name> name) {
1127 Handle<Object> func;
1128 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, func,
1129 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, receiver, name));
1130 if (IsNullOrUndefined(*func, isolate)) {
1131 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1132 }
1133 if (!IsCallable(*func)) {
1134 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kPropertyNotFunction,
1135 func, name, receiver));
1136 }
1137 return func;
1138}

1140namespace {
1141
1142MaybeHandle<FixedArray> CreateListFromArrayLikeFastPath(
1143 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object, ElementTypes element_types) {
1144 if (element_types == ElementTypes::kAll) {
1145 if (IsJSArray(*object)) {
1146 DirectHandle<JSArray> array = Cast<JSArray>(object);
1147 uint32_t length;
1148 if (!array->HasArrayPrototype(isolate) ||
1149 !Object::ToUint32(array->length(), &length) ||
1150 !array->HasFastElements() ||
1151 !JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *array)) {
1152 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
1153 }
1154 return array->GetElementsAccessor()->CreateListFromArrayLike(
1155 isolate, array, length);
1156 } else if (IsJSTypedArray(*object)) {
1157 DirectHandle<JSTypedArray> array = Cast<JSTypedArray>(object);
1158 size_t length = array->GetLength();
1159 if (array->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds() ||
1160 length > static_cast<size_t>(FixedArray::kMaxLength)) {
1161 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
1162 }
1163 static_assert(FixedArray::kMaxLength <=
1164 std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
1165 return array->GetElementsAccessor()->CreateListFromArrayLike(
1166 isolate, array, static_cast<uint32_t>(length));
1167 }
1168 }
1169 return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
1170}
1171
1172} // namespace
1173
1174// static
1175MaybeHandle<FixedArray> Object::CreateListFromArrayLike(
1176 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object, ElementTypes element_types) {
1177 // Fast-path for JSArray and JSTypedArray.
1178 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> fast_result =
1179 CreateListFromArrayLikeFastPath(isolate, object, element_types);
1180 if (!fast_result.is_null()) return fast_result;
1181 // 1. ReturnIfAbrupt(object).
1182 // 2. (default elementTypes -- not applicable.)
1183 // 3. If Type(obj) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
1184 if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) {
1185 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1186 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject,
1187 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
1188 "CreateListFromArrayLike")));
1189 }
1190
1191 // 4. Let len be ? ToLength(? Get(obj, "length")).
1192 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(object);
1193 DirectHandle<Object> raw_length_number;
1194 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, raw_length_number,
1195 Object::GetLengthFromArrayLike(isolate, receiver));
1196 uint32_t len;
1197 if (!Object::ToUint32(*raw_length_number, &len) ||
1198 len > static_cast<uint32_t>(FixedArray::kMaxLength)) {
1199 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1200 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength));
1201 }
1202 // 5. Let list be an empty List.
1203 Handle<FixedArray> list = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(len);
1204 // 6. Let index be 0.
1205 // 7. Repeat while index < len:
1206 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < len; ++index) {
1207 // 7a. Let indexName be ToString(index).
1208 // 7b. Let next be ? Get(obj, indexName).
1209 DirectHandle<Object> next;
1210 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1211 isolate, next, JSReceiver::GetElement(isolate, receiver, index));
1212 switch (element_types) {
1213 case ElementTypes::kAll:
1214 // Nothing to do.
1215 break;
1216 case ElementTypes::kStringAndSymbol: {
1217 // 7c. If Type(next) is not an element of elementTypes, throw a
1218 // TypeError exception.
1219 if (!IsName(*next)) {
1220 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1221 isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNotPropertyName, next));
1222 }
1223 // 7d. Append next as the last element of list.
1224 // Internalize on the fly so we can use pointer identity later.
1225 next = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(Cast<Name>(next));
1226 break;
1227 }
1228 }
1229 list->set(index, *next);
1230 // 7e. Set index to index + 1. (See loop header.)
1231 }
1232 // 8. Return list.
1233 return list;
1234}
1235
1236// static
1237MaybeHandle<Object> Object::GetLengthFromArrayLike(
1238 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object) {
1239 DirectHandle<Object> val;
1240 DirectHandle<Name> key = isolate->factory()->length_string();
1241 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, val,
1242 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, object, key));
1243 return Object::ToLength(isolate, val);
1244}
1245
1246// static
1247MaybeHandle<Object> Object::GetProperty(LookupIterator* it,
1248 bool is_global_reference) {
1249 for (;; it->Next()) {
1250 switch (it->state()) {
1251 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1252 UNREACHABLE();
1253 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
1254 bool was_found;
1255 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1256 // In case of global IC, the receiver is the global object. Replace by
1257 // the global proxy.
1258 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*receiver)) {
1259 receiver = direct_handle(
1260 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*receiver)->global_proxy(), it->isolate());
1261 }
1262 if (is_global_reference) {
1263 Maybe<bool> maybe = JSProxy::HasProperty(
1264 it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(), it->GetName());
1265 if (maybe.IsNothing()) return {};
1266 if (!maybe.FromJust()) {
1267 it->NotFound();
1268 return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1269 }
1270 }
1271 MaybeHandle<JSAny> result =
1272 JSProxy::GetProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
1273 it->GetName(), receiver, &was_found);
1274 if (!was_found && !is_global_reference) it->NotFound();
1275 return result;
1276 }
1277 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1278 return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1279 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
1280 bool done;
1281 Handle<JSAny> result;
1282 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1283 it->isolate(), result,
1284 JSObject::GetPropertyWithInterceptor(it, &done));
1285 if (done) return result;
1286 continue;
1287 }
1288 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
1289 if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
1290 return JSObject::GetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(it);
1291 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1292 return GetPropertyWithAccessor(it);
1293 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1294 return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1295 case LookupIterator::DATA:
1296 return it->GetDataValue();
1297 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1298 if (it->IsPrivateName()) {
1299 auto private_symbol = Cast<Symbol>(it->name());
1300 DirectHandle<String> name_string(
1301 Cast<String>(private_symbol->description()), it->isolate());
1302 if (private_symbol->is_private_brand()) {
1303 DirectHandle<String> class_name =
1304 name_string->length() == 0
1305 ? it->isolate()->factory()->anonymous_string()
1306 : name_string;
1307 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1308 it->isolate(),
1309 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateBrandInstance,
1310 class_name));
1311 }
1312 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1313 it->isolate(),
1314 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateMemberRead,
1315 name_string));
1316 }
1317
1318 return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
1319 }
1320 UNREACHABLE();
1321 }
1322}
1323
1324// static
1325MaybeHandle<JSAny> JSProxy::GetProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1326 DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
1327 DirectHandle<Name> name,
1328 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver,
1329 bool* was_found) {
1330 *was_found = true;
1331
1332 DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
1333 STACK_CHECK(isolate, kNullMaybeHandle);
1334 DirectHandle<Name> trap_name = isolate->factory()->get_string();
1335 // 1. Assert: IsPropertyKey(P) is true.
1336 // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
1337 DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSReceiver, Null>> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
1338 // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
1339 // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
1340 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
1341 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1342 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
1343 }
1344 // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot of O.
1345 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
1346 // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "get").
1347 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
1348 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1349 isolate, trap,
1350 Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), trap_name));
1351 // 7. If trap is undefined, then
1352 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
1353 // 7.a Return target.[[Get]](P, Receiver).
1354 PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
1355 LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, key, target);
1356 MaybeHandle<JSAny> result = Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetProperty(&it));
1357 *was_found = it.IsFound();
1358 return result;
1359 }
1360 // 8. Let trapResult be ? Call(trap, handler, Â«target, P, ReceiverÂ»).
1361 Handle<Object> trap_result;
1362 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name, receiver};
1363 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1364 isolate, trap_result,
1365 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)));
1366
1367 MaybeHandle<JSAny> result =
1368 JSProxy::CheckGetSetTrapResult(isolate, name, target, trap_result, kGet);
1369 if (result.is_null()) {
1370 return result;
1371 }
1372
1373 // 11. Return trap_result
1374 return Cast<JSAny>(trap_result);
1375}
1376
1377// static
1378MaybeHandle<JSAny> JSProxy::CheckGetSetTrapResult(
1379 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
1380 DirectHandle<Object> trap_result, AccessKind access_kind) {
1381 // 9. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
1382 PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
1383 Maybe<bool> target_found =
1384 JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, &target_desc);
1385 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(target_found);
1386 // 10. If targetDesc is not undefined, then
1387 if (target_found.FromJust()) {
1388 // 10.a. If IsDataDescriptor(targetDesc) and targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is
1389 // false and targetDesc.[[Writable]] is false, then
1390 // 10.a.i. If SameValue(trapResult, targetDesc.[[Value]]) is false,
1391 // throw a TypeError exception.
1392 bool inconsistent = PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(&target_desc) &&
1393 !target_desc.configurable() &&
1394 !target_desc.writable() &&
1395 !Object::SameValue(*trap_result, *target_desc.value());
1396 if (inconsistent) {
1397 if (access_kind == kGet) {
1398 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1399 isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyGetNonConfigurableData,
1400 name, target_desc.value(), trap_result));
1401 } else {
1402 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
1403 MessageTemplate::kProxySetFrozenData, name));
1404 return {};
1405 }
1406 }
1407 // 10.b. If IsAccessorDescriptor(targetDesc) and targetDesc.[[Configurable]]
1408 // is false and targetDesc.[[Get]] is undefined, then
1409 // 10.b.i. If trapResult is not undefined, throw a TypeError exception.
1410 if (access_kind == kGet) {
1411 inconsistent = PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(&target_desc) &&
1412 !target_desc.configurable() &&
1413 IsUndefined(*target_desc.get(), isolate) &&
1414 !IsUndefined(*trap_result, isolate);
1415 } else {
1416 inconsistent = PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(&target_desc) &&
1417 !target_desc.configurable() &&
1418 IsUndefined(*target_desc.set(), isolate);
1419 }
1420 if (inconsistent) {
1421 if (access_kind == kGet) {
1422 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1423 isolate,
1424 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyGetNonConfigurableAccessor,
1425 name, trap_result));
1426 } else {
1427 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
1428 MessageTemplate::kProxySetFrozenAccessor, name));
1429 return {};
1430 }
1431 }
1432 }
1433 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1434}
1435
1436// static
1437bool Object::ToInt32(Tagged<Object> obj, int32_t* value) {
1438 if (IsSmi(obj)) {
1439 *value = Smi::ToInt(obj);
1440 return true;
1441 }
1442 if (IsHeapNumber(obj)) {
1443 double num = Cast<HeapNumber>(obj)->value();
1444 // Check range before conversion to avoid undefined behavior.
1445 if (num >= kMinInt && num <= kMaxInt && FastI2D(FastD2I(num)) == num) {
1446 *value = FastD2I(num);
1447 return true;
1448 }
1449 }
1450 return false;
1451}
1452
1453// ES6 9.5.1
1454// static
1455MaybeDirectHandle<JSPrototype> JSProxy::GetPrototype(
1456 DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy) {
1457 Isolate* isolate = proxy->GetIsolate();
1458 DirectHandle<String> trap_name = isolate->factory()->getPrototypeOf_string();
1459
1460 STACK_CHECK(isolate, {});
1461
1462 // 1. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot.
1463 // 2. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
1464 // 3. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
1465 // 4. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot.
1466 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
1467 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1468 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
1469 }
1470 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
1471 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
1472
1473 // 5. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "getPrototypeOf").
1474 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
1475 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, trap,
1476 Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name));
1477 // 6. If trap is undefined, then return target.[[GetPrototypeOf]]().
1478 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
1479 return JSReceiver::GetPrototype(isolate, target);
1480 }
1481 // 7. Let handlerProto be ? Call(trap, handler, Â«targetÂ»).
1482 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target};
1483 DirectHandle<Object> handler_proto_result;
1484 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1485 isolate, handler_proto_result,
1486 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)));
1487 // 8. If Type(handlerProto) is neither Object nor Null, throw a TypeError.
1488 DirectHandle<JSPrototype> handler_proto;
1489 if (!TryCast(handler_proto_result, &handler_proto)) {
1490 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1491 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyGetPrototypeOfInvalid));
1492 }
1493 // 9. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
1494 Maybe<bool> is_extensible = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
1495 MAYBE_RETURN(is_extensible, {});
1496 // 10. If extensibleTarget is true, return handlerProto.
1497 if (is_extensible.FromJust()) return handler_proto;
1498 // 11. Let targetProto be ? target.[[GetPrototypeOf]]().
1499 DirectHandle<JSPrototype> target_proto;
1500 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, target_proto,
1501 JSReceiver::GetPrototype(isolate, target));
1502 // 12. If SameValue(handlerProto, targetProto) is false, throw a TypeError.
1503 if (!Object::SameValue(*handler_proto, *target_proto)) {
1504 THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1505 isolate,
1506 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyGetPrototypeOfNonExtensible));
1507 }
1508 // 13. Return handlerProto.
1509 return handler_proto;
1510}
1511
1512MaybeHandle<JSAny> Object::GetPropertyWithAccessor(LookupIterator* it) {
1513 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1514 DirectHandle<Object> structure = it->GetAccessors();
1515 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1516 // In case of global IC, the receiver is the global object. Replace by the
1517 // global proxy.
1518 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*receiver)) {
1519 receiver =
1520 direct_handle(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*receiver)->global_proxy(), isolate);
1521 }
1522
1523 // We should never get here to initialize a const with the hole value since a
1524 // const declaration would conflict with the getter.
1525 DCHECK(!IsForeign(*structure));
1526
1527 // API style callbacks.
1528 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1529 if (IsAccessorInfo(*structure)) {
1530 DirectHandle<Name> name = it->GetName();
1531 auto info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(structure);
1532
1533 if (!info->has_getter(isolate)) {
1534 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1535 }
1536
1537 if (info->is_sloppy() && !IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1538 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, receiver,
1539 Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver));
1540 }
1541
1542 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, info->data(), *receiver, *holder,
1543 Just(kDontThrow));
1544 Handle<JSAny> result = args.CallAccessorGetter(info, name);
1545 RETURN_EXCEPTION_IF_EXCEPTION(isolate);
1546 Handle<JSAny> reboxed_result(*result, isolate);
1547 if (info->replace_on_access() && IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1548 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate,
1549 Accessors::ReplaceAccessorWithDataProperty(
1550 isolate, receiver, holder, name, result));
1551 }
1552 return reboxed_result;
1553 }
1554
1555 auto accessor_pair = Cast<AccessorPair>(structure);
1556 // AccessorPair with 'cached' private property.
1557 if (it->TryLookupCachedProperty(accessor_pair)) {
1558 return Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetProperty(it));
1559 }
1560
1561 // Regular accessor.
1562 DirectHandle<Object> getter(accessor_pair->getter(), isolate);
1563 if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter)) {
1564 SaveAndSwitchContext save(isolate, holder->GetCreationContext().value());
1565 return Cast<JSAny>(Builtins::InvokeApiFunction(
1566 isolate, false, Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(getter), receiver, {},
1567 isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
1568 } else if (IsCallable(*getter)) {
1569 // TODO(rossberg): nicer would be to cast to some JSCallable here...
1570 return Object::GetPropertyWithDefinedGetter(receiver,
1571 Cast<JSReceiver>(getter));
1572 }
1573 // Getter is not a function.
1574 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1575}
1576
1577Maybe<bool> Object::SetPropertyWithAccessor(
1578 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
1579 Maybe<ShouldThrow> maybe_should_throw) {
1580 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1581 DirectHandle<Object> structure = it->GetAccessors();
1582 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1583 // In case of global IC, the receiver is the global object. Replace by the
1584 // global proxy.
1585 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*receiver)) {
1586 receiver =
1587 direct_handle(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*receiver)->global_proxy(), isolate);
1588 }
1589
1590 // We should never get here to initialize a const with the hole value since a
1591 // const declaration would conflict with the setter.
1592 DCHECK(!IsForeign(*structure));
1593
1594 // API style callbacks.
1595 DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1596 if (IsAccessorInfo(*structure)) {
1597 DirectHandle<Name> name = it->GetName();
1598 auto info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(structure);
1599
1600 if (!info->has_setter(isolate)) {
1601 // TODO(verwaest): We should not get here anymore once all AccessorInfos
1602 // are marked as special_data_property. They cannot both be writable and
1603 // not have a setter.
1604 return Just(true);
1605 }
1606
1607 if (info->is_sloppy() && !IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1608 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1609 isolate, receiver, Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1610 Nothing<bool>());
1611 }
1612
1613 PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, info->data(), *receiver, *holder,
1614 maybe_should_throw);
1615 bool result = args.CallAccessorSetter(info, name, value);
1616 RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
1617 // Ensure the setter callback respects the "should throw" value - it's
1618 // allowed to fail without throwing only in case of kDontThrow.
1619 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!result,
1620 GetShouldThrow(isolate, maybe_should_throw) == kDontThrow);
1621 return Just(result);
1622 }
1623
1624 // Regular accessor.
1625 DirectHandle<Object> setter(Cast<AccessorPair>(*structure)->setter(),
1626 isolate);
1627 if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter)) {
1628 SaveAndSwitchContext save(isolate, holder->GetCreationContext().value());
1629 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {value};
1630 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1631 isolate,
1632 Builtins::InvokeApiFunction(
1633 isolate, false, Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(setter), receiver,
1634 base::VectorOf(args), isolate->factory()->undefined_value()),
1635 Nothing<bool>());
1636 return Just(true);
1637 } else if (IsCallable(*setter)) {
1638 // TODO(rossberg): nicer would be to cast to some JSCallable here...
1639 return SetPropertyWithDefinedSetter(receiver, Cast<JSReceiver>(setter),
1640 value, maybe_should_throw);
1641 }
1642
1643 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, maybe_should_throw),
1644 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNoSetterInCallback,
1645 it->GetName(), it->GetHolder<JSObject>()));
1646}
1647
1648MaybeHandle<JSAny> Object::GetPropertyWithDefinedGetter(
1649 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> getter) {
1650 Isolate* isolate = getter->GetIsolate();
1651
1652 // Platforms with simulators like arm/arm64 expose a funny issue. If the
1653 // simulator has a separate JS stack pointer from the C++ stack pointer, it
1654 // can miss C++ stack overflows in the stack guard at the start of JavaScript
1655 // functions. It would be very expensive to check the C++ stack pointer at
1656 // that location. The best solution seems to be to break the impasse by
1657 // adding checks at possible recursion points. What's more, we don't put
1658 // this stack check behind the USE_SIMULATOR define in order to keep
1659 // behavior the same between hardware and simulators.
1660 StackLimitCheck check(isolate);
1661 if (check.JsHasOverflowed()) {
1662 isolate->StackOverflow();
1663 return kNullMaybeHandle;
1664 }
1665
1666 return Cast<JSAny>(Execution::Call(isolate, getter, receiver, {}));
1667}
1668
1669Maybe<bool> Object::SetPropertyWithDefinedSetter(
1670 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> setter,
1671 DirectHandle<Object> value, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1672 Isolate* isolate = setter->GetIsolate();
1673
1674 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {value};
1675 RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1676 isolate, Execution::Call(isolate, setter, receiver, base::VectorOf(args)),
1677 Nothing<bool>());
1678 return Just(true);
1679}

1681// static
1682Tagged<Map> Object::GetPrototypeChainRootMap(Tagged<Object> obj,
1683 Isolate* isolate) {
1684 DisallowGarbageCollection no_alloc;
1685 if (IsSmi(obj)) {
1686 Tagged<Context> native_context = isolate->context()->native_context();
1687 return native_context->number_function()->initial_map();
1688 }
1689
1690 const Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object = Cast<HeapObject>(obj);
1691 return heap_object->map()->GetPrototypeChainRootMap(isolate);
1692}

1694// static
1695Tagged<Smi> Object::GetOrCreateHash(Tagged<Object> obj, Isolate* isolate) {
1696 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1697 Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetSimpleHash(obj);
1698 if (IsSmi(hash)) return Cast<Smi>(hash);
1699
1700 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(obj));
1701 return Cast<JSReceiver>(obj)->GetOrCreateIdentityHash(isolate);
1702}
1703
1704// static
1705bool Object::SameValue(Tagged<Object> obj, Tagged<Object> other) {
1706 if (other == obj) return true;
1707
1708 if (IsNumber(obj) && IsNumber(other)) {
1709 return SameNumberValue(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(obj)),
1710 Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(other)));
1711 }
1712 if (IsString(obj) && IsString(other)) {
1713 return Cast<String>(obj)->Equals(Cast<String>(other));
1714 }
1715 if (IsBigInt(obj) && IsBigInt(other)) {
1716 return BigInt::EqualToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(obj), Cast<BigInt>(other));
1717 }
1718 return false;
1719}
1720
1721// static
1722bool Object::SameValueZero(Tagged<Object> obj, Tagged<Object> other) {
1723 if (other == obj) return true;
1724
1725 if (IsNumber(obj) && IsNumber(other)) {
1726 double this_value = Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(obj));
1727 double other_value = Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(other));
1728 // +0 == -0 is true
1729 return this_value == other_value ||
1730 (std::isnan(this_value) && std::isnan(other_value));
1731 }
1732 if (IsString(obj) && IsString(other)) {
1733 return Cast<String>(obj)->Equals(Cast<String>(other));
1734 }
1735 if (IsBigInt(obj) && IsBigInt(other)) {
1736 return BigInt::EqualToBigInt(Cast<BigInt>(obj), Cast<BigInt>(other));
1737 }
1738 return false;
1739}
1740
1741MaybeHandle<Object> Object::ArraySpeciesConstructor(
1742 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSAny> original_array) {
1743 Handle<Object> default_species = isolate->array_function();
1744 if (!v8_flags.builtin_subclassing) return default_species;
1745 if (IsJSArray(*original_array) &&
1746 Cast<JSArray>(original_array)->HasArrayPrototype(isolate) &&
1747 Protectors::IsArraySpeciesLookupChainIntact(isolate)) {
1748 return default_species;
1749 }
1750 Handle<Object> constructor = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1751 Maybe<bool> is_array = IsArray(original_array);
1752 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(is_array);
1753 if (is_array.FromJust()) {
1754 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1755 isolate, constructor,
1756 Object::GetProperty(isolate, original_array,
1757 isolate->factory()->constructor_string()));
1758 if (IsConstructor(*constructor)) {
1759 DirectHandle<NativeContext> constructor_context;
1760 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1761 isolate, constructor_context,
1762 JSReceiver::GetFunctionRealm(Cast<JSReceiver>(constructor)));
1763 if (*constructor_context != *isolate->native_context() &&
1764 *constructor == constructor_context->array_function()) {
1765 constructor = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1766 }
1767 }
1768 if (IsJSReceiver(*constructor)) {
1769 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1770 isolate, constructor,
1771 JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(constructor),
1772 isolate->factory()->species_symbol()));
1773 if (IsNull(*constructor, isolate)) {
1774 constructor = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1775 }
1776 }
1777 }
1778 if (IsUndefined(*constructor, isolate)) {
1779 return default_species;
1780 } else {
1781 if (!IsConstructor(*constructor)) {
1782 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1783 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSpeciesNotConstructor));
1784 }
1785 return constructor;
1786 }
1787}
1788
1789// ES6 section 7.3.20 SpeciesConstructor ( O, defaultConstructor )
1790V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT MaybeHandle<Object> Object::SpeciesConstructor(
1791 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> recv,
1792 Handle<JSFunction> default_ctor) {
1793 DirectHandle<Object> ctor_obj;
1794 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1795 isolate, ctor_obj,
1796 JSObject::GetProperty(isolate, recv,
1797 isolate->factory()->constructor_string()));
1798
1799 if (IsUndefined(*ctor_obj, isolate)) return default_ctor;
1800
1801 if (!IsJSReceiver(*ctor_obj)) {
1802 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1803 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kConstructorNotReceiver));
1804 }
1805
1806 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> ctor = Cast<JSReceiver>(ctor_obj);
1807
1808 Handle<Object> species;
1809 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1810 isolate, species,
1811 JSObject::GetProperty(isolate, ctor,
1812 isolate->factory()->species_symbol()));
1813
1814 if (IsNullOrUndefined(*species, isolate)) {
1815 return default_ctor;
1816 }
1817
1818 if (IsConstructor(*species)) return species;
1819
1820 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
1821 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kSpeciesNotConstructor));
1822}
1823
1824// static
1825bool Object::IterationHasObservableEffects(Tagged<Object> obj) {
1826 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1827 // Check that this object is an array.
1828 if (!IsJSArray(obj)) return true;
1829 Tagged<JSArray> array = Cast<JSArray>(obj);
1830
1831 // Check that we have the original ArrayPrototype.
1832 Tagged<Object> array_proto = array->map()->prototype();
1833 if (!IsJSObject(array_proto)) return true;
1834 Tagged<NativeContext> native_context = array->GetCreationContext().value();
1835 auto initial_array_prototype = native_context->initial_array_prototype();
1836 if (initial_array_prototype != array_proto) return true;
1837
1838 Isolate* isolate = array->GetIsolate();
1839 // Check that the ArrayPrototype hasn't been modified in a way that would
1840 // affect iteration.
1841 if (!Protectors::IsArrayIteratorLookupChainIntact(isolate)) return true;
1842
1843 // For FastPacked kinds, iteration will have the same effect as simply
1844 // accessing each property in order.
1845 ElementsKind array_kind = array->GetElementsKind();
1846 if (IsFastPackedElementsKind(array_kind)) return false;
1847
1848 // For FastHoley kinds, an element access on a hole would cause a lookup on
1849 // the prototype. This could have different results if the prototype has been
1850 // changed.
1851 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(array_kind) &&
1852 Protectors::IsNoElementsIntact(isolate)) {
1853 return false;
1854 }
1855 return true;
1856}
1857
1858// static
1859bool Object::IsCodeLike(Tagged<Object> obj, Isolate* isolate) {
1860 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1861 return IsJSReceiver(obj) && Cast<JSReceiver>(obj)->IsCodeLike(isolate);
1862}

1892std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const Brief& v) {
1893 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_object(v.value);
1894 Tagged<Smi> smi;
1895 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
1896 if (maybe_object.ToSmi(&smi)) {
1897 Smi::SmiPrint(smi, os);
1898 } else if (maybe_object.IsCleared()) {
1899 os << "[cleared]";
1900 } else if (maybe_object.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object)) {
1901 os << "[weak] ";
1902 heap_object->HeapObjectShortPrint(os);
1903 } else if (maybe_object.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object)) {
1904 heap_object->HeapObjectShortPrint(os);
1905 } else {
1906 UNREACHABLE();
1907 }
1908 return os;
1909}
