1935
1936int HeapObject::SizeFromMap(Tagged<Map> map) const {
1937 int instance_size = map->instance_size();
1938 if (instance_size != kVariableSizeSentinel) return instance_size;
1939 // Only inline the most frequent cases.
1940 InstanceType instance_type = map->instance_type();
1941 if (base::IsInRange(instance_type, FIRST_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE,
1942 LAST_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
1943 return UncheckedCast<FixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1944 }
1945#define CASE(TypeCamelCase, TYPE_UPPER_CASE) \
1946 if (instance_type == TYPE_UPPER_CASE##_TYPE) { \
1947 return UncheckedCast<TypeCamelCase>(*this)->AllocatedSize(); \
1948 }
1949 SIMPLE_HEAP_OBJECT_LIST2(CASE)
1950#undef CASE
1951 if (instance_type == SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS_TYPE) {
1952 return UncheckedCast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1953 }
1954 if (base::IsInRange(instance_type, FIRST_CONTEXT_TYPE, LAST_CONTEXT_TYPE)) {
1955 if (instance_type == NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE) return NativeContext::kSize;
1956 return Context::SizeFor(UncheckedCast<Context>(*this)->length());
1957 }
1958 if (instance_type == SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE ||
1959 instance_type == INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE ||
1960 instance_type == SHARED_SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE) {
1961 // Strings may get concurrently truncated, hence we have to access its
1962 // length synchronized.
1963 return SeqOneByteString::SizeFor(
1964 UncheckedCast<SeqOneByteString>(*this)->length(kAcquireLoad));
1965 }
1966 if (instance_type == BYTECODE_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1967 return BytecodeArray::SizeFor(
1968 UncheckedCast<BytecodeArray>(*this)->length(kAcquireLoad));
1969 }
1970 if (instance_type == FREE_SPACE_TYPE) {
1971 return UncheckedCast<FreeSpace>(*this)->size(kRelaxedLoad);
1972 }
1973 if (instance_type == SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE ||
1974 instance_type == INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE ||
1975 instance_type == SHARED_SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE) {
1976 // Strings may get concurrently truncated, hence we have to access its
1977 // length synchronized.
1978 return SeqTwoByteString::SizeFor(
1979 UncheckedCast<SeqTwoByteString>(*this)->length(kAcquireLoad));
1980 }
1981 if (instance_type == FIXED_DOUBLE_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1982 return UncheckedCast<FixedDoubleArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1983 }
1984 if (instance_type == TRUSTED_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1985 return UncheckedCast<TrustedFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1986 }
1987 if (instance_type == PROTECTED_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1988 return UncheckedCast<ProtectedFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1989 }
1990 if (instance_type == PROTECTED_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1991 return UncheckedCast<ProtectedWeakFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1992 }
1993 if (instance_type == TRUSTED_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1994 return UncheckedCast<TrustedWeakFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1995 }
1996 if (instance_type == TRUSTED_BYTE_ARRAY_TYPE) {
1997 return UncheckedCast<TrustedByteArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
1998 }
1999 if (instance_type == FEEDBACK_METADATA_TYPE) {
2000 return UncheckedCast<FeedbackMetadata>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
2001 }
2002 if (base::IsInRange(instance_type, FIRST_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE,
2003 LAST_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
2004 return DescriptorArray::SizeFor(
2005 UncheckedCast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->number_of_all_descriptors());
2006 }
2007 if (base::IsInRange(instance_type, FIRST_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE,
2008 LAST_WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
2009 return UncheckedCast<WeakFixedArray>(*this)->AllocatedSize();
2010 }
2011 if (instance_type == WEAK_ARRAY_LIST_TYPE) {
2012 return WeakArrayList::SizeForCapacity(
2013 UncheckedCast<WeakArrayList>(*this)->capacity());
2014 }
2015 if (instance_type == SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE) {
2016 return SmallOrderedHashSet::SizeFor(
2017 UncheckedCast<SmallOrderedHashSet>(*this)->Capacity());
2018 }
2019 if (instance_type == SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE) {
2020 return SmallOrderedHashMap::SizeFor(
2021 UncheckedCast<SmallOrderedHashMap>(*this)->Capacity());
2022 }
2023 if (instance_type == SMALL_ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE) {
2024 return SmallOrderedNameDictionary::SizeFor(
2025 UncheckedCast<SmallOrderedNameDictionary>(*this)->Capacity());
2026 }
2027 if (instance_type == SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE) {
2028 return SwissNameDictionary::SizeFor(
2029 UncheckedCast<SwissNameDictionary>(*this)->Capacity());
2030 }
2031 if (instance_type == PROPERTY_ARRAY_TYPE) {
2032 return PropertyArray::SizeFor(
2033 UncheckedCast<PropertyArray>(*this)->length(kAcquireLoad));
2034 }
2035 if (instance_type == FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE) {
2036 return FeedbackVector::SizeFor(
2037 UncheckedCast<FeedbackVector>(*this)->length());
2038 }
2039 if (instance_type == BIGINT_TYPE) {
2040 return BigInt::SizeFor(UncheckedCast<BigInt>(*this)->length());
2041 }
2042 if (instance_type == PREPARSE_DATA_TYPE) {
2043 Tagged<PreparseData> data = UncheckedCast<PreparseData>(*this);
2044 return PreparseData::SizeFor(data->data_length(), data->children_length());
2045 }
2046#define MAKE_TORQUE_SIZE_FOR(TYPE, TypeName) \
2047 if (instance_type == TYPE) { \
2048 return UncheckedCast<TypeName>(*this)->AllocatedSize(); \
2049 }
2050 TORQUE_INSTANCE_TYPE_TO_BODY_DESCRIPTOR_LIST(MAKE_TORQUE_SIZE_FOR)
2051#undef MAKE_TORQUE_SIZE_FOR
2052
2053 if (instance_type == INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE) {
2054 return UncheckedCast<InstructionStream>(*this)->Size();
2055 }
2056 if (instance_type == COVERAGE_INFO_TYPE) {
2057 return CoverageInfo::SizeFor(
2058 UncheckedCast<CoverageInfo>(*this)->slot_count());
2059 }
2060#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2061 if (instance_type == WASM_TYPE_INFO_TYPE) {
2062 return WasmTypeInfo::SizeFor(
2063 UncheckedCast<WasmTypeInfo>(*this)->supertypes_length());
2064 }
2065 if (instance_type == WASM_STRUCT_TYPE) {
2066 return WasmStruct::GcSafeSize(map);
2067 }
2068 if (instance_type == WASM_ARRAY_TYPE) {
2069 return WasmArray::SizeFor(map, UncheckedCast<WasmArray>(*this)->length());
2070 }
2071 if (instance_type == WASM_NULL_TYPE) {
2072 return WasmNull::kSize;
2073 }
2074 if (instance_type == WASM_DISPATCH_TABLE_TYPE) {
2075 return WasmDispatchTable::SizeFor(
2076 UncheckedCast<WasmDispatchTable>(*this)->capacity());
2077 }
2078#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2079 DCHECK_EQ(instance_type, EMBEDDER_DATA_ARRAY_TYPE);
2080 return EmbedderDataArray::SizeFor(
2081 UncheckedCast<EmbedderDataArray>(*this)->length());
2082}
2083
2084bool HeapObject::NeedsRehashing(PtrComprCageBase cage_base) const {
2085 return NeedsRehashing(map(cage_base)->instance_type());
2086}
2087
2088bool HeapObject::NeedsRehashing(InstanceType instance_type) const {
2089 if (V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE_BOOL) {
2090 // Use map() only when it's guaranteed that it's not an InstructionStream
2091 // object.
2092 DCHECK_IMPLIES(instance_type != INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE,
2093 instance_type == map()->instance_type());
2094 } else {
2095 DCHECK_EQ(instance_type, map()->instance_type());
2096 }
2097 switch (instance_type) {
2098 case DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2099 case STRONG_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2100 return Cast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->number_of_descriptors() > 1;
2101 case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
2102 return Cast<TransitionArray>(*this)->number_of_transitions() > 1;
2103 case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2104 case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2105 return false; // We'll rehash from the JSMap or JSSet referencing them.
2106 case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2107 case NAME_TO_INDEX_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2108 case REGISTERED_SYMBOL_TABLE_TYPE:
2109 case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2110 case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2111 case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2112 case HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2113 case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2114 case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2115 case SMALL_ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2116 case SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2117 case JS_MAP_TYPE:
2118 case JS_SET_TYPE:
2119 return true;
2120 default:
2121 return false;
2122 }
2123 UNREACHABLE();
2124}
2125
2126bool HeapObject::CanBeRehashed(PtrComprCageBase cage_base) const {
2127 DCHECK(NeedsRehashing(cage_base));
2128 switch (map(cage_base)->instance_type()) {
2129 case JS_MAP_TYPE:
2130 case JS_SET_TYPE:
2131 return true;
2132 case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2133 case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2134 UNREACHABLE(); // We'll rehash from the JSMap or JSSet referencing them.
2135 case ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2136 return false;
2137 case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2138 case NAME_TO_INDEX_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2139 case REGISTERED_SYMBOL_TABLE_TYPE:
2140 case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2141 case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2142 case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2143 case SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2144 return true;
2145 case DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2146 case STRONG_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2147 return true;
2148 case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
2149 return true;
2150 case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2151 return Cast<SmallOrderedHashMap>(*this)->NumberOfElements() == 0;
2152 case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2153 return Cast<SmallOrderedHashMap>(*this)->NumberOfElements() == 0;
2154 case SMALL_ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2155 return Cast<SmallOrderedNameDictionary>(*this)->NumberOfElements() == 0;
2156 default:
2157 return false;
2158 }
2159 UNREACHABLE();
2160}
2161
2162template <typename IsolateT>
2163void HeapObject::RehashBasedOnMap(IsolateT* isolate) {
2164 switch (map(isolate)->instance_type()) {
2165 case HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2166 Cast<ObjectHashTable>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2167 break;
2168 case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2169 Cast<NameDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2170 break;
2171 case NAME_TO_INDEX_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
2172 Cast<NameToIndexHashTable>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2173 break;
2174 case REGISTERED_SYMBOL_TABLE_TYPE:
2175 Cast<RegisteredSymbolTable>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2176 break;
2177 case SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2178 Cast<SwissNameDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2179 break;
2180 case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2181 Cast<GlobalDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2182 break;
2183 case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2184 Cast<NumberDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2185 break;
2186 case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2187 Cast<SimpleNumberDictionary>(*this)->Rehash(isolate);
2188 break;
2189 case DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2190 case STRONG_DESCRIPTOR_ARRAY_TYPE:
2191 DCHECK_LE(1, Cast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->number_of_descriptors());
2192 Cast<DescriptorArray>(*this)->Sort();
2193 break;
2194 case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
2195 Cast<TransitionArray>(*this)->Sort();
2196 break;
2197 case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2198 DCHECK_EQ(0, Cast<SmallOrderedHashMap>(*this)->NumberOfElements());
2199 break;
2200 case SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2201 DCHECK_EQ(0, Cast<SmallOrderedHashSet>(*this)->NumberOfElements());
2202 break;
2203 case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
2204 case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
2205 UNREACHABLE(); // We'll rehash from the JSMap or JSSet referencing them.
2206 case JS_MAP_TYPE: {
2207 Cast<JSMap>(*this)->Rehash(isolate->AsIsolate());
2208 break;
2209 }
2210 case JS_SET_TYPE: {
2211 Cast<JSSet>(*this)->Rehash(isolate->AsIsolate());
2212 break;
2213 }
2214 case SMALL_ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
2215 DCHECK_EQ(0, Cast<SmallOrderedNameDictionary>(*this)->NumberOfElements());
2216 break;
2217 case INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2218 case INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
2219 // Rare case, rehash read-only space strings before they are sealed.
2220 DCHECK(ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(*this));
2221 Cast<String>(*this)->EnsureHash();
2222 break;
2223 default:
2224 // TODO(ishell): remove once b/326043780 is no longer an issue.
2225 isolate->AsIsolate()->PushParamsAndDie(
2226 reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptr()), reinterpret_cast<void*>(map().ptr()),
2227 reinterpret_cast<void*>(
2228 static_cast<uintptr_t>(map()->instance_type())));
2229 UNREACHABLE();
2230 }
2231}
2232template void HeapObject::RehashBasedOnMap(Isolate* isolate);
2233template void HeapObject::RehashBasedOnMap(LocalIsolate* isolate);
2234
2235void DescriptorArray::GeneralizeAllFields(bool clear_constness) {
2236 int length = number_of_descriptors();
2237 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(length)) {
2238 PropertyDetails details = GetDetails(i);
2239 details = details.CopyWithRepresentation(Representation::Tagged());
2240 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
2241 // Since constness is not propagated across proto transitions we must
2242 // clear the flag here.
2243 if (clear_constness) {
2244 details = details.CopyWithConstness(PropertyConstness::kMutable);
2245 }
2246 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
2247 SetValue(i, FieldType::Any());
2248 }
2249 SetDetails(i, details);
2250 }
2251}
2252
2253MaybeHandle<Object> Object::SetProperty(Isolate* isolate,
2254 DirectHandle<JSAny> object,
2255 DirectHandle<Name> name,
2256 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2257 StoreOrigin store_origin,
2258 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2259 LookupIterator it(isolate, object, name);
2260 MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(SetProperty(&it, value, store_origin, should_throw));
2261 return indirect_handle(value, isolate);
2262}
2263
2264Maybe<bool> Object::SetPropertyInternal(LookupIterator* it,
2265 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2266 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
2267 StoreOrigin store_origin, bool* found) {
2268 it->UpdateProtector();
2269 DCHECK(it->IsFound());
2270
2271 // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
2272 // interceptor calls.
2273 AssertNoContextChange ncc(it->isolate());
2274
2275 for (;; it->Next()) {
2276 switch (it->state()) {
2277 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
2278 if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
2279 // Check whether it makes sense to reuse the lookup iterator. Here it
2280 // might still call into setters up the prototype chain.
2281 return JSObject::SetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(it, value,
2282 should_throw);
2283
2284 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
2285 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
2286 // In case of global IC, the receiver is the global object. Replace by
2287 // the global proxy.
2288 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*receiver)) {
2289 receiver = direct_handle(
2290 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*receiver)->global_proxy(), it->isolate());
2291 }
2292 return JSProxy::SetProperty(it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(), it->GetName(),
2293 value, receiver, should_throw);
2294 }
2295
2296 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
2297 RETURN_FAILURE(it->isolate(), kThrowOnError,
2298 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
2299
2300 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
2301 if (it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
2302 InterceptorResult result;
2303 if (!JSObject::SetPropertyWithInterceptor(it, should_throw, value)
2304 .To(&result)) {
2305 // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
2306 return Nothing<bool>();
2307 }
2308 switch (result) {
2309 case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
2310 return Just(false);
2311 case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
2312 return Just(true);
2313 case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
2314 // Proceed lookup.
2315 break;
2316 }
2317 // Assuming that the callback has side effects, we use
2318 // Object::SetSuperProperty() which works properly regardless on
2319 // whether the property was present on the receiver or not when
2320 // storing to the receiver.
2321 // Proceed lookup from the next state.
2322 it->Next();
2323 } else {
2324 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> maybe_attributes =
2325 JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptor(it);
2326 if (maybe_attributes.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
2327 if ((maybe_attributes.FromJust() & READ_ONLY) != 0) {
2328 return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2329 }
2330 // At this point we might have called interceptor's query or getter
2331 // callback. Assuming that the callbacks have side effects, we use
2332 // Object::SetSuperProperty() which works properly regardless on
2333 // whether the property was present on the receiver or not when
2334 // storing to the receiver.
2335 if (maybe_attributes.FromJust() == ABSENT) {
2336 // Proceed lookup from the next state.
2337 it->Next();
2338 } else {
2339 // Finish lookup in order to make Object::SetSuperProperty() store
2340 // property to the receiver.
2341 it->NotFound();
2342 }
2343 }
2344 return Object::SetSuperProperty(it, value, store_origin, should_throw);
2345 }
2346
2347 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
2348 if (it->IsReadOnly()) {
2349 return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2350 }
2351 DirectHandle<Object> accessors = it->GetAccessors();
2352 if (IsAccessorInfo(*accessors) &&
2353 !it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
2354 *found = false;
2355 return Nothing<bool>();
2356 }
2357 return SetPropertyWithAccessor(it, value, should_throw);
2358 }
2359 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND: {
2360 // IntegerIndexedElementSet converts value to a Number/BigInt prior to
2361 // the bounds check. The bounds check has already happened here, but
2362 // perform the possibly effectful ToNumber (or ToBigInt) operation
2363 // anyways.
2364 DirectHandle<JSTypedArray> holder = it->GetHolder<JSTypedArray>();
2365 DirectHandle<Object> converted_value;
2366 if (holder->type() == kExternalBigInt64Array ||
2367 holder->type() == kExternalBigUint64Array) {
2368 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2369 it->isolate(), converted_value,
2370 BigInt::FromObject(it->isolate(), value), Nothing<bool>());
2371 } else {
2372 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2373 it->isolate(), converted_value,
2374 Object::ToNumber(it->isolate(), value), Nothing<bool>());
2375 }
2376
2377 // For RAB/GSABs, the above conversion might grow the buffer so that the
2378 // index is no longer out of bounds. Redo the bounds check and try
2379 // again.
2380 it->RecheckTypedArrayBounds();
2381 if (it->state() != LookupIterator::DATA) {
2382 // Still out of bounds.
2383 DCHECK_EQ(it->state(), LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND);
2384
2385 // FIXME: Throw a TypeError if the holder is detached here
2386 // (IntegerIndexedElementSet step 5).
2387
2388 // TODO(verwaest): Per spec, we should return false here (steps 6-9
2389 // in IntegerIndexedElementSet), resulting in an exception being
2390 // thrown on OOB accesses in strict code. Historically, v8 has not
2391 // done made this change due to uncertainty about web compat.
2392 // (v8:4901)
2393 return Just(true);
2394 }
2395 value = converted_value;
2396 [[fallthrough]];
2397 }
2398
2399 case LookupIterator::DATA:
2400 if (it->IsReadOnly()) {
2401 return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2402 }
2403 if (it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
2404 return SetDataProperty(it, value);
2405 }
2406 [[fallthrough]];
2407 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
2408 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
2409 *found = false;
2410 return Nothing<bool>();
2411 }
2412 UNREACHABLE();
2413 }
2414}
2415
2416bool Object::CheckContextualStoreToJSGlobalObject(
2417 LookupIterator* it, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2418 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2419
2420 if (IsJSGlobalObject(*it->GetReceiver(), isolate) &&
2421 (GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw) == ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)) {
2422 if (it->state() == LookupIterator::TRANSITION) {
2423 // The property cell that we have created is garbage because we are going
2424 // to throw now instead of putting it into the global dictionary. However,
2425 // the cell might already have been stored into the feedback vector, so
2426 // we must invalidate it nevertheless.
2427 it->transition_cell()->ClearAndInvalidate(isolate);
2428 }
2429 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewReferenceError(
2430 MessageTemplate::kNotDefined, it->GetName()));
2431 return false;
2432 }
2433 return true;
2434}
2435
2436Maybe<bool> Object::SetProperty(LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2437 StoreOrigin store_origin,
2438 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2439 if (it->IsFound()) {
2440 bool found = true;
2441 Maybe<bool> result =
2442 SetPropertyInternal(it, value, should_throw, store_origin, &found);
2443 if (found) return result;
2444 }
2445
2446 if (!CheckContextualStoreToJSGlobalObject(it, should_throw)) {
2447 return Nothing<bool>();
2448 }
2449 return AddDataProperty(it, value, NONE, should_throw, store_origin);
2450}
2451
2452Maybe<bool> Object::SetSuperProperty(LookupIterator* it,
2453 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2454 StoreOrigin store_origin,
2455 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2456 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2457
2458 if (it->IsFound()) {
2459 bool found = true;
2460 Maybe<bool> result =
2461 SetPropertyInternal(it, value, should_throw, store_origin, &found);
2462 if (found) return result;
2463 }
2464
2465 it->UpdateProtector();
2466
2467 // The property either doesn't exist on the holder or exists there as a data
2468 // property.
2469
2470 if (!IsJSReceiver(*it->GetReceiver())) {
2471 return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it, value, should_throw);
2472 }
2473 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(it->GetReceiver());
2474
2475 // Note, the callers rely on the fact that this code is redoing the full own
2476 // lookup from scratch.
2477 LookupIterator own_lookup(isolate, receiver, it->GetKey(),
2478 LookupIterator::OWN);
2479 for (;; own_lookup.Next()) {
2480 switch (own_lookup.state()) {
2481 case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
2482 if (!own_lookup.HasAccess()) {
2483 return JSObject::SetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(&own_lookup, value,
2484 should_throw);
2485 }
2486 continue;
2487
2488 case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
2489 if (IsAccessorInfo(*own_lookup.GetAccessors())) {
2490 if (own_lookup.IsReadOnly()) {
2491 return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(&own_lookup, value, should_throw);
2492 }
2493 return Object::SetPropertyWithAccessor(&own_lookup, value,
2494 should_throw);
2495 }
2496 [[fallthrough]];
2497 case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
2498 return RedefineIncompatibleProperty(isolate, it->GetName(), value,
2499 should_throw);
2500
2501 case LookupIterator::DATA: {
2502 if (own_lookup.IsReadOnly()) {
2503 return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(&own_lookup, value, should_throw);
2504 }
2505 return SetDataProperty(&own_lookup, value);
2506 }
2507
2508 case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
2509 case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
2510 PropertyDescriptor desc;
2511 Maybe<bool> owned =
2512 JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(&own_lookup, &desc);
2513 MAYBE_RETURN(owned, Nothing<bool>());
2514 if (!owned.FromJust()) {
2515 // |own_lookup| might become outdated at this point anyway.
2516 // TODO(leszeks): Remove this restart since we don't really use the
2517 // lookup iterator after this.
2518 own_lookup.Restart();
2519 if (!CheckContextualStoreToJSGlobalObject(&own_lookup,
2520 should_throw)) {
2521 return Nothing<bool>();
2522 }
2523 return JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, receiver, it->GetKey(),
2524 value, should_throw);
2525 }
2526 if (PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(&desc) ||
2527 !desc.writable()) {
2528 return RedefineIncompatibleProperty(isolate, it->GetName(), value,
2529 should_throw);
2530 }
2531
2532 PropertyDescriptor value_desc;
2533 value_desc.set_value(Cast<JSAny>(value));
2534 return JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, receiver, it->GetName(),
2535 &value_desc, should_throw);
2536 }
2537
2538 case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
2539 if (!CheckContextualStoreToJSGlobalObject(&own_lookup, should_throw)) {
2540 return Nothing<bool>();
2541 }
2542 return AddDataProperty(&own_lookup, value, NONE, should_throw,
2543 store_origin);
2544
2545 case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
2546 RETURN_FAILURE(it->isolate(), kThrowOnError,
2547 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
2548
2549 case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
2550 UNREACHABLE();
2551 }
2552 UNREACHABLE();
2553 }
2554}
2555
2556Maybe<bool> Object::CannotCreateProperty(Isolate* isolate,
2557 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver,
2558 DirectHandle<Object> name,
2559 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2560 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2561 RETURN_FAILURE(
2562 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
2563 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kStrictCannotCreateProperty, name,
2564 Object::TypeOf(isolate, receiver), receiver));
2565}
2566
2567Maybe<bool> Object::WriteToReadOnlyProperty(
2568 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2569 Maybe<ShouldThrow> maybe_should_throw) {
2570 ShouldThrow should_throw = GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), maybe_should_throw);
2571 if (it->IsFound() && !it->HolderIsReceiver()) {
2572 // "Override mistake" attempted, record a use count to track this per
2573 // v8:8175
2574 v8::Isolate::UseCounterFeature feature =
2575 should_throw == kThrowOnError
2576 ? v8::Isolate::kAttemptOverrideReadOnlyOnPrototypeStrict
2577 : v8::Isolate::kAttemptOverrideReadOnlyOnPrototypeSloppy;
2578 it->isolate()->CountUsage(feature);
2579 }
2580 return WriteToReadOnlyProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetReceiver(),
2581 it->GetName(), value, should_throw);
2582}
2583
2584Maybe<bool> Object::WriteToReadOnlyProperty(Isolate* isolate,
2585 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver,
2586 DirectHandle<Object> name,
2587 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2588 ShouldThrow should_throw) {
2589 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
2590 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kStrictReadOnlyProperty, name,
2591 Object::TypeOf(isolate, receiver), receiver));
2592}
2593
2594Maybe<bool> Object::RedefineIncompatibleProperty(
2595 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> name, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2596 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2597 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
2598 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed, name));
2599}
2600
2601Maybe<bool> Object::SetDataProperty(LookupIterator* it,
2602 DirectHandle<Object> value) {
2603 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2604 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsJSProxy(*it->GetReceiver(), isolate),
2605 it->GetName()->IsPrivateName());
2606 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!it->IsElement() && it->GetName()->IsPrivateName(),
2607 it->state() == LookupIterator::DATA);
2608 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(it->GetReceiver());
2609
2610 // Store on the holder which may be hidden behind the receiver.
2611 DCHECK(it->HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype());
2612
2613 DirectHandle<Object> to_assign = value;
2614 // Convert the incoming value to a number for storing into typed arrays.
2615 if (it->IsElement() && IsJSObject(*receiver, isolate) &&
2616 Cast<JSObject>(*receiver)->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements(
2617 isolate)) {
2618 auto receiver_ta = Cast<JSTypedArray>(receiver);
2619 ElementsKind elements_kind = Cast<JSObject>(*receiver)->GetElementsKind();
2620 if (IsBigIntTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
2621 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, to_assign,
2622 BigInt::FromObject(isolate, value),
2623 Nothing<bool>());
2624 if (V8_UNLIKELY(receiver_ta->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds() ||
2625 it->index() >= receiver_ta->GetLength())) {
2626 return Just(true);
2627 }
2628 } else if (!IsNumber(*value) && !IsUndefined(*value, isolate)) {
2629 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, to_assign,
2630 Object::ToNumber(isolate, value),
2631 Nothing<bool>());
2632 if (V8_UNLIKELY(receiver_ta->IsDetachedOrOutOfBounds() ||
2633 it->index() >= receiver_ta->GetLength())) {
2634 return Just(true);
2635 }
2636 }
2637 }
2638
2639 DCHECK(!IsWasmObject(*receiver, isolate));
2640 if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsJSSharedStruct(*receiver, isolate) ||
2641 IsJSSharedArray(*receiver, isolate))) {
2642 // Shared structs can only point to primitives or shared values.
2643 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2644 isolate, to_assign, Object::Share(isolate, to_assign, kThrowOnError),
2645 Nothing<bool>());
2646 it->WriteDataValue(to_assign, false);
2647 } else {
2648 // Possibly migrate to the most up-to-date map that will be able to store
2649 // |value| under it->name().
2650 it->PrepareForDataProperty(to_assign);
2651
2652 // Write the property value.
2653 it->WriteDataValue(to_assign, false);
2654 }
2655
2656#if VERIFY_HEAP
2657 if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
2658 receiver->HeapObjectVerify(isolate);
2659 }
2660#endif
2661 return Just(true);
2662}
2663
2664Maybe<bool> Object::AddDataProperty(LookupIterator* it,
2665 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2666 PropertyAttributes attributes,
2667 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
2668 StoreOrigin store_origin,
2669 EnforceDefineSemantics semantics) {
2670 if (!IsJSReceiver(*it->GetReceiver())) {
2671 return CannotCreateProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetReceiver(), it->GetName(),
2672 value, should_throw);
2673 }
2674
2675 // Private symbols should be installed on JSProxy using
2676 // JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol.
2677 if (IsJSProxy(*it->GetReceiver()) && it->GetName()->IsPrivate() &&
2678 !it->GetName()->IsPrivateName()) {
2679 RETURN_FAILURE(it->isolate(), GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), should_throw),
2680 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyPrivate));
2681 }
2682
2683 DCHECK_NE(LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND, it->state());
2684
2685 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = it->GetStoreTarget<JSReceiver>();
2686 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsJSProxy(*receiver), it->GetName()->IsPrivateName());
2687 DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsJSProxy(*receiver),
2688 it->state() == LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND);
2689
2690 // If the receiver is a JSGlobalProxy, store on the prototype (JSGlobalObject)
2691 // instead. If the prototype is Null, the proxy is detached.
2692 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*receiver)) return Just(true);
2693
2694 Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2695
2696 if (it->ExtendingNonExtensible(receiver)) {
2697 bool is_shared_object = IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*receiver);
2698 RETURN_FAILURE(
2699 isolate, GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), should_throw),
2700 NewTypeError(
2701 semantics == EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine
2702 ? (is_shared_object
2703 ? MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowedFixedLayout
2704 : MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed)
2705 : (is_shared_object ? MessageTemplate::kObjectFixedLayout
2706 : MessageTemplate::kObjectNotExtensible),
2707 it->GetName()));
2708 }
2709
2710 if (it->IsElement(*receiver)) {
2711 if (IsJSArray(*receiver)) {
2712 DirectHandle<JSArray> array = Cast<JSArray>(receiver);
2713 if (JSArray::WouldChangeReadOnlyLength(array, it->array_index())) {
2714 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(it->isolate(), should_throw),
2715 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kStrictReadOnlyProperty,
2716 isolate->factory()->length_string(),
2717 Object::TypeOf(isolate, array), array));
2718 }
2719 }
2720
2721 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver_obj = Cast<JSObject>(receiver);
2722 MAYBE_RETURN(JSObject::AddDataElement(receiver_obj, it->array_index(),
2723 value, attributes),
2724 Nothing<bool>());
2725 JSObject::ValidateElements(*receiver_obj);
2726 return Just(true);
2727 }
2728
2729 return Object::TransitionAndWriteDataProperty(it, value, attributes,
2730 should_throw, store_origin);
2731}
2732
2733// static
2734Maybe<bool> Object::TransitionAndWriteDataProperty(
2735 LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2736 PropertyAttributes attributes, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
2737 StoreOrigin store_origin) {
2738 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = it->GetStoreTarget<JSReceiver>();
2739 it->UpdateProtector();
2740 // Migrate to the most up-to-date map that will be able to store |value|
2741 // under it->name() with |attributes|.
2742 it->PrepareTransitionToDataProperty(receiver, value, attributes,
2743 store_origin);
2744 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::TRANSITION, it->state());
2745 it->ApplyTransitionToDataProperty(receiver);
2746
2747 // Write the property value.
2748 it->WriteDataValue(value, true);
2749
2750#if VERIFY_HEAP
2751 if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
2752 receiver->HeapObjectVerify(it->isolate());
2753 }
2754#endif
2755
2756 return Just(true);
2757}
2758
2759// static
2760template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
2761 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
2762typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType Object::ShareSlow(
2763 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<HeapObject> value,
2764 ShouldThrow throw_if_cannot_be_shared) {
2765 // Use Object::Share() if value might already be shared.
2766 DCHECK(!IsShared(*value));
2767
2768 SharedObjectSafePublishGuard publish_guard;
2769
2770 if (IsString(*value)) {
2771 return String::Share(isolate, Cast<String>(value));
2772 }
2773
2774 if (IsHeapNumber(*value)) {
2775 uint64_t bits = Cast<HeapNumber>(*value)->value_as_bits();
2776 return isolate->factory()
2777 ->NewHeapNumberFromBits<AllocationType::kSharedOld>(bits);
2778 }
2779
2780 if (throw_if_cannot_be_shared == kThrowOnError) {
2781 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
2782 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotBeShared, value));
2783 }
2784 return {};
2785}
2786
2787template V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MaybeDirectHandle<Object> Object::ShareSlow(
2788 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<HeapObject> value,
2789 ShouldThrow throw_if_cannot_be_shared);
2790template V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MaybeIndirectHandle<Object> Object::ShareSlow(
2791 Isolate* isolate, IndirectHandle<HeapObject> value,
2792 ShouldThrow throw_if_cannot_be_shared);

2794namespace {
2795
2796template <class T>
2797int AppendUniqueCallbacks(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<ArrayList> callbacks,
2798 DirectHandle<typename T::Array> array,
2799 int valid_descriptors) {
2800 int nof_callbacks = callbacks->length();
2801
2802 // Fill in new callback descriptors. Process the callbacks from
2803 // back to front so that the last callback with a given name takes
2804 // precedence over previously added callbacks with that name.
2805 for (int i = nof_callbacks - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
2806 DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> entry(Cast<AccessorInfo>(callbacks->get(i)),
2807 isolate);
2808 DirectHandle<Name> key(Cast<Name>(entry->name()), isolate);
2809 DCHECK(IsUniqueName(*key));
2810 // Check if a descriptor with this name already exists before writing.
2811 if (!T::Contains(key, entry, valid_descriptors, array)) {
2812 T::Insert(key, entry, valid_descriptors, array);
2813 valid_descriptors++;
2814 }
2815 }
2816
2817 return valid_descriptors;
2818}
2819
2820struct FixedArrayAppender {
2821 using Array = FixedArray;
2822 static bool Contains(DirectHandle<Name> key, DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> entry,
2823 int valid_descriptors, DirectHandle<FixedArray> array) {
2824 for (int i = 0; i < valid_descriptors; i++) {
2825 if (*key == Cast<AccessorInfo>(array->get(i))->name()) return true;
2826 }
2827 return false;
2828 }
2829 static void Insert(DirectHandle<Name> key, DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> entry,
2830 int valid_descriptors, DirectHandle<FixedArray> array) {
2831 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2832 array->set(valid_descriptors, *entry);
2833 }
2834};
2835
2836} // namespace
2837
2838int AccessorInfo::AppendUnique(Isolate* isolate,
2839 DirectHandle<Object> descriptors,
2840 DirectHandle<FixedArray> array,
2841 int valid_descriptors) {
2842 auto callbacks = Cast<ArrayList>(descriptors);
2843 DCHECK_GE(array->length(), callbacks->length() + valid_descriptors);
2844 return AppendUniqueCallbacks<FixedArrayAppender>(isolate, callbacks, array,
2845 valid_descriptors);
2846}
2847
2848void JSProxy::Revoke(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy) {
2849 Isolate* isolate = proxy->GetIsolate();
2850 // ES#sec-proxy-revocation-functions
2851 if (!proxy->IsRevoked()) {
2852 // 5. Set p.[[ProxyTarget]] to null.
2853 proxy->set_target(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).null_value());
2854 // 6. Set p.[[ProxyHandler]] to null.
2855 proxy->set_handler(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).null_value());
2856 }
2857 DCHECK(proxy->IsRevoked());
2858}
2859
2860// static
2861Maybe<bool> JSProxy::IsArray(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy) {
2862 Isolate* isolate = proxy->GetIsolate();
2863 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object = Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy);
2864 for (int i = 0; i < JSProxy::kMaxIterationLimit; i++) {
2865 proxy = Cast<JSProxy>(object);
2866 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
2867 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
2868 MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked,
2869 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked("IsArray")));
2870 return Nothing<bool>();
2871 }
2872 object = direct_handle(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
2873 if (IsJSArray(*object)) return Just(true);
2874 if (!IsJSProxy(*object)) return Just(false);
2875 }
2876
2877 // Too deep recursion, throw a RangeError.
2878 isolate->StackOverflow();
2879 return Nothing<bool>();
2880}
2881
2882Maybe<bool> JSProxy::HasProperty(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
2883 DirectHandle<Name> name) {
2884 DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
2885 STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
2886 // 1. (Assert)
2887 // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
2888 DirectHandle<Object> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
2889 // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
2890 // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
2891 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
2892 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
2893 MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, isolate->factory()->has_string()));
2894 return Nothing<bool>();
2895 }
2896 // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot of O.
2897 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
2898 // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "has").
2899 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
2900 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2901 isolate, trap,
2902 Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler),
2903 isolate->factory()->has_string()),
2904 Nothing<bool>());
2905 // 7. If trap is undefined, then
2906 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
2907 // 7a. Return target.[[HasProperty]](P).
2908 return JSReceiver::HasProperty(isolate, target, name);
2909 }
2910 // 8. Let booleanTrapResult be ToBoolean(? Call(trap, handler, Â«target, PÂ»)).
2911 DirectHandle<Object> trap_result_obj;
2912 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name};
2913 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2914 isolate, trap_result_obj,
2915 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
2916 Nothing<bool>());
2917 bool boolean_trap_result = Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result_obj, isolate);
2918 // 9. If booleanTrapResult is false, then:
2919 if (!boolean_trap_result) {
2920 MAYBE_RETURN(JSProxy::CheckHasTrap(isolate, name, target), Nothing<bool>());
2921 }
2922 // 10. Return booleanTrapResult.
2923 return Just(boolean_trap_result);
2924}
2925
2926Maybe<bool> JSProxy::CheckHasTrap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Name> name,
2927 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target) {
2928 // 9a. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
2929 PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
2930 Maybe<bool> target_found =
2931 JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, &target_desc);
2932 MAYBE_RETURN(target_found, Nothing<bool>());
2933 // 9b. If targetDesc is not undefined, then:
2934 if (target_found.FromJust()) {
2935 // 9b i. If targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is false, throw a TypeError
2936 // exception.
2937 if (!target_desc.configurable()) {
2938 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
2939 MessageTemplate::kProxyHasNonConfigurable, name));
2940 return Nothing<bool>();
2941 }
2942 // 9b ii. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
2943 Maybe<bool> extensible_target = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
2944 MAYBE_RETURN(extensible_target, Nothing<bool>());
2945 // 9b iii. If extensibleTarget is false, throw a TypeError exception.
2946 if (!extensible_target.FromJust()) {
2947 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
2948 MessageTemplate::kProxyHasNonExtensible, name));
2949 return Nothing<bool>();
2950 }
2951 }
2952 return Just(true);
2953}
2954
2955Maybe<bool> JSProxy::SetProperty(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
2956 DirectHandle<Name> name,
2957 DirectHandle<Object> value,
2958 DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver,
2959 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2960 DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
2961 Isolate* isolate = proxy->GetIsolate();
2962 STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
2963 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
2964 DirectHandle<String> trap_name = factory->set_string();
2965
2966 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
2967 isolate->Throw(
2968 *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
2969 return Nothing<bool>();
2970 }
2971 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
2972 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
2973
2974 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
2975 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2976 isolate, trap, Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name),
2977 Nothing<bool>());
2978 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
2979 PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
2980 LookupIterator it(isolate, receiver, key, target);
2981
2982 return Object::SetSuperProperty(&it, value, StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
2983 should_throw);
2984 }
2985
2986 DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
2987 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name, value, receiver};
2988 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2989 isolate, trap_result,
2990 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
2991 Nothing<bool>());
2992 if (!Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate)) {
2993 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
2994 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsishFor,
2995 trap_name, name));
2996 }
2997
2998 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
2999 JSProxy::CheckGetSetTrapResult(isolate, name, target, value, kSet);
3000
3001 if (result.is_null()) {
3002 return Nothing<bool>();
3003 }
3004 return Just(true);
3005}
3006
3007Maybe<bool> JSProxy::DeletePropertyOrElement(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3008 DirectHandle<Name> name,
3009 LanguageMode language_mode) {
3010 DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
3011 ShouldThrow should_throw =
3012 is_sloppy(language_mode) ? kDontThrow : kThrowOnError;
3013 Isolate* isolate = proxy->GetIsolate();
3014 STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3015 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3016 DirectHandle<String> trap_name = factory->deleteProperty_string();
3017
3018 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3019 isolate->Throw(
3020 *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3021 return Nothing<bool>();
3022 }
3023 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3024 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
3025
3026 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3027 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3028 isolate, trap, Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name),
3029 Nothing<bool>());
3030 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3031 return JSReceiver::DeletePropertyOrElement(isolate, target, name,
3032 language_mode);
3033 }
3034
3035 DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
3036 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name};
3037 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3038 isolate, trap_result,
3039 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3040 Nothing<bool>());
3041 if (!Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate)) {
3042 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
3043 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsishFor,
3044 trap_name, name));
3045 }
3046
3047 // Enforce the invariant.
3048 return JSProxy::CheckDeleteTrap(isolate, name, target);
3049}
3050
3051Maybe<bool> JSProxy::CheckDeleteTrap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Name> name,
3052 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target) {
3053 // 10. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
3054 PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
3055 Maybe<bool> target_found =
3056 JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, &target_desc);
3057 MAYBE_RETURN(target_found, Nothing<bool>());
3058 // 11. If targetDesc is undefined, return true.
3059 if (target_found.FromJust()) {
3060 // 12. If targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3061 if (!target_desc.configurable()) {
3062 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3063 MessageTemplate::kProxyDeletePropertyNonConfigurable, name));
3064 return Nothing<bool>();
3065 }
3066 // 13. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
3067 Maybe<bool> extensible_target = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3068 MAYBE_RETURN(extensible_target, Nothing<bool>());
3069 // 14. If extensibleTarget is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3070 if (!extensible_target.FromJust()) {
3071 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3072 MessageTemplate::kProxyDeletePropertyNonExtensible, name));
3073 return Nothing<bool>();
3074 }
3075 }
3076 return Just(true);
3077}
3078
3079// static
3080MaybeHandle<JSProxy> JSProxy::New(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> target,
3081 DirectHandle<Object> handler) {
3082 if (!IsJSReceiver(*target)) {
3083 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyNonObject));
3084 }
3085 if (!IsJSReceiver(*handler)) {
3086 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyNonObject));
3087 }
3088 return isolate->factory()->NewJSProxy(Cast<JSReceiver>(target),
3089 Cast<JSReceiver>(handler));
3090}
3091
3092Maybe<PropertyAttributes> JSProxy::GetPropertyAttributes(LookupIterator* it) {
3093 PropertyDescriptor desc;
3094 Maybe<bool> found = JSProxy::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
3095 it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(), it->GetName(), &desc);
3096 MAYBE_RETURN(found, Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
3097 if (!found.FromJust()) return Just(ABSENT);
3098 return Just(desc.ToAttributes());
3099}

3101// TODO(jkummerow): Consider unification with FastAsArrayLength() in
3102// accessors.cc.
3103bool PropertyKeyToArrayLength(DirectHandle<Object> value, uint32_t* length) {
3104 DCHECK(IsNumber(*value) || IsName(*value));
3105 if (Object::ToArrayLength(*value, length)) return true;
3106 if (IsString(*value)) return Cast<String>(*value)->AsArrayIndex(length);
3107 return false;
3108}
3109
3110bool PropertyKeyToArrayIndex(DirectHandle<Object> index_obj, uint32_t* output) {
3111 return PropertyKeyToArrayLength(index_obj, output) && *output != kMaxUInt32;
3112}
3113
3114// ES6 9.4.2.1
3115// static
3116Maybe<bool> JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(Isolate* isolate,
3117 DirectHandle<JSArray> o,
3118 DirectHandle<Object> name,
3119 PropertyDescriptor* desc,
3120 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
3121 if (IsName(*name)) {
3122 name = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(Cast<Name>(name));
3123 }
3124
3125 // 1. Assert: IsPropertyKey(P) is true. ("P" is |name|.)
3126 // 2. If P is "length", then:
3127 if (*name == ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).length_string()) {
3128 // 2a. Return ArraySetLength(A, Desc).
3129 return ArraySetLength(isolate, o, desc, should_throw);
3130 }
3131 // 3. Else if P is an array index, then:
3132 uint32_t index = 0;
3133 if (PropertyKeyToArrayIndex(name, &index)) {
3134 // 3a. Let oldLenDesc be OrdinaryGetOwnProperty(A, "length").
3135 PropertyDescriptor old_len_desc;
3136 Maybe<bool> success = GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
3137 isolate, o, isolate->factory()->length_string(), &old_len_desc);
3138 // 3b. (Assert)
3139 DCHECK(success.FromJust());
3140 USE(success);
3141 // 3c. Let oldLen be oldLenDesc.[[Value]].
3142 uint32_t old_len = 0;
3143 CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(*old_len_desc.value(), &old_len));
3144 // 3d. Let index be ToUint32(P).
3145 // (Already done above.)
3146 // 3e. (Assert)
3147 // 3f. If index >= oldLen and oldLenDesc.[[Writable]] is false,
3148 // return false.
3149 if (index >= old_len && old_len_desc.has_writable() &&
3150 !old_len_desc.writable()) {
3151 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3152 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed, name));
3153 }
3154 // 3g. Let succeeded be OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, P, Desc).
3155 Maybe<bool> succeeded =
3156 OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, o, name, desc, should_throw);
3157 // 3h. Assert: succeeded is not an abrupt completion.
3158 // In our case, if should_throw == kThrowOnError, it can be!
3159 // 3i. If succeeded is false, return false.
3160 if (succeeded.IsNothing() || !succeeded.FromJust()) return succeeded;
3161 // 3j. If index >= oldLen, then:
3162 if (index >= old_len) {
3163 // 3j i. Set oldLenDesc.[[Value]] to index + 1.
3164 old_len_desc.set_value(isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(index + 1));
3165 // 3j ii. Let succeeded be
3166 // OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, "length", oldLenDesc).
3167 succeeded = OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, o,
3168 isolate->factory()->length_string(),
3169 &old_len_desc, should_throw);
3170 // 3j iii. Assert: succeeded is true.
3171 DCHECK(succeeded.FromJust());
3172 USE(succeeded);
3173 }
3174 // 3k. Return true.
3175 return Just(true);
3176 }
3177
3178 // 4. Return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, P, Desc).
3179 return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, o, name, desc, should_throw);
3180}
3181
3182// Part of ES6 9.4.2.4 ArraySetLength.
3183// static
3184bool JSArray::AnythingToArrayLength(Isolate* isolate,
3185 Handle<Object> length_object,
3186 uint32_t* output) {
3187 // Fast path: check numbers and strings that can be converted directly
3188 // and unobservably.
3189 if (Object::ToArrayLength(*length_object, output)) return true;
3190 if (IsString(*length_object) &&
3191 Cast<String>(length_object)->AsArrayIndex(output)) {
3192 return true;
3193 }
3194 // Slow path: follow steps in ES6 9.4.2.4 "ArraySetLength".
3195 // 3. Let newLen be ToUint32(Desc.[[Value]]).
3196 DirectHandle<Number> uint32_v;
3197 if (!Object::ToUint32(isolate, length_object).ToHandle(&uint32_v)) {
3198 // 4. ReturnIfAbrupt(newLen).
3199 return false;
3200 }
3201 // 5. Let numberLen be ToNumber(Desc.[[Value]]).
3202 DirectHandle<Number> number_v;
3203 if (!Object::ToNumber(isolate, length_object).ToHandle(&number_v)) {
3204 // 6. ReturnIfAbrupt(newLen).
3205 return false;
3206 }
3207 // 7. If newLen != numberLen, throw a RangeError exception.
3208 if (Object::NumberValue(*uint32_v) != Object::NumberValue(*number_v)) {
3209 DirectHandle<Object> exception =
3210 isolate->factory()->NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength);
3211 isolate->Throw(*exception);
3212 return false;
3213 }
3214 CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(*uint32_v, output));
3215 return true;
3216}
3217
3218// ES6 9.4.2.4
3219// static
3220Maybe<bool> JSArray::ArraySetLength(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSArray> a,
3221 PropertyDescriptor* desc,
3222 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
3223 // 1. If the [[Value]] field of Desc is absent, then
3224 if (!desc->has_value()) {
3225 // 1a. Return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, "length", Desc).
3226 return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(
3227 isolate, a, isolate->factory()->length_string(), desc, should_throw);
3228 }
3229 // 2. Let newLenDesc be a copy of Desc.
3230 // (Actual copying is not necessary.)
3231 PropertyDescriptor* new_len_desc = desc;
3232 // 3. - 7. Convert Desc.[[Value]] to newLen.
3233 uint32_t new_len = 0;
3234 if (!AnythingToArrayLength(isolate, desc->value(), &new_len)) {
3235 DCHECK(isolate->has_exception());
3236 return Nothing<bool>();
3237 }
3238 // 8. Set newLenDesc.[[Value]] to newLen.
3239 // (Done below, if needed.)
3240 // 9. Let oldLenDesc be OrdinaryGetOwnProperty(A, "length").
3241 PropertyDescriptor old_len_desc;
3242 Maybe<bool> success = GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
3243 isolate, a, isolate->factory()->length_string(), &old_len_desc);
3244 // 10. (Assert)
3245 DCHECK(success.FromJust());
3246 USE(success);
3247 // 11. Let oldLen be oldLenDesc.[[Value]].
3248 uint32_t old_len = 0;
3249 CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(*old_len_desc.value(), &old_len));
3250 // 12. If newLen >= oldLen, then
3251 if (new_len >= old_len) {
3252 // 8. Set newLenDesc.[[Value]] to newLen.
3253 // 12a. Return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(A, "length", newLenDesc).
3254 new_len_desc->set_value(isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(new_len));
3255 return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, a,
3256 isolate->factory()->length_string(),
3257 new_len_desc, should_throw);
3258 }
3259 // 13. If oldLenDesc.[[Writable]] is false, return false.
3260 if (!old_len_desc.writable() ||
3261 // Also handle the {configurable: true} and enumerable changes
3262 // since we later use JSArray::SetLength instead of
3263 // OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty to change the length,
3264 // and it doesn't have access to the descriptor anymore.
3265 new_len_desc->configurable() ||
3266 (new_len_desc->has_enumerable() &&
3267 (old_len_desc.enumerable() != new_len_desc->enumerable()))) {
3268 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3269 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
3270 isolate->factory()->length_string()));
3271 }
3272 // 14. If newLenDesc.[[Writable]] is absent or has the value true,
3273 // let newWritable be true.
3274 bool new_writable = false;
3275 if (!new_len_desc->has_writable() || new_len_desc->writable()) {
3276 new_writable = true;
3277 } else {
3278 // 15. Else,
3279 // 15a. Need to defer setting the [[Writable]] attribute to false in case
3280 // any elements cannot be deleted.
3281 // 15b. Let newWritable be false. (It's initialized as "false" anyway.)
3282 // 15c. Set newLenDesc.[[Writable]] to true.
3283 // (Not needed.)
3284 }
3285 // Most of steps 16 through 19 is implemented by JSArray::SetLength.
3286 MAYBE_RETURN(JSArray::SetLength(a, new_len), Nothing<bool>());
3287 // Steps 19d-ii, 20.
3288 if (!new_writable) {
3289 PropertyDescriptor readonly;
3290 readonly.set_writable(false);
3291 success = OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, a,
3292 isolate->factory()->length_string(),
3293 &readonly, should_throw);
3294 DCHECK(success.FromJust());
3295 USE(success);
3296 }
3297 uint32_t actual_new_len = 0;
3298 CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(a->length(), &actual_new_len));
3299 // Steps 19d-v, 21. Return false if there were non-deletable elements.
3300 bool result = actual_new_len == new_len;
3301 if (!result) {
3302 RETURN_FAILURE(
3303 isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3304 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kStrictDeleteProperty,
3305 isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(actual_new_len - 1),
3306 a));
3307 }
3308 return Just(result);
3309}
3310
3311// ES6 9.5.6
3312// static
3313Maybe<bool> JSProxy::DefineOwnProperty(Isolate* isolate,
3314 DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3315 DirectHandle<Object> key,
3316 PropertyDescriptor* desc,
3317 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
3318 STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3319 if (IsSymbol(*key) && Cast<Symbol>(key)->IsPrivate()) {
3320 DCHECK(!Cast<Symbol>(key)->IsPrivateName());
3321 return JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol(isolate, proxy, Cast<Symbol>(key), desc,
3322 should_throw);
3323 }
3324 DirectHandle<String> trap_name = isolate->factory()->defineProperty_string();
3325 // 1. Assert: IsPropertyKey(P) is true.
3326 DCHECK(IsName(*key) || IsNumber(*key));
3327 // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
3328 DirectHandle<Object> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
3329 // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
3330 // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
3331 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3332 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3333 MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3334 return Nothing<bool>();
3335 }
3336 // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot of O.
3337 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3338 // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "defineProperty").
3339 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3340 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3341 isolate, trap,
3342 Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), trap_name),
3343 Nothing<bool>());
3344 // 7. If trap is undefined, then:
3345 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3346 // 7a. Return target.[[DefineOwnProperty]](P, Desc).
3347 return JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, target, key, desc,
3348 should_throw);
3349 }
3350 // 8. Let descObj be FromPropertyDescriptor(Desc).
3351 DirectHandle<Object> desc_obj = desc->ToObject(isolate);
3352 // 9. Let booleanTrapResult be
3353 // ToBoolean(? Call(trap, handler, Â«target, P, descObjÂ»)).
3354 DirectHandle<Name> property_name =
3355 IsName(*key) ? Cast<Name>(key)
3356 : Cast<Name>(isolate->factory()->NumberToString(key));
3357 // Do not leak private property names.
3358 DCHECK(!property_name->IsPrivate());
3359 DirectHandle<Object> trap_result_obj;
3360 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, property_name, desc_obj};
3361 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3362 isolate, trap_result_obj,
3363 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3364 Nothing<bool>());
3365 // 10. If booleanTrapResult is false, return false.
3366 if (!Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result_obj, isolate)) {
3367 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3368 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsishFor,
3369 trap_name, property_name));
3370 }
3371 // 11. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
3372 PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
3373 Maybe<bool> target_found =
3374 JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, key, &target_desc);
3375 MAYBE_RETURN(target_found, Nothing<bool>());
3376 // 12. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
3377 Maybe<bool> maybe_extensible = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3378 MAYBE_RETURN(maybe_extensible, Nothing<bool>());
3379 bool extensible_target = maybe_extensible.FromJust();
3380 // 13. If Desc has a [[Configurable]] field and if Desc.[[Configurable]]
3381 // is false, then:
3382 // 13a. Let settingConfigFalse be true.
3383 // 14. Else let settingConfigFalse be false.
3384 bool setting_config_false = desc->has_configurable() && !desc->configurable();
3385 // 15. If targetDesc is undefined, then
3386 if (!target_found.FromJust()) {
3387 // 15a. If extensibleTarget is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3388 if (!extensible_target) {
3389 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3390 MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyNonExtensible, property_name));
3391 return Nothing<bool>();
3392 }
3393 // 15b. If settingConfigFalse is true, throw a TypeError exception.
3394 if (setting_config_false) {
3395 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3396 MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyNonConfigurable, property_name));
3397 return Nothing<bool>();
3398 }
3399 } else {
3400 // 16. Else targetDesc is not undefined,
3401 // 16a. If IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor(extensibleTarget, Desc,
3402 // targetDesc) is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3403 Maybe<bool> valid = IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor(
3404 isolate, extensible_target, desc, &target_desc, property_name,
3405 Just(kDontThrow));
3406 MAYBE_RETURN(valid, Nothing<bool>());
3407 if (!valid.FromJust()) {
3408 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3409 MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyIncompatible, property_name));
3410 return Nothing<bool>();
3411 }
3412 // 16b. If settingConfigFalse is true and targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is
3413 // true, throw a TypeError exception.
3414 if (setting_config_false && target_desc.configurable()) {
3415 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3416 MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyNonConfigurable, property_name));
3417 return Nothing<bool>();
3418 }
3419 // 16c. If IsDataDescriptor(targetDesc) is true,
3420 // targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is
3421 // false, and targetDesc.[[Writable]] is true, then
3422 if (PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(&target_desc) &&
3423 !target_desc.configurable() && target_desc.writable()) {
3424 // 16c i. If Desc has a [[Writable]] field and Desc.[[Writable]] is false,
3425 // throw a TypeError exception.
3426 if (desc->has_writable() && !desc->writable()) {
3427 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3428 MessageTemplate::kProxyDefinePropertyNonConfigurableWritable,
3429 property_name));
3430 return Nothing<bool>();
3431 }
3432 }
3433 }
3434 // 17. Return true.
3435 return Just(true);
3436}
3437
3438// static
3439Maybe<bool> JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol(Isolate* isolate,
3440 DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3441 DirectHandle<Symbol> private_name,
3442 PropertyDescriptor* desc,
3443 Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
3444 // Despite the generic name, this can only add private data properties.
3445 if (!PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(desc) ||
3446 desc->ToAttributes() != DONT_ENUM) {
3447 RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
3448 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyPrivate));
3449 }
3450 DCHECK(proxy->map()->is_dictionary_map());
3451 DirectHandle<Object> value =
3452 desc->has_value() ? desc->value()
3453 : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
3454
3455 LookupIterator it(isolate, proxy, private_name, proxy);
3456
3457 if (it.IsFound()) {
3458 DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::DATA, it.state());
3459 DCHECK_EQ(DONT_ENUM, it.property_attributes());
3460 // We are not tracking constness for private symbols added to JSProxy
3461 // objects.
3462 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyConstness::kMutable, it.property_details().constness());
3463 it.WriteDataValue(value, false);
3464 return Just(true);
3465 }
3466
3467 PropertyDetails details(PropertyKind::kData, DONT_ENUM,
3468 PropertyConstness::kMutable);
3469 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3470 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> dict(proxy->property_dictionary_swiss(),
3471 isolate);
3472 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> result =
3473 SwissNameDictionary::Add(isolate, dict, private_name, value, details);
3474 if (!dict.is_identical_to(result)) proxy->SetProperties(*result);
3475 } else {
3476 DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dict(proxy->property_dictionary(), isolate);
3477 DirectHandle<NameDictionary> result =
3478 NameDictionary::Add(isolate, dict, private_name, value, details);
3479 if (!dict.is_identical_to(result)) proxy->SetProperties(*result);
3480 }
3481 return Just(true);
3482}
3483
3484// ES6 9.5.5
3485// static
3486Maybe<bool> JSProxy::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(Isolate* isolate,
3487 DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3488 DirectHandle<Name> name,
3489 PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
3490 DCHECK(!name->IsPrivate());
3491 STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3492
3493 DirectHandle<String> trap_name =
3494 isolate->factory()->getOwnPropertyDescriptor_string();
3495 // 1. (Assert)
3496 // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
3497 DirectHandle<Object> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
3498 // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
3499 // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
3500 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3501 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3502 MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3503 return Nothing<bool>();
3504 }
3505 // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot of O.
3506 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3507 // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "getOwnPropertyDescriptor").
3508 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3509 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3510 isolate, trap,
3511 Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), trap_name),
3512 Nothing<bool>());
3513 // 7. If trap is undefined, then
3514 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3515 // 7a. Return target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
3516 return JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, desc);
3517 }
3518 // 8. Let trapResultObj be ? Call(trap, handler, Â«target, PÂ»).
3519 Handle<JSAny> trap_result_obj;
3520 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, name};
3521 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3522 isolate, trap_result_obj,
3523 Cast<JSAny>(
3524 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args))),
3525 Nothing<bool>());
3526 // 9. If Type(trapResultObj) is neither Object nor Undefined, throw a
3527 // TypeError exception.
3528 if (!IsJSReceiver(*trap_result_obj) &&
3529 !IsUndefined(*trap_result_obj, isolate)) {
3530 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3531 MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorInvalid, name));
3532 return Nothing<bool>();
3533 }
3534 // 10. Let targetDesc be ? target.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
3535 PropertyDescriptor target_desc;
3536 Maybe<bool> found =
3537 JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, target, name, &target_desc);
3538 MAYBE_RETURN(found, Nothing<bool>());
3539 // 11. If trapResultObj is undefined, then
3540 if (IsUndefined(*trap_result_obj, isolate)) {
3541 // 11a. If targetDesc is undefined, return undefined.
3542 if (!found.FromJust()) return Just(false);
3543 // 11b. If targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is false, throw a TypeError
3544 // exception.
3545 if (!target_desc.configurable()) {
3546 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3547 MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorUndefined, name));
3548 return Nothing<bool>();
3549 }
3550 // 11c. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
3551 Maybe<bool> extensible_target = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3552 MAYBE_RETURN(extensible_target, Nothing<bool>());
3553 // 11d. (Assert)
3554 // 11e. If extensibleTarget is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3555 if (!extensible_target.FromJust()) {
3556 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3557 MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorNonExtensible, name));
3558 return Nothing<bool>();
3559 }
3560 // 11f. Return undefined.
3561 return Just(false);
3562 }
3563 // 12. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
3564 Maybe<bool> extensible_target = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3565 MAYBE_RETURN(extensible_target, Nothing<bool>());
3566 // 13. Let resultDesc be ? ToPropertyDescriptor(trapResultObj).
3567 if (!PropertyDescriptor::ToPropertyDescriptor(isolate, trap_result_obj,
3568 desc)) {
3569 DCHECK(isolate->has_exception());
3570 return Nothing<bool>();
3571 }
3572 // 14. Call CompletePropertyDescriptor(resultDesc).
3573 PropertyDescriptor::CompletePropertyDescriptor(isolate, desc);
3574 // 15. Let valid be IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor (extensibleTarget,
3575 // resultDesc, targetDesc).
3576 Maybe<bool> valid = IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor(
3577 isolate, extensible_target.FromJust(), desc, &target_desc, name,
3578 Just(kDontThrow));
3579 MAYBE_RETURN(valid, Nothing<bool>());
3580 // 16. If valid is false, throw a TypeError exception.
3581 if (!valid.FromJust()) {
3582 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3583 MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorIncompatible, name));
3584 return Nothing<bool>();
3585 }
3586 // 17. If resultDesc.[[Configurable]] is false, then
3587 if (!desc->configurable()) {
3588 // 17a. If targetDesc is undefined or targetDesc.[[Configurable]] is true:
3589 if (target_desc.is_empty() || target_desc.configurable()) {
3590 // 17a i. Throw a TypeError exception.
3591 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3592 MessageTemplate::kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorNonConfigurable,
3593 name));
3594 return Nothing<bool>();
3595 }
3596 // 17b. If resultDesc has a [[Writable]] field and resultDesc.[[Writable]]
3597 // is false, then
3598 if (desc->has_writable() && !desc->writable()) {
3599 // 17b i. If targetDesc.[[Writable]] is true, throw a TypeError exception.
3600 if (target_desc.writable()) {
3601 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
3602 MessageTemplate::
3603 kProxyGetOwnPropertyDescriptorNonConfigurableWritable,
3604 name));
3605 return Nothing<bool>();
3606 }
3607 }
3608 }
3609 // 18. Return resultDesc.
3610 return Just(true);
3611}
3612
3613Maybe<bool> JSProxy::PreventExtensions(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
3614 ShouldThrow should_throw) {
3615 Isolate* isolate = proxy->GetIsolate();
3616 STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3617 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3618 DirectHandle<String> trap_name = factory->preventExtensions_string();
3619
3620 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3621 isolate->Throw(
3622 *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3623 return Nothing<bool>();
3624 }
3625 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3626 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
3627
3628 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3629 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3630 isolate, trap, Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name),
3631 Nothing<bool>());
3632 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3633 return JSReceiver::PreventExtensions(isolate, target, should_throw);
3634 }
3635
3636 DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
3637 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target};
3638 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3639 isolate, trap_result,
3640 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3641 Nothing<bool>());
3642 if (!Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate)) {
3643 RETURN_FAILURE(
3644 isolate, should_throw,
3645 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsish, trap_name));
3646 }
3647
3648 // Enforce the invariant.
3649 Maybe<bool> target_result = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3650 MAYBE_RETURN(target_result, Nothing<bool>());
3651 if (target_result.FromJust()) {
3652 isolate->Throw(*factory->NewTypeError(
3653 MessageTemplate::kProxyPreventExtensionsExtensible));
3654 return Nothing<bool>();
3655 }
3656 return Just(true);
3657}
3658
3659Maybe<bool> JSProxy::IsExtensible(DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy) {
3660 Isolate* isolate = proxy->GetIsolate();
3661 STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
3662 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3663 DirectHandle<String> trap_name = factory->isExtensible_string();
3664
3665 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
3666 isolate->Throw(
3667 *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
3668 return Nothing<bool>();
3669 }
3670 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
3671 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> handler(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->handler()), isolate);
3672
3673 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
3674 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3675 isolate, trap, Object::GetMethod(isolate, handler, trap_name),
3676 Nothing<bool>());
3677 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
3678 return JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3679 }
3680
3681 DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
3682 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target};
3683 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3684 isolate, trap_result,
3685 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
3686 Nothing<bool>());
3687
3688 // Enforce the invariant.
3689 Maybe<bool> target_result = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
3690 MAYBE_RETURN(target_result, Nothing<bool>());
3691 if (target_result.FromJust() != Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate)) {
3692 isolate->Throw(
3693 *factory->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyIsExtensibleInconsistent,
3694 factory->ToBoolean(target_result.FromJust())));
3695 return Nothing<bool>();
3696 }
3697 return target_result;
3698}
3699
3700Handle<DescriptorArray> DescriptorArray::CopyUpTo(
3701 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> desc, int enumeration_index,
3702 int slack) {
3703 return DescriptorArray::CopyUpToAddAttributes(isolate, desc,
3704 enumeration_index, NONE, slack);
3705}
3706
3707Handle<DescriptorArray> DescriptorArray::CopyUpToAddAttributes(
3708 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> source_handle,
3709 int enumeration_index, PropertyAttributes attributes, int slack) {
3710 if (enumeration_index + slack == 0) {
3711 return isolate->factory()->empty_descriptor_array();
3712 }
3713
3714 int size = enumeration_index;
3715 Handle<DescriptorArray> copy_handle =
3716 DescriptorArray::Allocate(isolate, size, slack);
3717
3718 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3719 Tagged<DescriptorArray> source = *source_handle;
3720 Tagged<DescriptorArray> copy = *copy_handle;
3721
3722 if (attributes != NONE) {
3723 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(size)) {
3724 Tagged<MaybeObject> value_or_field_type = source->GetValue(i);
3725 Tagged<Name> key = source->GetKey(i);
3726 PropertyDetails details = source->GetDetails(i);
3727 // Bulk attribute changes never affect private properties.
3728 if (!key->IsPrivate()) {
3729 int mask = DONT_DELETE | DONT_ENUM;
3730 // READ_ONLY is an invalid attribute for JS setters/getters.
3731 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
3732 if (details.kind() != PropertyKind::kAccessor ||
3733 !(value_or_field_type.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object) &&
3734 IsAccessorPair(heap_object))) {
3735 mask |= READ_ONLY;
3736 }
3737 details = details.CopyAddAttributes(
3738 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(attributes & mask));
3739 }
3740 copy->Set(i, key, value_or_field_type, details);
3741 }
3742 } else {
3743 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(size)) {
3744 copy->CopyFrom(i, source);
3745 }
3746 }
3747
3748 if (source->number_of_descriptors() != enumeration_index) copy->Sort();
3749
3750 return copy_handle;
3751}
3752
3753bool DescriptorArray::IsEqualUpTo(Tagged<DescriptorArray> desc,
3754 int nof_descriptors) {
3755 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(nof_descriptors)) {
3756 if (GetKey(i) != desc->GetKey(i) || GetValue(i) != desc->GetValue(i)) {
3757 return false;
3758 }
3759 PropertyDetails details = GetDetails(i);
3760 PropertyDetails other_details = desc->GetDetails(i);
3761 if (details.kind() != other_details.kind() ||
3762 details.location() != other_details.location() ||
3763 !details.representation().Equals(other_details.representation())) {
3764 return false;
3765 }
3766 }
3767 return true;
3768}
3769
3770// static
3771Handle<WeakArrayList> PrototypeUsers::Add(Isolate* isolate,
3772 Handle<WeakArrayList> array,
3773 DirectHandle<Map> value,
3774 int* assigned_index) {
3775 int length = array->length();
3776 if (length == 0) {
3777 // Uninitialized WeakArrayList; need to initialize empty_slot_index.
3778 array = WeakArrayList::EnsureSpace(isolate, array, kFirstIndex + 1);
3779 set_empty_slot_index(*array, kNoEmptySlotsMarker);
3780 array->Set(kFirstIndex, MakeWeak(*value));
3781 array->set_length(kFirstIndex + 1);
3782 if (assigned_index != nullptr) *assigned_index = kFirstIndex;
3783 return array;
3784 }
3785
3786 // If the array has unfilled space at the end, use it.
3787 if (!array->IsFull()) {
3788 array->Set(length, MakeWeak(*value));
3789 array->set_length(length + 1);
3790 if (assigned_index != nullptr) *assigned_index = length;
3791 return array;
3792 }
3793
3794 // If there are empty slots, use one of them.
3795 int empty_slot = Smi::ToInt(empty_slot_index(*array));
3796
3797 if (empty_slot == kNoEmptySlotsMarker) {
3798 // GCs might have cleared some references, rescan the array for empty slots.
3799 PrototypeUsers::ScanForEmptySlots(*array);
3800 empty_slot = Smi::ToInt(empty_slot_index(*array));
3801 }
3802
3803 if (empty_slot != kNoEmptySlotsMarker) {
3804 DCHECK_GE(empty_slot, kFirstIndex);
3805 CHECK_LT(empty_slot, array->length());
3806 int next_empty_slot = array->Get(empty_slot).ToSmi().value();
3807
3808 array->Set(empty_slot, MakeWeak(*value));
3809 if (assigned_index != nullptr) *assigned_index = empty_slot;
3810
3811 set_empty_slot_index(*array, next_empty_slot);
3812 return array;
3813 } else {
3814 DCHECK_EQ(empty_slot, kNoEmptySlotsMarker);
3815 }
3816
3817 // Array full and no empty slots. Grow the array.
3818 array = WeakArrayList::EnsureSpace(isolate, array, length + 1);
3819 array->Set(length, MakeWeak(*value));
3820 array->set_length(length + 1);
3821 if (assigned_index != nullptr) *assigned_index = length;
3822 return array;
3823}
3824
3825// static
3826void PrototypeUsers::ScanForEmptySlots(Tagged<WeakArrayList> array) {
3827 for (int i = kFirstIndex; i < array->length(); i++) {
3828 if (array->Get(i).IsCleared()) {
3829 PrototypeUsers::MarkSlotEmpty(array, i);
3830 }
3831 }
3832}
3833
3834Tagged<WeakArrayList> PrototypeUsers::Compact(DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> array,
3835 Heap* heap,
3836 CompactionCallback callback,
3837 AllocationType allocation) {
3838 if (array->length() == 0) {
3839 return *array;
3840 }
3841 int new_length = kFirstIndex + array->CountLiveWeakReferences();
3842 if (new_length == array->length()) {
3843 return *array;
3844 }
3845
3846 DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> new_array = WeakArrayList::EnsureSpace(
3847 heap->isolate(),
3848 handle(ReadOnlyRoots(heap).empty_weak_array_list(), heap->isolate()),
3849 new_length, allocation);
3850 // Allocation might have caused GC and turned some of the elements into
3851 // cleared weak heap objects. Count the number of live objects again.
3852 int copy_to = kFirstIndex;
3853 for (int i = kFirstIndex; i < array->length(); i++) {
3854 Tagged<MaybeObject> element = array->Get(i);
3855 Tagged<HeapObject> value;
3856 if (element.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&value)) {
3857 callback(value, i, copy_to);
3858 new_array->Set(copy_to++, element);
3859 } else {
3860 DCHECK(element.IsCleared() || element.IsSmi());
3861 }
3862 }
3863 new_array->set_length(copy_to);
3864 set_empty_slot_index(*new_array, kNoEmptySlotsMarker);
3865 return *new_array;
3866}

3875 : isolate->factory()->NewDescriptorArray(nof_descriptors, slack,
3876 allocation);
3877}

3880 AllocationType allocation);

3883 AllocationType allocation);

3885void DescriptorArray::Initialize(Tagged<EnumCache> empty_enum_cache,
3886 Tagged<HeapObject> undefined_value,
3887 int nof_descriptors, int slack,
3888 uint32_t raw_gc_state) {
3889 DCHECK_GE(nof_descriptors, 0);

3892 set_number_of_all_descriptors(nof_descriptors + slack);
3893 set_number_of_descriptors(nof_descriptors);
3894 set_raw_gc_state(raw_gc_state, kRelaxedStore);
3895 set_enum_cache(empty_enum_cache, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3896 MemsetTagged(GetDescriptorSlot(0), undefined_value,
3897 number_of_all_descriptors() * kEntrySize);
3898}

3930
3931void DescriptorArray::Sort() {
3932 // In-place heap sort.
3933 const int len = number_of_descriptors();
3934 // Reset sorting since the descriptor array might contain invalid pointers.
3935 for (int i = 0; i < len; ++i) SetSortedKey(i, i);
3936 // Bottom-up max-heap construction.
3937 // Index of the last node with children.
3938 int max_parent_index = (len / 2) - 1;
3939 for (int i = max_parent_index; i >= 0; --i) {
3940 int parent_index = i;
3941 const uint32_t parent_hash = GetSortedKey(i)->hash();
3942 while (parent_index <= max_parent_index) {
3943 int child_index = 2 * parent_index + 1;
3944 uint32_t child_hash = GetSortedKey(child_index)->hash();
3945 if (child_index + 1 < len) {
3946 uint32_t right_child_hash = GetSortedKey(child_index + 1)->hash();
3947 if (right_child_hash > child_hash) {
3948 child_index++;
3949 child_hash = right_child_hash;
3950 }
3951 }
3952 if (child_hash <= parent_hash) break;
3953 SwapSortedKeys(parent_index, child_index);
3954 // Now element at child_index could be < its children.
3955 parent_index = child_index; // parent_hash remains correct.
3956 }
3957 }
3958
3959 // Extract elements and create sorted array.
3960 for (int i = len - 1; i > 0; --i) {
3961 // Put max element at the back of the array.
3962 SwapSortedKeys(0, i);
3963 // Shift down the new top element.
3964 int parent_index = 0;
3965 const uint32_t parent_hash = GetSortedKey(parent_index)->hash();
3966 max_parent_index = (i / 2) - 1;
3967 while (parent_index <= max_parent_index) {
3968 int child_index = parent_index * 2 + 1;
3969 uint32_t child_hash = GetSortedKey(child_index)->hash();
3970 if (child_index + 1 < i) {
3971 uint32_t right_child_hash = GetSortedKey(child_index + 1)->hash();
3972 if (right_child_hash > child_hash) {
3973 child_index++;
3974 child_hash = right_child_hash;
3975 }
3976 }
3977 if (child_hash <= parent_hash) break;
3978 SwapSortedKeys(parent_index, child_index);
3979 parent_index = child_index;
3980 }
3981 }
3982 DCHECK(IsSortedNoDuplicates());
3983}
3984
3985void DescriptorArray::CheckNameCollisionDuringInsertion(Descriptor* desc,
3986 uint32_t desc_hash,
3987 int insertion_index) {
3988 DCHECK_GE(insertion_index, 0);
3989 DCHECK_LE(insertion_index, number_of_all_descriptors());
3990
3991 if (insertion_index <= 0) return;
3992
3993 for (int i = insertion_index; i > 0; --i) {
3994 Tagged<Name> current_key = GetSortedKey(i - 1);
3995 if (current_key->hash() != desc_hash) return;
3996 CHECK(current_key != *desc->GetKey());
3997 }
3998}
