4000Handle<AccessorPair> AccessorPair::Copy(Isolate* isolate,
4001 DirectHandle<AccessorPair> pair) {
4002 Handle<AccessorPair> copy = isolate->factory()->NewAccessorPair();
4003 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4004 Tagged<AccessorPair> raw_src = *pair;
4005 Tagged<AccessorPair> raw_copy = *copy;
4006 raw_copy->set_getter(raw_src->getter());
4007 raw_copy->set_setter(raw_src->setter());
4008 return copy;
4009}
4010
4011Handle<JSAny> AccessorPair::GetComponent(
4012 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
4013 DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessor_pair, AccessorComponent component) {
4014 Handle<Object> accessor(accessor_pair->get(component), isolate);
4015 if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*accessor)) {
4016 // TODO(v8:5962): pass the right name here: "get "/"set " + prop.
4017 Handle<JSFunction> function =
4018 ApiNatives::InstantiateFunction(isolate, native_context,
4019 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(accessor))
4020 .ToHandleChecked();
4021 accessor_pair->set(component, *function, kReleaseStore);
4022 return function;
4023 }
4024 if (IsNull(*accessor, isolate)) {
4025 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
4026 }
4027 return Cast<JSAny>(accessor);
4028}

4030#ifdef DEBUG
4031bool DescriptorArray::IsEqualTo(Tagged<DescriptorArray> other) {
4032 if (number_of_all_descriptors() != other->number_of_all_descriptors()) {
4033 return false;
4034 }
4035 for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(number_of_descriptors())) {
4036 if (GetKey(i) != other->GetKey(i)) return false;
4037 if (GetDetails(i).AsSmi() != other->GetDetails(i).AsSmi()) return false;
4038 if (GetValue(i) != other->GetValue(i)) return false;
4039 }
4040 return true;
4041}

4044// static
4045MaybeHandle<String> Name::ToFunctionName(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Name> name) {
4046 if (IsString(*name)) return Cast<String>(name);
4047 // ES6 section 9.2.11 SetFunctionName, step 4.
4048 DirectHandle<Object> description(Cast<Symbol>(name)->description(), isolate);
4049 if (IsUndefined(*description, isolate)) {
4050 return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
4051 }
4052 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
4053 builder.AppendCharacter('[');
4054 builder.AppendString(Cast<String>(description));
4055 builder.AppendCharacter(']');
4056 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish(), isolate);
4057}
4058
4059// static
4060MaybeHandle<String> Name::ToFunctionName(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Name> name,
4061 DirectHandle<String> prefix) {
4062 DirectHandle<String> name_string;
4063 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, name_string,
4064 ToFunctionName(isolate, name));
4065 IncrementalStringBuilder builder(isolate);
4066 builder.AppendString(prefix);
4067 builder.AppendCharacter(' ');
4068 builder.AppendString(name_string);
4069 return indirect_handle(builder.Finish(), isolate);
4070}
4071
4072void Relocatable::PostGarbageCollectionProcessing(Isolate* isolate) {
4073 Relocatable* current = isolate->relocatable_top();
4074 while (current != nullptr) {
4075 current->PostGarbageCollection();
4076 current = current->prev_;
4077 }
4078}
4079
4080// Reserve space for statics needing saving and restoring.
4081int Relocatable::ArchiveSpacePerThread() { return sizeof(Relocatable*); }
4082
4083// Archive statics that are thread-local.
4084char* Relocatable::ArchiveState(Isolate* isolate, char* to) {
4085 *reinterpret_cast<Relocatable**>(to) = isolate->relocatable_top();
4086 isolate->set_relocatable_top(nullptr);
4087 return to + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
4088}
4089
4090// Restore statics that are thread-local.
4091char* Relocatable::RestoreState(Isolate* isolate, char* from) {
4092 isolate->set_relocatable_top(*reinterpret_cast<Relocatable**>(from));
4093 return from + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
4094}
4095
4096char* Relocatable::Iterate(RootVisitor* v, char* thread_storage) {
4097 Relocatable* top = *reinterpret_cast<Relocatable**>(thread_storage);
4098 Iterate(v, top);
4099 return thread_storage + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
4100}
4101
4102void Relocatable::Iterate(Isolate* isolate, RootVisitor* v) {
4103 Iterate(v, isolate->relocatable_top());
4104}
4105
4106void Relocatable::Iterate(RootVisitor* v, Relocatable* top) {
4107 Relocatable* current = top;
4108 while (current != nullptr) {
4109 current->IterateInstance(v);
4110 current = current->prev_;
4111 }
4112}
4113
4114namespace {
4115
4116template <typename sinkchar>
4117void WriteFixedArrayToFlat(Tagged<FixedArray> fixed_array, int length,
4118 Tagged<String> separator, sinkchar* sink,
4119 int sink_length) {
4120 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4121 CHECK_GT(length, 0);
4122 CHECK_LE(length, fixed_array->length());
4123#ifdef DEBUG
4124 sinkchar* sink_end = sink + sink_length;
4125#endif
4126
4127 const int separator_length = separator->length();
4128 const bool use_one_byte_separator_fast_path =
4129 separator_length == 1 && sizeof(sinkchar) == 1 &&
4130 StringShape(separator).IsSequentialOneByte();
4131 uint8_t separator_one_char;
4132 if (use_one_byte_separator_fast_path) {
4133 CHECK(StringShape(separator).IsSequentialOneByte());
4134 CHECK_EQ(separator->length(), 1);
4135 separator_one_char = Cast<SeqOneByteString>(separator)->GetChars(no_gc)[0];
4136 }
4137
4138 uint32_t num_separators = 0;
4139 uint32_t repeat_last = 0;
4140 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4141 Tagged<Object> element = fixed_array->get(i);
4142 const bool element_is_special = IsSmi(element);
4143
4144 // If element is a positive Smi, it represents the number of separators to
4145 // write. If it is a negative Smi, it reprsents the number of times the last
4146 // string is repeated.
4147 if (V8_UNLIKELY(element_is_special)) {
4148 int count;
4149 CHECK(Object::ToInt32(element, &count));
4150 if (count > 0) {
4151 num_separators = count;
4152 // Verify that Smis (number of separators) only occur when necessary:
4153 // 1) at the beginning
4154 // 2) at the end
4155 // 3) when the number of separators > 1
4156 // - It is assumed that consecutive Strings will have one
4157 // separator,
4158 // so there is no need for a Smi.
4159 DCHECK(i == 0 || i == length - 1 || num_separators > 1);
4160 } else {
4161 repeat_last = -count;
4162 // Repeat is only possible when the previous element is not special.
4163 DCHECK_GT(i, 0);
4164 DCHECK(IsString(fixed_array->get(i - 1)));
4165 }
4166 }
4167
4168 // Write separator(s) if necessary.
4169 if (num_separators > 0 && separator_length > 0) {
4170 // TODO(pwong): Consider doubling strategy employed by runtime-strings.cc
4171 // WriteRepeatToFlat().
4172 // Fast path for single character, single byte separators.
4173 if (use_one_byte_separator_fast_path) {
4174 DCHECK_LE(sink + num_separators, sink_end);
4175 memset(sink, separator_one_char, num_separators);
4176 DCHECK_EQ(separator_length, 1);
4177 sink += num_separators;
4178 } else {
4179 for (uint32_t j = 0; j < num_separators; j++) {
4180 DCHECK_LE(sink + separator_length, sink_end);
4181 String::WriteToFlat(separator, sink, 0, separator_length);
4182 sink += separator_length;
4183 }
4184 }
4185 num_separators = 0;
4186 }
4187
4188 // Repeat the last written string |repeat_last| times (including
4189 // separators).
4190 if (V8_UNLIKELY(repeat_last > 0)) {
4191 Tagged<Object> last_element = fixed_array->get(i - 1);
4192 int string_length = Cast<String>(last_element)->length();
4193 // The implemented logic requires that string length is > 0. Empty strings
4194 // are handled by repeating the separator (positive smi in the fixed
4195 // array) already.
4196 DCHECK_GT(string_length, 0);
4197 int length_with_sep = string_length + separator_length;
4198 // Only copy separators between elements, not at the start or beginning.
4199 sinkchar* copy_end =
4200 sink + (length_with_sep * repeat_last) - separator_length;
4201 int copy_length = length_with_sep;
4202 while (sink < copy_end - copy_length) {
4203 DCHECK_LE(sink + copy_length, sink_end);
4204 memcpy(sink, sink - copy_length, copy_length * sizeof(sinkchar));
4205 sink += copy_length;
4206 copy_length *= 2;
4207 }
4208 int remaining = static_cast<int>(copy_end - sink);
4209 if (remaining > 0) {
4210 DCHECK_LE(sink + remaining, sink_end);
4211 memcpy(sink, sink - remaining - separator_length,
4212 remaining * sizeof(sinkchar));
4213 sink += remaining;
4214 }
4215 repeat_last = 0;
4216 num_separators = 1;
4217 }
4218
4219 if (V8_LIKELY(!element_is_special)) {
4220 DCHECK(IsString(element));
4221 Tagged<String> string = Cast<String>(element);
4222 const int string_length = string->length();
4223
4224 DCHECK(string_length == 0 || sink < sink_end);
4225 String::WriteToFlat(string, sink, 0, string_length);
4226 sink += string_length;
4227
4228 // Next string element, needs at least one separator preceding it.
4229 num_separators = 1;
4230 }
4231 }
4232
4233 // Verify we have written to the end of the sink.
4234 DCHECK_EQ(sink, sink_end);
4235}
4236
4237} // namespace
4238
4239// static
4240Address JSArray::ArrayJoinConcatToSequentialString(Isolate* isolate,
4241 Address raw_fixed_array,
4242 intptr_t length,
4243 Address raw_separator,
4244 Address raw_dest) {
4245 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4246 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
4247 Tagged<FixedArray> fixed_array =
4248 Cast<FixedArray>(Tagged<Object>(raw_fixed_array));
4249 Tagged<String> separator = Cast<String>(Tagged<Object>(raw_separator));
4250 Tagged<String> dest = Cast<String>(Tagged<Object>(raw_dest));
4251 DCHECK(IsFixedArray(fixed_array));
4252 DCHECK(StringShape(dest).IsSequentialOneByte() ||
4253 StringShape(dest).IsSequentialTwoByte());
4254
4255 if (StringShape(dest).IsSequentialOneByte()) {
4256 WriteFixedArrayToFlat(fixed_array, static_cast<int>(length), separator,
4257 Cast<SeqOneByteString>(dest)->GetChars(no_gc),
4258 dest->length());
4259 } else {
4260 DCHECK(StringShape(dest).IsSequentialTwoByte());
4261 WriteFixedArrayToFlat(fixed_array, static_cast<int>(length), separator,
4262 Cast<SeqTwoByteString>(dest)->GetChars(no_gc),
4263 dest->length());
4264 }
4265 return dest.ptr();
4266}
4267
4268uint32_t StringHasher::MakeArrayIndexHash(uint32_t value, uint32_t length) {
4269 // For array indexes mix the length into the hash as an array index could
4270 // be zero.
4271 DCHECK_LE(length, String::kMaxArrayIndexSize);
4272 DCHECK(TenToThe(String::kMaxCachedArrayIndexLength) <
4273 (1 << String::kArrayIndexValueBits));
4274
4275 value <<= String::ArrayIndexValueBits::kShift;
4276 value |= length << String::ArrayIndexLengthBits::kShift;
4277
4278 DCHECK(String::IsIntegerIndex(value));
4279 DCHECK_EQ(length <= String::kMaxCachedArrayIndexLength,
4280 Name::ContainsCachedArrayIndex(value));
4281 return value;
4282}

4284void Oddball::Initialize(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Oddball> oddball,
4285 const char* to_string, DirectHandle<Number> to_number,
4286 const char* type_of, uint8_t kind) {
4287 DirectHandle<String> internalized_to_string =
4288 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(to_string);
4289 DirectHandle<String> internalized_type_of =
4290 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(type_of);
4291 if (IsHeapNumber(*to_number)) {
4292 oddball->set_to_number_raw_as_bits(
4293 Cast<HeapNumber>(to_number)->value_as_bits());
4294 } else {
4295 oddball->set_to_number_raw(Object::NumberValue(*to_number));
4296 }
4297 oddball->set_to_number(*to_number);
4298 oddball->set_to_string(*internalized_to_string);
4299 oddball->set_type_of(*internalized_type_of);
4300 oddball->set_kind(kind);
4301}

4303// static
4304int Script::GetEvalPosition(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> script) {
4305 DCHECK(script->compilation_type() == Script::CompilationType::kEval);
4306 int position = script->eval_from_position();
4307 if (position < 0) {
4308 // Due to laziness, the position may not have been translated from code
4309 // offset yet, which would be encoded as negative integer. In that case,
4310 // translate and set the position.
4311 if (!script->has_eval_from_shared()) {
4312 position = 0;
4313 } else {
4314 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(script->eval_from_shared(),
4315 isolate);
4316 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate, shared);
4317 position =
4318 shared->abstract_code(isolate)->SourcePosition(isolate, -position);
4319 }
4320 DCHECK_GE(position, 0);
4321 script->set_eval_from_position(position);
4322 }
4323 return position;
4324}

4327 DirectHandle<Script> script) {
4328 DCHECK(!script->has_line_ends());
4329 Tagged<Object> src_obj = script->source();
4330 if (IsString(src_obj)) {
4331 DirectHandle<String> src(Cast<String>(src_obj), isolate);
4332 return String::CalculateLineEndsVector(isolate, src, true);
4333 }
4334
4335 return String::LineEndsVector();
4336}

4338template <typename IsolateT>
4339// static
4340void Script::InitLineEndsInternal(IsolateT* isolate,
4341 DirectHandle<Script> script) {
4342 DCHECK(!script->has_line_ends());
4343 DCHECK(script->CanHaveLineEnds());
4344 Tagged<Object> src_obj = script->source();
4345 if (!IsString(src_obj)) {
4346 DCHECK(IsUndefined(src_obj, isolate));
4347 script->set_line_ends(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array());
4348 } else {
4349 DCHECK(IsString(src_obj));
4350 DirectHandle<String> src(Cast<String>(src_obj), isolate);
4351 DirectHandle<FixedArray> array =
4352 String::CalculateLineEnds(isolate, src, true);
4353 script->set_line_ends(*array);
4354 }
4355 DCHECK(IsFixedArray(script->line_ends()));
4356 DCHECK(script->has_line_ends());
4357}

4363 InitLineEnds(isolate, script);
4364 } else if (script->line_ends() ==
4365 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array()) {
4366 DCHECK(script->has_line_ends());
4367 script->set_line_ends(Smi::zero());
4368 DCHECK(!script->has_line_ends());
4369 }

4424namespace {
4425
4426template <typename Char>
4427bool GetPositionInfoSlowImpl(base::Vector<Char> source, int position,
4428 Script::PositionInfo* info) {
4429 DCHECK(DisallowPositionInfoSlow::IsAllowed());
4430 if (position < 0) {
4431 position = 0;
4432 }
4433 int line = 0;
4434 const auto begin = std::cbegin(source);
4435 const auto end = std::cend(source);
4436 for (auto line_begin = begin; line_begin < end;) {
4437 const auto line_end = std::find(line_begin, end, '\n');
4438 if (position <= (line_end - begin)) {
4439 info->line = line;
4440 info->column = static_cast<int>((begin + position) - line_begin);
4441 info->line_start = static_cast<int>(line_begin - begin);
4442 info->line_end = static_cast<int>(line_end - begin);
4443 return true;
4444 }
4445 ++line;
4446 line_begin = line_end + 1;
4447 }
4448 return false;
4449}
4450bool GetPositionInfoSlow(const Tagged<Script> script, int position,
4451 const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc,
4452 Script::PositionInfo* info) {
4453 if (!IsString(script->source())) {
4454 return false;
4455 }
4456 auto source = Cast<String>(script->source());
4457 const auto flat = source->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
4458 return flat.IsOneByte()
4459 ? GetPositionInfoSlowImpl(flat.ToOneByteVector(), position, info)
4460 : GetPositionInfoSlowImpl(flat.ToUC16Vector(), position, info);
4461}

4463int GetLineEnd(const String::LineEndsVector& vector, int line) {
4464 return vector[line];
4465}
4466
4467int GetLineEnd(const Tagged<FixedArray>& array, int line) {
4468 return Smi::ToInt(array->get(line));
4469}

4471int GetLength(const String::LineEndsVector& vector) {
4472 return static_cast<int>(vector.size());
4473}
4474
4475int GetLength(const Tagged<FixedArray>& array) { return array->length(); }
4476
4477template <typename LineEndsContainer>
4478bool GetLineEndsContainerPositionInfo(const LineEndsContainer& ends,
4479 int position, Script::PositionInfo* info,
4480 const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) {
4481 const int ends_len = GetLength(ends);
4482 if (ends_len == 0) return false;
4483
4484 // Return early on invalid positions. Negative positions behave as if 0 was
4485 // passed, and positions beyond the end of the script return as failure.
4486 if (position < 0) {
4487 position = 0;
4488 } else if (position > GetLineEnd(ends, ends_len - 1)) {
4489 return false;
4490 }
4491
4492 // Determine line number by doing a binary search on the line ends array.
4493 if (GetLineEnd(ends, 0) >= position) {
4494 info->line = 0;
4495 info->line_start = 0;
4496 info->column = position;
4497 } else {
4498 int left = 0;
4499 int right = ends_len - 1;
4500
4501 while (right > 0) {
4502 DCHECK_LE(left, right);
4503 const int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
4504 if (position > GetLineEnd(ends, mid)) {
4505 left = mid + 1;
4506 } else if (position <= GetLineEnd(ends, mid - 1)) {
4507 right = mid - 1;
4508 } else {
4509 info->line = mid;
4510 break;
4511 }
4512 }
4513 DCHECK(GetLineEnd(ends, info->line) >= position &&
4514 GetLineEnd(ends, info->line - 1) < position);
4515 info->line_start = GetLineEnd(ends, info->line - 1) + 1;
4516 info->column = position - info->line_start;
4517 }
4518
4519 return true;
4520}
4521
4522} // namespace
4523
4524void Script::AddPositionInfoOffset(PositionInfo* info,
4525 OffsetFlag offset_flag) const {
4526 // Add offsets if requested.
4527 if (offset_flag == OffsetFlag::kWithOffset) {
4528 if (info->line == 0) {
4529 info->column += column_offset();
4530 }
4531 info->line += line_offset();
4532 } else {
4533 DCHECK_EQ(offset_flag, OffsetFlag::kNoOffset);
4534 }
4535}
4536
4537template <typename LineEndsContainer>
4538bool Script::GetPositionInfoInternal(
4539 const LineEndsContainer& ends, int position, Script::PositionInfo* info,
4540 const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) const {
4541 if (!GetLineEndsContainerPositionInfo(ends, position, info, no_gc))
4542 return false;
4543
4544 // Line end is position of the linebreak character.
4545 info->line_end = GetLineEnd(ends, info->line);
4546 if (info->line_end > 0) {
4547 DCHECK(IsString(source()));
4548 Tagged<String> src = Cast<String>(source());
4549 if (src->length() >= static_cast<uint32_t>(info->line_end) &&
4550 src->Get(info->line_end - 1) == '\r') {
4551 info->line_end--;
4552 }
4553 }
4554
4555 return true;
4556}
4557
4558template bool Script::GetPositionInfoInternal<String::LineEndsVector>(
4559 const String::LineEndsVector& ends, int position,
4560 Script::PositionInfo* info, const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) const;
4561template bool Script::GetPositionInfoInternal<Tagged<FixedArray>>(
4562 const Tagged<FixedArray>& ends, int position, Script::PositionInfo* info,
4563 const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) const;
4564
4565bool Script::GetPositionInfo(int position, PositionInfo* info,
4566 OffsetFlag offset_flag) const {
4567 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4568
4569#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4570 // For wasm, we use the byte offset as the column.
4571 if (type() == Script::Type::kWasm) {
4572 DCHECK_LE(0, position);
4573 wasm::NativeModule* native_module = wasm_native_module();
4574 const wasm::WasmModule* module = native_module->module();
4575 if (module->functions.empty()) return false;
4576 info->line = 0;
4577 info->column = position;
4578 info->line_start = module->functions[0].code.offset();
4579 info->line_end = module->functions.back().code.end_offset();
4580 return true;
4581 }
4582#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4583
4584 if (!has_line_ends()) {
4585 // Slow mode: we do not have line_ends. We have to iterate through source.
4586 if (!GetPositionInfoSlow(*this, position, no_gc, info)) {
4587 return false;
4588 }
4589 } else {
4590 DCHECK(has_line_ends());
4591 Tagged<FixedArray> ends = Cast<FixedArray>(line_ends());
4592
4593 if (!GetPositionInfoInternal(ends, position, info, no_gc)) return false;
4594 }
4595
4596 AddPositionInfoOffset(info, offset_flag);
4597
4598 return true;
4599}
4600
4601bool Script::GetPositionInfoWithLineEnds(
4602 int position, PositionInfo* info, const String::LineEndsVector& line_ends,
4603 OffsetFlag offset_flag) const {
4604 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4605 if (!GetPositionInfoInternal(line_ends, position, info, no_gc)) return false;
4606
4607 AddPositionInfoOffset(info, offset_flag);
4608
4609 return true;
4610}
4611
4612bool Script::GetLineColumnWithLineEnds(
4613 int position, int& line, int& column,
4614 const String::LineEndsVector& line_ends) {
4615 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4616 PositionInfo info;
4617 if (!GetLineEndsContainerPositionInfo(line_ends, position, &info, no_gc)) {
4618 line = -1;
4619 column = -1;
4620 return false;
4621 }
4622
4623 line = info.line;
4624 column = info.column;
4625
4626 return true;
4627}

4659// static
4660Handle<String> Script::GetScriptHash(Isolate* isolate,
4661 DirectHandle<Script> script,
4662 bool forceForInspector) {
4663 if (script->origin_options().IsOpaque() && !forceForInspector) {
4664 return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
4665 }
4666
4667 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
4668 {
4669 Tagged<Object> maybe_source_hash = script->source_hash(cage_base);
4670 if (IsString(maybe_source_hash, cage_base)) {
4671 Handle<String> precomputed(Cast<String>(maybe_source_hash), isolate);
4672 if (precomputed->length() > 0) {
4673 return precomputed;
4674 }
4675 }
4676 }
4677
4678 DirectHandle<String> src_text;
4679 {
4680 Tagged<Object> maybe_script_source = script->source(cage_base);
4681
4682 if (!IsString(maybe_script_source, cage_base)) {
4683 return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
4684 }
4685 src_text = direct_handle(Cast<String>(maybe_script_source), isolate);
4686 }
4687
4688 char formatted_hash[kSizeOfFormattedSha256Digest];
4689
4690 std::unique_ptr<char[]> string_val = src_text->ToCString();
4691 size_t len = strlen(string_val.get());
4692 uint8_t hash[kSizeOfSha256Digest];
4693 SHA256_hash(string_val.get(), len, hash);
4694 FormatBytesToHex(formatted_hash, kSizeOfFormattedSha256Digest, hash,
4695 kSizeOfSha256Digest);
4696 formatted_hash[kSizeOfSha256Digest * 2] = '\0';
4697
4698 Handle<String> result =
4699 isolate->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(formatted_hash);
4700 script->set_source_hash(*result);
4701 return result;
4702}
4703
4704template <typename IsolateT>
4705MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Script::FindSharedFunctionInfo(
4706 DirectHandle<Script> script, IsolateT* isolate,
4707 FunctionLiteral* function_literal) {
4708 DCHECK(function_literal->shared_function_info().is_null());
4709 int function_literal_id = function_literal->function_literal_id();
4710 CHECK_NE(function_literal_id, kInvalidInfoId);
4711 // If this check fails, the problem is most probably the function id
4712 // renumbering done by AstFunctionLiteralIdReindexer; in particular, that
4713 // AstTraversalVisitor doesn't recurse properly in the construct which
4714 // triggers the mismatch.
4715 CHECK_LT(function_literal_id, script->infos()->length());
4716 Tagged<MaybeObject> shared = script->infos()->get(function_literal_id);
4717 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
4718 if (!shared.GetHeapObject(&heap_object) ||
4719 IsUndefined(heap_object, isolate)) {
4720 return MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>();
4721 }
4722 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> result(Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(heap_object),
4723 isolate);
4724 function_literal->set_shared_function_info(result);
4725 return result;
4726}
4727template MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Script::FindSharedFunctionInfo(
4728 DirectHandle<Script> script, Isolate* isolate,
4729 FunctionLiteral* function_literal);
4730template MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Script::FindSharedFunctionInfo(
4731 DirectHandle<Script> script, LocalIsolate* isolate,
4732 FunctionLiteral* function_literal);

4742 return Script();

4761
4762// ES6: 9.5.2 [[SetPrototypeOf]] (V)
4763// static
4764Maybe<bool> JSProxy::SetPrototype(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSProxy> proxy,
4765 DirectHandle<Object> value,
4766 bool from_javascript,
4767 ShouldThrow should_throw) {
4768 STACK_CHECK(isolate, Nothing<bool>());
4769 DirectHandle<Name> trap_name = isolate->factory()->setPrototypeOf_string();
4770 // 1. Assert: Either Type(V) is Object or Type(V) is Null.
4771 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*value) || IsNull(*value, isolate));
4772 // 2. Let handler be the value of the [[ProxyHandler]] internal slot of O.
4773 DirectHandle<Object> handler(proxy->handler(), isolate);
4774 // 3. If handler is null, throw a TypeError exception.
4775 // 4. Assert: Type(handler) is Object.
4776 if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
4777 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
4778 MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked, trap_name));
4779 return Nothing<bool>();
4780 }
4781 // 5. Let target be the value of the [[ProxyTarget]] internal slot.
4782 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target(Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target()), isolate);
4783 // 6. Let trap be ? GetMethod(handler, "getPrototypeOf").
4784 DirectHandle<Object> trap;
4785 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4786 isolate, trap,
4787 Object::GetMethod(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(handler), trap_name),
4788 Nothing<bool>());
4789 // 7. If trap is undefined, then return target.[[SetPrototypeOf]]().
4790 if (IsUndefined(*trap, isolate)) {
4791 return JSReceiver::SetPrototype(isolate, target, value, from_javascript,
4792 should_throw);
4793 }
4794 // 8. Let booleanTrapResult be ToBoolean(? Call(trap, handler, Â«target, VÂ»)).
4795 DirectHandle<Object> args[] = {target, value};
4796 DirectHandle<Object> trap_result;
4797 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
4798 isolate, trap_result,
4799 Execution::Call(isolate, trap, handler, base::VectorOf(args)),
4800 Nothing<bool>());
4801 bool bool_trap_result = Object::BooleanValue(*trap_result, isolate);
4802 // 9. If booleanTrapResult is false, return false.
4803 if (!bool_trap_result) {
4804 RETURN_FAILURE(
4805 isolate, should_throw,
4806 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsish, trap_name));
4807 }
4808 // 10. Let extensibleTarget be ? IsExtensible(target).
4809 Maybe<bool> is_extensible = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, target);
4810 if (is_extensible.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
4811 // 11. If extensibleTarget is true, return true.
4812 if (is_extensible.FromJust()) {
4813 if (bool_trap_result) return Just(true);
4814 RETURN_FAILURE(
4815 isolate, should_throw,
4816 NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyTrapReturnedFalsish, trap_name));
4817 }
4818 // 12. Let targetProto be ? target.[[GetPrototypeOf]]().
4819 DirectHandle<Object> target_proto;
4820 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, target_proto,
4821 JSReceiver::GetPrototype(isolate, target),
4822 Nothing<bool>());
4823 // 13. If SameValue(V, targetProto) is false, throw a TypeError exception.
4824 if (bool_trap_result && !Object::SameValue(*value, *target_proto)) {
4825 isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
4826 MessageTemplate::kProxySetPrototypeOfNonExtensible));
4827 return Nothing<bool>();
4828 }
4829 // 14. Return true.
4830 return Just(true);
4831}
4832
4833bool JSArray::SetLengthWouldNormalize(uint32_t new_length) {
4834 if (!HasFastElements()) return false;
4835 uint32_t capacity = static_cast<uint32_t>(elements()->length());
4836 uint32_t new_capacity;
4837 return JSArray::SetLengthWouldNormalize(GetHeap(), new_length) &&
4838 ShouldConvertToSlowElements(*this, capacity, new_length - 1,
4839 &new_capacity);
4840}
4841
4842void AllocationSite::ResetPretenureDecision() {
4843 set_pretenure_decision(kUndecided);
4844 set_memento_found_count(0);
4845 set_memento_create_count(0);
4846}
4847
4848AllocationType AllocationSite::GetAllocationType() const {
4849 PretenureDecision mode = pretenure_decision();
4850 // Zombie objects "decide" to be untenured.
4851 return mode == kTenure ? AllocationType::kOld : AllocationType::kYoung;
4852}
4853
4854bool AllocationSite::IsNested() {
4855 DCHECK(v8_flags.trace_track_allocation_sites);
4856 Tagged<Object> current = boilerplate()->GetHeap()->allocation_sites_list();
4857 while (IsAllocationSite(current)) {
4858 Tagged<AllocationSite> current_site = Cast<AllocationSite>(current);
4859 if (current_site->nested_site() == *this) {
4860 return true;
4861 }
4862 current = current_site->weak_next();
4863 }
4864 return false;
4865}
4866
4867bool AllocationSite::ShouldTrack(ElementsKind from, ElementsKind to) {
4868 if (!V8_ALLOCATION_SITE_TRACKING_BOOL) return false;
4869 return IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(from, to);
4870}
4871
4872const char* AllocationSite::PretenureDecisionName(PretenureDecision decision) {
4873 switch (decision) {
4874 case kUndecided:
4875 return "undecided";
4876 case kDontTenure:
4877 return "don't tenure";
4878 case kMaybeTenure:
4879 return "maybe tenure";
4880 case kTenure:
4881 return "tenure";
4882 case kZombie:
4883 return "zombie";
4884 default:
4885 UNREACHABLE();
4886 }
4887}
4888
4889// static
4890bool JSArray::MayHaveReadOnlyLength(Tagged<Map> js_array_map) {
4891 DCHECK(IsJSArrayMap(js_array_map));
4892 if (js_array_map->is_dictionary_map()) return true;
4893
4894 // Fast path: "length" is the first fast property of arrays with non
4895 // dictionary properties. Since it's not configurable, it's guaranteed to be
4896 // the first in the descriptor array.
4897 InternalIndex first(0);
4898 DCHECK(js_array_map->instance_descriptors()->GetKey(first) ==
4899 GetReadOnlyRoots().length_string());
4900 return js_array_map->instance_descriptors()->GetDetails(first).IsReadOnly();
4901}
4902
4903bool JSArray::HasReadOnlyLength(DirectHandle<JSArray> array) {
4904 Tagged<Map> map = array->map();
4905
4906 // If map guarantees that there can't be a read-only length, we are done.
4907 if (!MayHaveReadOnlyLength(map)) return false;
4908
4909 // Look at the object.
4910 Isolate* isolate = array->GetIsolate();
4911 LookupIterator it(isolate, array, isolate->factory()->length_string(), array,
4912 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
4913 CHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::ACCESSOR, it.state());
4914 return it.IsReadOnly();
4915}
4916
4917bool JSArray::WouldChangeReadOnlyLength(DirectHandle<JSArray> array,
4918 uint32_t index) {
4919 uint32_t length = 0;
4920 CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(array->length(), &length));
4921 if (length <= index) return HasReadOnlyLength(array);
4922 return false;
4923}
4924
4925const char* Symbol::PrivateSymbolToName() const {
4926 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
4927#define SYMBOL_CHECK_AND_PRINT(_, name) \
4928 if (this == roots.name()) return #name;
4929 PRIVATE_SYMBOL_LIST_GENERATOR(SYMBOL_CHECK_AND_PRINT, /* not used */)
4930#undef SYMBOL_CHECK_AND_PRINT
4931 return "UNKNOWN";
4932}
4933
4934v8::Promise::PromiseState JSPromise::status() const {
4935 int value = flags() & StatusBits::kMask;
4936 DCHECK(value == 0 || value == 1 || value == 2);
4937 return static_cast<v8::Promise::PromiseState>(value);
4938}
4939
4940void JSPromise::set_status(Promise::PromiseState status) {
4941 int value = flags() & ~StatusBits::kMask;
4942 set_flags(value | status);
4943}
4944
4945// static
4946const char* JSPromise::Status(v8::Promise::PromiseState status) {
4947 switch (status) {
4948 case v8::Promise::kFulfilled:
4949 return "fulfilled";
4950 case v8::Promise::kPending:
4951 return "pending";
4952 case v8::Promise::kRejected:
4953 return "rejected";
4954 }
4955 UNREACHABLE();
4956}
4957
4958// static
4959Handle<Object> JSPromise::Fulfill(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
4960 DirectHandle<Object> value) {
4961 Isolate* const isolate = promise->GetIsolate();
4962
4963#ifdef V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
4964 if (isolate->HasContextPromiseHooks()) {
4965 isolate->raw_native_context()->RunPromiseHook(
4966 PromiseHookType::kResolve, indirect_handle(promise, isolate),
4967 isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
4968 }
4969#endif
4970
4971 // 1. Assert: The value of promise.[[PromiseState]] is "pending".
4972 CHECK_EQ(Promise::kPending, promise->status());
4973
4974 // 2. Let reactions be promise.[[PromiseFulfillReactions]].
4975 DirectHandle<Object> reactions(promise->reactions(), isolate);
4976
4977 // 3. Set promise.[[PromiseResult]] to value.
4978 // 4. Set promise.[[PromiseFulfillReactions]] to undefined.
4979 // 5. Set promise.[[PromiseRejectReactions]] to undefined.
4980 promise->set_reactions_or_result(Cast<JSAny>(*value));
4981
4982 // 6. Set promise.[[PromiseState]] to "fulfilled".
4983 promise->set_status(Promise::kFulfilled);
4984
4985 // 7. Return TriggerPromiseReactions(reactions, value).
4986 return TriggerPromiseReactions(isolate, reactions, value,
4987 PromiseReaction::kFulfill);
4988}
4989
4990static void MoveMessageToPromise(Isolate* isolate,
4991 DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise) {
4992 if (!isolate->has_pending_message()) return;
4993
4994 if (isolate->debug()->is_active()) {
4995 DirectHandle<Object> message(isolate->pending_message(), isolate);
4996 DirectHandle<Symbol> key =
4997 isolate->factory()->promise_debug_message_symbol();
4998 Object::SetProperty(isolate, promise, key, message,
4999 StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
5000 Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError))
5001 .Assert();
5002 }
5003
5004 // The message object for a rejected promise was only stored for this purpose.
5005 // Clear it, otherwise we might leak memory.
5006 isolate->clear_pending_message();
5007}
5008
5009// static
5010Handle<Object> JSPromise::Reject(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
5011 DirectHandle<Object> reason,
5012 bool debug_event) {
5013 Isolate* const isolate = promise->GetIsolate();
5014 DCHECK(
5015 !reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate)->GetCurrentContext().IsEmpty());
5016
5017 MoveMessageToPromise(isolate, promise);
5018
5019 if (debug_event) isolate->debug()->OnPromiseReject(promise, reason);
5020 isolate->RunAllPromiseHooks(PromiseHookType::kResolve, promise,
5021 isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
5022
5023 // 1. Assert: The value of promise.[[PromiseState]] is "pending".
5024 CHECK_EQ(Promise::kPending, promise->status());
5025
5026 // 2. Let reactions be promise.[[PromiseRejectReactions]].
5027 DirectHandle<Object> reactions(promise->reactions(), isolate);
5028
5029 // 3. Set promise.[[PromiseResult]] to reason.
5030 // 4. Set promise.[[PromiseFulfillReactions]] to undefined.
5031 // 5. Set promise.[[PromiseRejectReactions]] to undefined.
5032 promise->set_reactions_or_result(Cast<JSAny>(*reason));
5033
5034 // 6. Set promise.[[PromiseState]] to "rejected".
5035 promise->set_status(Promise::kRejected);
5036
5037 // 7. If promise.[[PromiseIsHandled]] is false, perform
5038 // HostPromiseRejectionTracker(promise, "reject").
5039 if (!promise->has_handler()) {
5040 isolate->ReportPromiseReject(promise, reason, kPromiseRejectWithNoHandler);
5041 }
5042
5043 // 8. Return TriggerPromiseReactions(reactions, reason).
5044 return TriggerPromiseReactions(isolate, reactions, reason,
5045 PromiseReaction::kReject);
5046}
5047
5048// https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-promise-resolve-functions
5049// static
5050MaybeHandle<Object> JSPromise::Resolve(DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
5051 DirectHandle<Object> resolution_obj) {
5052 Isolate* const isolate = promise->GetIsolate();
5053 DCHECK(
5054 !reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate)->GetCurrentContext().IsEmpty());
5055
5056 isolate->RunPromiseHook(PromiseHookType::kResolve, promise,
5057 isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
5058
5059 // 7. If SameValue(resolution, promise) is true, then
5060 if (promise.is_identical_to(resolution_obj)) {
5061 // a. Let selfResolutionError be a newly created TypeError object.
5062 DirectHandle<Object> self_resolution_error =
5063 isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kPromiseCyclic,
5064 resolution_obj);
5065 // b. Return RejectPromise(promise, selfResolutionError).
5066 return Reject(promise, self_resolution_error);
5067 }
5068
5069 // 8. If Type(resolution) is not Object, then
5070 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> resolution_recv;
5071 if (!TryCast<JSReceiver>(resolution_obj, &resolution_recv)) {
5072 // a. Return FulfillPromise(promise, resolution).
5073 return Fulfill(promise, resolution_obj);
5074 }
5075
5076 // 9. Let then be Get(resolution, "then").
5077 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> then;
5078
5079 // Make sure a lookup of "then" on any JSPromise whose [[Prototype]] is the
5080 // initial %PromisePrototype% yields the initial method. In addition this
5081 // protector also guards the negative lookup of "then" on the intrinsic
5082 // %ObjectPrototype%, meaning that such lookups are guaranteed to yield
5083 // undefined without triggering any side-effects.
5084 if (IsJSPromise(*resolution_recv) &&
5085 resolution_recv->map()->prototype()->map()->instance_type() ==
5086 JS_PROMISE_PROTOTYPE_TYPE &&
5087 Protectors::IsPromiseThenLookupChainIntact(isolate)) {
5088 // We can skip the "then" lookup on {resolution} if its [[Prototype]]
5089 // is the (initial) Promise.prototype and the Promise#then protector
5090 // is intact, as that guards the lookup path for the "then" property
5091 // on JSPromise instances which have the (initial) %PromisePrototype%.
5092 then = isolate->promise_then();
5093 } else {
5094 then = JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, resolution_recv,
5095 isolate->factory()->then_string());
5096 }
5097
5098 // 10. If then is an abrupt completion, then
5099 DirectHandle<Object> then_action;
5100 if (!then.ToHandle(&then_action)) {
5101 // The "then" lookup can cause termination.
5102 if (!isolate->is_catchable_by_javascript(isolate->exception())) {
5103 return kNullMaybeHandle;
5104 }
5105
5106 // a. Return RejectPromise(promise, then.[[Value]]).
5107 DirectHandle<Object> reason(isolate->exception(), isolate);
5108 isolate->clear_exception();
5109 return Reject(promise, reason, false);
5110 }
5111
5112 // 11. Let thenAction be then.[[Value]].
5113 // 12. If IsCallable(thenAction) is false, then
5114 if (!IsCallable(*then_action)) {
5115 // a. Return FulfillPromise(promise, resolution).
5116 return Fulfill(promise, resolution_recv);
5117 }
5118
5119 // 13. Let job be NewPromiseResolveThenableJob(promise, resolution,
5120 // thenAction).
5121 DirectHandle<NativeContext> then_context;
5122 if (!JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(Cast<JSReceiver>(then_action))
5123 .ToHandle(&then_context)) {
5124 then_context = isolate->native_context();
5125 }
5126
5127 DirectHandle<PromiseResolveThenableJobTask> task =
5128 isolate->factory()->NewPromiseResolveThenableJobTask(
5129 promise, resolution_recv, Cast<JSReceiver>(then_action),
5130 then_context);
5131 if (isolate->debug()->is_active() && IsJSPromise(*resolution_recv)) {
5132 // Mark the dependency of the new {promise} on the {resolution}.
5133 Object::SetProperty(isolate, resolution_recv,
5134 isolate->factory()->promise_handled_by_symbol(),
5135 promise)
5136 .Check();
5137 }
5138 MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue = then_context->microtask_queue();
5139 if (microtask_queue) microtask_queue->EnqueueMicrotask(*task);
5140
5141 // 15. Return undefined.
5142 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
5143}
5144
5145// static
5146Handle<Object> JSPromise::TriggerPromiseReactions(
5147 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> reactions,
5148 DirectHandle<Object> argument, PromiseReaction::Type type) {
5149 CHECK(IsSmi(*reactions) || IsPromiseReaction(*reactions));
5150
5151 // We need to reverse the {reactions} here, since we record them
5152 // on the JSPromise in the reverse order.
5153 {
5154 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5155 Tagged<UnionOf<Smi, PromiseReaction>> current =
5156 Cast<UnionOf<Smi, PromiseReaction>>(*reactions);
5157 Tagged<UnionOf<Smi, PromiseReaction>> reversed = Smi::zero();
5158 while (!IsSmi(current)) {
5159 Tagged<UnionOf<Smi, PromiseReaction>> next =
5160 Cast<PromiseReaction>(current)->next();
5161 Cast<PromiseReaction>(current)->set_next(reversed);
5162 reversed = current;
5163 current = next;
5164 }
5165 reactions = direct_handle(reversed, isolate);
5166 }
5167
5168 // Morph the {reactions} into PromiseReactionJobTasks
5169 // and push them onto the microtask queue.
5170 while (!IsSmi(*reactions)) {
5171 auto task = Cast<HeapObject>(reactions);
5172 auto reaction = Cast<PromiseReaction>(task);
5173 reactions = direct_handle(reaction->next(), isolate);
5174
5175 // According to HTML, we use the context of the appropriate handler as the
5176 // context of the microtask. See step 3 of HTML's EnqueueJob:
5177 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/C/#enqueuejob(queuename,-job,-arguments)
5178 DirectHandle<NativeContext> handler_context;
5179
5180 DirectHandle<UnionOf<Undefined, JSCallable>> primary_handler;
5181 DirectHandle<UnionOf<Undefined, JSCallable>> secondary_handler;
5182 if (type == PromiseReaction::kFulfill) {
5183 primary_handler = direct_handle(reaction->fulfill_handler(), isolate);
5184 secondary_handler = direct_handle(reaction->reject_handler(), isolate);
5185 } else {
5186 primary_handler = direct_handle(reaction->reject_handler(), isolate);
5187 secondary_handler = direct_handle(reaction->fulfill_handler(), isolate);
5188 }
5189
5190 bool has_handler_context = false;
5191 if (IsJSReceiver(*primary_handler)) {
5192 has_handler_context =
5193 JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(Cast<JSReceiver>(primary_handler))
5194 .ToHandle(&handler_context);
5195 }
5196 if (!has_handler_context && IsJSReceiver(*secondary_handler)) {
5197 has_handler_context = JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(
5198 Cast<JSReceiver>(secondary_handler))
5199 .ToHandle(&handler_context);
5200 }
5201 if (!has_handler_context) handler_context = isolate->native_context();
5202
5203 static_assert(
5204 static_cast<int>(PromiseReaction::kSize) ==
5205 static_cast<int>(
5206 PromiseReactionJobTask::kSizeOfAllPromiseReactionJobTasks));
5207 if (type == PromiseReaction::kFulfill) {
5208 task->set_map(
5209 isolate,
5210 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).promise_fulfill_reaction_job_task_map(),
5211 kReleaseStore);
5212 Cast<PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask>(task)->set_argument(*argument);
5213 Cast<PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask>(task)->set_context(*handler_context);
5214 static_assert(
5215 static_cast<int>(PromiseReaction::kFulfillHandlerOffset) ==
5216 static_cast<int>(PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask::kHandlerOffset));
5217 static_assert(
5218 static_cast<int>(PromiseReaction::kPromiseOrCapabilityOffset) ==
5219 static_cast<int>(
5220 PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask::kPromiseOrCapabilityOffset));
5221#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
5222 static_assert(
5223 static_cast<int>(
5224 PromiseReaction::kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset) ==
5225 static_cast<int>(PromiseFulfillReactionJobTask::
5226 kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset));
5227#endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
5228 } else {
5229 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5230 task->set_map(
5231 isolate,
5232 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).promise_reject_reaction_job_task_map(),
5233 kReleaseStore);
5234 Cast<PromiseRejectReactionJobTask>(task)->set_argument(*argument);
5235 Cast<PromiseRejectReactionJobTask>(task)->set_context(*handler_context);
5236 Cast<PromiseRejectReactionJobTask>(task)->set_handler(*primary_handler);
5237 static_assert(
5238 static_cast<int>(PromiseReaction::kPromiseOrCapabilityOffset) ==
5239 static_cast<int>(
5240 PromiseRejectReactionJobTask::kPromiseOrCapabilityOffset));
5241#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
5242 static_assert(
5243 static_cast<int>(
5244 PromiseReaction::kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset) ==
5245 static_cast<int>(PromiseRejectReactionJobTask::
5246 kContinuationPreservedEmbedderDataOffset));
5247#endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
5248 }
5249
5250 MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue = handler_context->microtask_queue();
5251 if (microtask_queue) {
5252 microtask_queue->EnqueueMicrotask(*Cast<PromiseReactionJobTask>(task));
5253 }
5254 }
5255
5256 return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
5257}
5258
5259template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5260void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::IteratePrefix(ObjectVisitor* v) {
5261 BodyDescriptorBase::IteratePointers(this, 0, kElementsStartOffset, v);
5262}
5263
5264template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5265void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::IterateElements(ObjectVisitor* v) {
5266 BodyDescriptorBase::IteratePointers(this, kElementsStartOffset,
5267 SizeFor(length()), v);
5268}
5269
5270template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5271template <typename IsolateT>
5272Handle<Derived> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::New(
5273 IsolateT* isolate, int at_least_space_for, AllocationType allocation,
5274 MinimumCapacity capacity_option) {
5275 DCHECK_LE(0, at_least_space_for);
5276 DCHECK_IMPLIES(capacity_option == USE_CUSTOM_MINIMUM_CAPACITY,
5277 base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(at_least_space_for));
5278
5279 int capacity = (capacity_option == USE_CUSTOM_MINIMUM_CAPACITY)
5280 ? at_least_space_for
5281 : ComputeCapacity(at_least_space_for);
5282 if (capacity > HashTable::kMaxCapacity) {
5283 isolate->FatalProcessOutOfHeapMemory("invalid table size");
5284 }
5285 return NewInternal(isolate, capacity, allocation);
5286}
5287
5288template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5289template <typename IsolateT>
5290Handle<Derived> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::NewInternal(
5291 IsolateT* isolate, int capacity, AllocationType allocation) {
5292 auto* factory = isolate->factory();
5293 int length = EntryToIndex(InternalIndex(capacity));
5294 Handle<FixedArray> array = factory->NewFixedArrayWithMap(
5295 Derived::GetMap(isolate->roots_table()), length, allocation);
5296 Handle<Derived> table = Cast<Derived>(array);
5297 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5298 Tagged<Derived> raw_table = *table;
5299 raw_table->SetNumberOfElements(0);
5300 raw_table->SetNumberOfDeletedElements(0);
5301 raw_table->SetCapacity(capacity);
5302 return table;
5303}
5304
5305template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5306void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::Rehash(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
5307 Tagged<Derived> new_table) {
5308 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5309 WriteBarrierMode mode = new_table->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
5310
5311 DCHECK_LT(NumberOfElements(), new_table->Capacity());
5312
5313 // Copy prefix to new array.
5314 for (int i = kPrefixStartIndex; i < kElementsStartIndex; i++) {
5315 new_table->set(i, get(i), mode);
5316 }
5317
5318 // Rehash the elements.
5319 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5320 for (InternalIndex i : this->IterateEntries()) {
5321 uint32_t from_index = EntryToIndex(i);
5322 Tagged<Object> k = this->get(from_index);
5323 if (!IsKey(roots, k)) continue;
5324 uint32_t hash = TodoShape::HashForObject(roots, k);
5325 uint32_t insertion_index =
5326 EntryToIndex(new_table->FindInsertionEntry(cage_base, roots, hash));
5327 new_table->set_key(insertion_index, get(from_index), mode);
5328 for (int j = 1; j < TodoShape::kEntrySize; j++) {
5329 new_table->set(insertion_index + j, get(from_index + j), mode);
5330 }
5331 }
5332 new_table->SetNumberOfElements(NumberOfElements());
5333 new_table->SetNumberOfDeletedElements(0);
5334}
5335
5336template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5337InternalIndex HashTable<Derived, Shape>::EntryForProbe(ReadOnlyRoots roots,
5338 Tagged<Object> k,
5339 int probe,
5340 InternalIndex expected) {
5341 uint32_t hash = TodoShape::HashForObject(roots, k);
5342 uint32_t capacity = this->Capacity();
5343 InternalIndex entry = FirstProbe(hash, capacity);
5344 for (int i = 1; i < probe; i++) {
5345 if (entry == expected) return expected;
5346 entry = NextProbe(entry, i, capacity);
5347 }
5348 return entry;
5349}
5350
5351template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5352void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::Swap(InternalIndex entry1, InternalIndex entry2,
5353 WriteBarrierMode mode) {
5354 int index1 = EntryToIndex(entry1);
5355 int index2 = EntryToIndex(entry2);
5356 Tagged<Object> temp[TodoShape::kEntrySize];
5357 Derived* self = static_cast<Derived*>(this);
5358 for (int j = 0; j < TodoShape::kEntrySize; j++) {
5359 temp[j] = get(index1 + j);
5360 }
5361 self->set_key(index1, get(index2), mode);
5362 for (int j = 1; j < TodoShape::kEntrySize; j++) {
5363 set(index1 + j, get(index2 + j), mode);
5364 }
5365 self->set_key(index2, temp[0], mode);
5366 for (int j = 1; j < TodoShape::kEntrySize; j++) {
5367 set(index2 + j, temp[j], mode);
5368 }
5369}
5370
5371template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5372void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::Rehash(PtrComprCageBase cage_base) {
5373 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5374 WriteBarrierMode mode = GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
5375 ReadOnlyRoots roots = EarlyGetReadOnlyRoots();
5376 uint32_t capacity = Capacity();
5377 bool done = false;
5378 for (int probe = 1; !done; probe++) {
5379 // All elements at entries given by one of the first _probe_ probes
5380 // are placed correctly. Other elements might need to be moved.
5381 done = true;
5382 for (InternalIndex current(0); current.raw_value() < capacity;
5383 /* {current} is advanced manually below, when appropriate.*/) {
5384 Tagged<Object> current_key = KeyAt(cage_base, current);
5385 if (!IsKey(roots, current_key)) {
5386 ++current; // Advance to next entry.
5387 continue;
5388 }
5389 InternalIndex target = EntryForProbe(roots, current_key, probe, current);
5390 if (current == target) {
5391 ++current; // Advance to next entry.
5392 continue;
5393 }
5394 Tagged<Object> target_key = KeyAt(cage_base, target);
5395 if (!IsKey(roots, target_key) ||
5396 EntryForProbe(roots, target_key, probe, target) != target) {
5397 // Put the current element into the correct position.
5398 Swap(current, target, mode);
5399 // The other element will be processed on the next iteration,
5400 // so don't advance {current} here!
5401 } else {
5402 // The place for the current element is occupied. Leave the element
5403 // for the next probe.
5404 done = false;
5405 ++current; // Advance to next entry.
5406 }
5407 }
5408 }
5409 // Wipe deleted entries.
5410 Tagged<Object> the_hole = roots.the_hole_value();
5411 Tagged<HeapObject> undefined = roots.undefined_value();
5412 Derived* self = static_cast<Derived*>(this);
5413 for (InternalIndex current : InternalIndex::Range(capacity)) {
5414 if (KeyAt(cage_base, current) == the_hole) {
5415 self->set_key(EntryToIndex(current) + kEntryKeyIndex, undefined,
5416 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5417 }
5418 }
5419 SetNumberOfDeletedElements(0);
5420}
5421
5422template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5423template <typename IsolateT, template <typename> typename HandleType>
5424 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5425HandleType<Derived> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::EnsureCapacity(
5426 IsolateT* isolate, HandleType<Derived> table, int n,
5427 AllocationType allocation) {
5428 if (table->HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(n)) return table;
5429
5430 int capacity = table->Capacity();
5431 int new_nof = table->NumberOfElements() + n;
5432
5433 bool should_pretenure = allocation == AllocationType::kOld ||
5434 ((capacity > kMinCapacityForPretenure) &&
5435 !HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*table));
5436 HandleType<Derived> new_table = HashTable::New(
5437 isolate, new_nof,
5438 should_pretenure ? AllocationType::kOld : AllocationType::kYoung);
5439
5440 table->Rehash(isolate, *new_table);
5441 return new_table;
5442}
5443
5444template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5445bool HashTable<Derived, Shape>::HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(
5446 int number_of_additional_elements) {
5447 return HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(Capacity(), NumberOfElements(),
5448 NumberOfDeletedElements(),
5449 number_of_additional_elements);
5450}
5451
5452// static
5453template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5454bool HashTable<Derived, Shape>::HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(
5455 int capacity, int number_of_elements, int number_of_deleted_elements,
5456 int number_of_additional_elements) {
5457 int nof = number_of_elements + number_of_additional_elements;
5458 // Return true if:
5459 // 50% is still free after adding number_of_additional_elements elements and
5460 // at most 50% of the free elements are deleted elements.
5461 if ((nof < capacity) &&
5462 ((number_of_deleted_elements <= (capacity - nof) / 2))) {
5463 int needed_free = nof / 2;
5464 if (nof + needed_free <= capacity) return true;
5465 }
5466 return false;
5467}
5468
5469// static
5470template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5471int HashTable<Derived, Shape>::ComputeCapacityWithShrink(
5472 int current_capacity, int at_least_room_for) {
5473 // Shrink to fit the number of elements if only a quarter of the
5474 // capacity is filled with elements.
5475 if (at_least_room_for > (current_capacity / 4)) return current_capacity;
5476 // Recalculate the smaller capacity actually needed.
5477 int new_capacity = ComputeCapacity(at_least_room_for);
5478 DCHECK_GE(new_capacity, at_least_room_for);
5479 // Don't go lower than room for {kMinShrinkCapacity} elements.
5480 if (new_capacity < Derived::kMinShrinkCapacity) return current_capacity;
5481 return new_capacity;
5482}
5483
5484// static
5485template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5486template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5487 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5488HandleType<Derived> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::Shrink(Isolate* isolate,
5489 HandleType<Derived> table,
5490 int additional_capacity) {
5491 int new_capacity = ComputeCapacityWithShrink(
5492 table->Capacity(), table->NumberOfElements() + additional_capacity);
5493 if (new_capacity == table->Capacity()) return table;
5494 DCHECK_GE(new_capacity, Derived::kMinShrinkCapacity);
5495
5496 bool pretenure = (new_capacity > kMinCapacityForPretenure) &&
5497 !HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*table);
5498 HandleType<Derived> new_table =
5499 HashTable::New(isolate, new_capacity,
5500 pretenure ? AllocationType::kOld : AllocationType::kYoung,
5501 USE_CUSTOM_MINIMUM_CAPACITY);
5502
5503 table->Rehash(isolate, *new_table);
5504 return new_table;
5505}
5506
5507template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5508InternalIndex HashTable<Derived, Shape>::FindInsertionEntry(
5509 PtrComprCageBase cage_base, ReadOnlyRoots roots, uint32_t hash) {
5510 uint32_t capacity = Capacity();
5511 uint32_t count = 1;
5512 // EnsureCapacity will guarantee the hash table is never full.
5513 for (InternalIndex entry = FirstProbe(hash, capacity);;
5514 entry = NextProbe(entry, count++, capacity)) {
5515 if (!IsKey(roots, KeyAt(cage_base, entry))) return entry;
5516 }
5517}
5518
5519std::optional<Tagged<PropertyCell>>
5520GlobalDictionary::TryFindPropertyCellForConcurrentLookupIterator(
5521 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Name> name, RelaxedLoadTag tag) {
5522 // This reimplements HashTable::FindEntry for use in a concurrent setting.
5523 // 1) Atomic loads.
5524 // 2) IsPendingAllocation checks.
5525 // 3) Return the PropertyCell value instead of the InternalIndex to avoid a
5526 // repeated load (unsafe with concurrent modifications).
5527
5528 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5529 PtrComprCageBase cage_base{isolate};
5530 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5531 const int32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(roots, name);
5532 const uint32_t capacity = Capacity();
5533 uint32_t count = 1;
5534 Tagged<Object> undefined = roots.undefined_value();
5535 Tagged<Object> the_hole = roots.the_hole_value();
5536 // EnsureCapacity will guarantee the hash table is never full.
5537 for (InternalIndex entry = FirstProbe(hash, capacity);;
5538 entry = NextProbe(entry, count++, capacity)) {
5539 Tagged<Object> element = KeyAt(cage_base, entry, kRelaxedLoad);
5540 if (isolate->heap()->IsPendingAllocation(element)) return {};
5541 if (element == undefined) return {};
5542 if (TodoShape::kMatchNeedsHoleCheck && element == the_hole) continue;
5543 if (!TodoShape::IsMatch(name, element)) continue;
5544 CHECK(IsPropertyCell(element, cage_base));
5545 return Cast<PropertyCell>(element);
5546 }
5547}
5548
5549Handle<StringSet> StringSet::New(Isolate* isolate) {
5550 return HashTable::New(isolate, 0);
5551}
5552
5553Handle<StringSet> StringSet::Add(Isolate* isolate, Handle<StringSet> stringset,
5554 DirectHandle<String> name) {
5555 if (!stringset->Has(isolate, name)) {
5556 stringset = EnsureCapacity(isolate, stringset);
5557 uint32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), *name);
5558 InternalIndex entry = stringset->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash);
5559 stringset->set(EntryToIndex(entry), *name);
5560 stringset->ElementAdded();
5561 }
5562 return stringset;
5563}
5564
5565bool StringSet::Has(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name) {
5566 return FindEntry(isolate, *name).is_found();
5567}
5568
5569Handle<RegisteredSymbolTable> RegisteredSymbolTable::Add(
5570 Isolate* isolate, Handle<RegisteredSymbolTable> table,
5571 DirectHandle<String> key, DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol) {
5572 // Validate that the key is absent.
5573 SLOW_DCHECK(table->FindEntry(isolate, key).is_not_found());
5574
5575 table = EnsureCapacity(isolate, table);
5576 uint32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), key);
5577 InternalIndex entry = table->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash);
5578 table->set(EntryToIndex(entry), *key);
5579 table->set(EntryToValueIndex(entry), *symbol);
5580 table->ElementAdded();
5581 return table;
5582}

5608
5609template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5610int BaseNameDictionary<Derived, Shape>::NextEnumerationIndex(
5611 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Derived> dictionary) {
5612 int index = dictionary->next_enumeration_index();
5613 // Check whether the next enumeration index is valid.
5614 if (!PropertyDetails::IsValidIndex(index)) {
5615 // If not, we generate new indices for the properties.
5616 DirectHandle<FixedArray> iteration_order =
5617 IterationIndices(isolate, dictionary);
5618 int length = iteration_order->length();
5619 DCHECK_LE(length, dictionary->NumberOfElements());
5620
5621 // Iterate over the dictionary using the enumeration order and update
5622 // the dictionary with new enumeration indices.
5623 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5624 InternalIndex internal_index(Smi::ToInt(iteration_order->get(i)));
5625 DCHECK(dictionary->IsKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(),
5626 dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, internal_index)));
5627
5628 int enum_index = PropertyDetails::kInitialIndex + i;
5629
5630 PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(internal_index);
5631 PropertyDetails new_details = details.set_index(enum_index);
5632 dictionary->DetailsAtPut(internal_index, new_details);
5633 }
5634
5635 index = PropertyDetails::kInitialIndex + length;
5636 }
5637
5638 // Don't update the next enumeration index here, since we might be looking at
5639 // an immutable empty dictionary.
5640 return index;
5641}
5642
5643template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5644template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5645 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5646HandleType<Derived> Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::DeleteEntry(
5647 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, InternalIndex entry) {
5648 DCHECK(TodoShape::kEntrySize != 3 ||
5649 dictionary->DetailsAt(entry).IsConfigurable());
5650 dictionary->ClearEntry(entry);
5651 dictionary->ElementRemoved();
5652 return Shrink(isolate, dictionary);
5653}
5654
5655template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5656template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5657 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5658HandleType<Derived> Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::AtPut(
5659 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5660 DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details) {
5661 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, key);
5662
5663 // If the entry is present set the value;
5664 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
5665 return Derived::Add(isolate, dictionary, key, value, details);
5666 }
5667
5668 // We don't need to copy over the enumeration index.
5669 dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
5670 if (TodoShape::kEntrySize == 3) dictionary->DetailsAtPut(entry, details);
5671 return dictionary;
5672}
5673
5674template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5675void Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::UncheckedAtPut(
5676 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5677 DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details) {
5678 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, key);
5679
5680 // If the entry is present set the value;
5681 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
5682 Derived::UncheckedAdd(isolate, dictionary, key, value, details);
5683 } else {
5684 // We don't need to copy over the enumeration index.
5685 dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
5686 if (TodoShape::kEntrySize == 3) dictionary->DetailsAtPut(entry, details);
5687 }
5688}
5689
5690template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5691template <typename IsolateT, template <typename> typename HandleType>
5692 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5693HandleType<Derived>
5694BaseNameDictionary<Derived, Shape>::AddNoUpdateNextEnumerationIndex(
5695 IsolateT* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5696 DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
5697 InternalIndex* entry_out) {
5698 // Insert element at empty or deleted entry.
5699 return Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::Add(isolate, dictionary, key, value,
5700 details, entry_out);
5701}
5702
5703template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5704template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5705 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5706HandleType<Derived> BaseNameDictionary<Derived, Shape>::Add(
5707 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5708 DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
5709 InternalIndex* entry_out) {
5710 // Insert element at empty or deleted entry
5711 DCHECK_EQ(0, details.dictionary_index());
5712 // Assign an enumeration index to the property and update
5713 // SetNextEnumerationIndex.
5714 int index = Derived::NextEnumerationIndex(isolate, dictionary);
5715 details = details.set_index(index);
5716 dictionary = AddNoUpdateNextEnumerationIndex(isolate, dictionary, key, value,
5717 details, entry_out);
5718 // Update enumeration index here in order to avoid potential modification of
5719 // the canonical empty dictionary which lives in read only space.
5720 dictionary->set_next_enumeration_index(index + 1);
5721 return dictionary;
5722}
5723
5724template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5725template <typename IsolateT, template <typename> typename HandleType,
5726 AllocationType key_allocation>
5727 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5728HandleType<Derived> Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::Add(
5729 IsolateT* isolate, HandleType<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
5730 DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
5731 InternalIndex* entry_out) {
5732 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5733 uint32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(roots, key);
5734 // Validate that the key is absent.
5735 SLOW_DCHECK(dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, key).is_not_found());
5736 // Check whether the dictionary should be extended.
5737 dictionary = Derived::EnsureCapacity(isolate, dictionary);
5738
5739 // Compute the key object.
5740 DirectHandle<Object> k =
5741 TodoShape::template AsHandle<key_allocation>(isolate, key);
5742
5743 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, roots, hash);
5744 dictionary->SetEntry(entry, *k, *value, details);
5745 DCHECK(IsNumber(dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry)) ||
5746 IsUniqueName(TodoShape::Unwrap(dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry))));
5747 dictionary->ElementAdded();
5748 if (entry_out) *entry_out = entry;
5749 return dictionary;
5750}
5751
5752template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5753template <typename IsolateT, template <typename> typename HandleType,
5754 AllocationType key_allocation>
5755 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Derived>, DirectHandle<Derived>>)
5756void Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::UncheckedAdd(IsolateT* isolate,
5757 HandleType<Derived> dictionary,
5758 Key key,
5759 DirectHandle<Object> value,
5760 PropertyDetails details) {
5761 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5762 uint32_t hash = TodoShape::Hash(roots, key);
5763 // Validate that the key is absent and we capacity is sufficient.
5764 SLOW_DCHECK(dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, key).is_not_found());
5765 DCHECK(dictionary->HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(1));
5766
5767 // Compute the key object.
5768 DirectHandle<Object> k =
5769 TodoShape::template AsHandle<key_allocation>(isolate, key);
5770
5771 InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, roots, hash);
5772 dictionary->SetEntry(entry, *k, *value, details);
5773 DCHECK(IsNumber(dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry)) ||
5774 IsUniqueName(TodoShape::Unwrap(dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, entry))));
5775}

5780 AllocationType allocation) {
5781 return Cast<Derived>(isolate->factory()->CopyFixedArrayWithMap(
5782 dictionary, Derived::GetMap(isolate->roots_table()), allocation));
5783}

5791
5792void NumberDictionary::UpdateMaxNumberKey(
5793 uint32_t key, DirectHandle<JSObject> dictionary_holder) {
5794 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5795 // If the dictionary requires slow elements an element has already
5796 // been added at a high index.
5797 if (requires_slow_elements()) return;
5798 // Check if this index is high enough that we should require slow
5799 // elements.
5800 if (key > kRequiresSlowElementsLimit) {
5801 if (!dictionary_holder.is_null()) {
5802 dictionary_holder->RequireSlowElements(this);
5803 }
5804 set_requires_slow_elements();
5805 return;
5806 }
5807 // Update max key value.
5808 Tagged<Object> max_index_object = get(kMaxNumberKeyIndex);
5809 if (!IsSmi(max_index_object) || max_number_key() < key) {
5810 FixedArray::set(kMaxNumberKeyIndex,
5811 Smi::FromInt(key << kRequiresSlowElementsTagSize));
5812 }
5813}
5814
5815template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
5816 requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<NumberDictionary>,
5817 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary>>)
5818HandleType<NumberDictionary> NumberDictionary::Set(
5819 Isolate* isolate, HandleType<NumberDictionary> dictionary, uint32_t key,
5820 DirectHandle<Object> value, DirectHandle<JSObject> dictionary_holder,
5821 PropertyDetails details) {
5822 // We could call Set with empty dictionaries. UpdateMaxNumberKey doesn't
5823 // expect empty dictionaries so make sure to call AtPut that correctly handles
5824 // them by creating new dictionary when required.
5825 HandleType<NumberDictionary> new_dictionary =
5826 AtPut(isolate, dictionary, key, value, details);
5827 new_dictionary->UpdateMaxNumberKey(key, dictionary_holder);
5828 return new_dictionary;
5829}

5846
5847void NumberDictionary::CopyValuesTo(Tagged<FixedArray> elements) {
5848 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5849 int pos = 0;
5850 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5851 WriteBarrierMode mode = elements->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
5852 for (InternalIndex i : this->IterateEntries()) {
5853 Tagged<Object> k;
5854 if (this->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) {
5855 elements->set(pos++, this->ValueAt(i), mode);
5856 }
5857 }
5858 DCHECK_EQ(pos, elements->length());
5859}
5860
5861template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5862int Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::NumberOfEnumerableProperties() {
5863 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5864 int result = 0;
5865 for (InternalIndex i : this->IterateEntries()) {
5866 Tagged<Object> k;
5867 if (!this->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
5868 if (Object::FilterKey(k, ENUMERABLE_STRINGS)) continue;
5869 PropertyDetails details = this->DetailsAt(i);
5870 PropertyAttributes attr = details.attributes();
5871 if ((int{attr} & ONLY_ENUMERABLE) == 0) result++;
5872 }
5873 return result;
5874}
5875
5876template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5877DirectHandle<FixedArray> BaseNameDictionary<Derived, Shape>::IterationIndices(
5878 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Derived> dictionary) {
5879 DirectHandle<FixedArray> array =
5880 isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(dictionary->NumberOfElements());
5881 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5882 int array_size = 0;
5883 {
5884 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5885 Tagged<Derived> raw_dictionary = *dictionary;
5886 for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
5887 Tagged<Object> k;
5888 if (!raw_dictionary->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
5889 array->set(array_size++, Smi::FromInt(i.as_int()));
5890 }
5891
5892 // The global dictionary doesn't track its deletion count, so we may iterate
5893 // fewer entries than the count of elements claimed by the dictionary.
5894 if (std::is_same_v<Derived, GlobalDictionary>) {
5895 DCHECK_LE(array_size, dictionary->NumberOfElements());
5896 } else {
5897 DCHECK_EQ(array_size, dictionary->NumberOfElements());
5898 }
5899
5900 EnumIndexComparator<Derived> cmp(raw_dictionary);
5901 // Use AtomicSlot wrapper to ensure that std::sort uses atomic load and
5902 // store operations that are safe for concurrent marking.
5903 AtomicSlot start(array->RawFieldOfFirstElement());
5904 std::sort(start, start + array_size, cmp);
5905 }
5906 return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, array, array_size);
5907}
5908
5909// Backwards lookup (slow).
5910template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5911Tagged<Object> Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::SlowReverseLookup(
5912 Tagged<Object> value) {
5913 Tagged<Derived> dictionary = Cast<Derived>(this);
5914 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5915 for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
5916 Tagged<Object> k;
5917 if (!dictionary->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
5918 Tagged<Object> e = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
5919 if (e == value) return k;
5920 }
5921 return roots.undefined_value();
5922}
5923
5924template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5925void ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::FillEntriesWithHoles(
5926 DirectHandle<Derived> table) {
5927 auto roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5928 int length = table->length();
5929 for (int i = Derived::EntryToIndex(InternalIndex(0)); i < length; i++) {
5930 table->set_the_hole(roots, i);
5931 }
5932}
5933
5934template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5935Tagged<Object> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Lookup(
5936 PtrComprCageBase cage_base, DirectHandle<Object> key, int32_t hash) {
5937 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5938 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5939 DCHECK(this->IsKey(roots, *key));
5940
5941 InternalIndex entry = this->FindEntry(cage_base, roots, key, hash);
5942 if (entry.is_not_found()) return roots.the_hole_value();
5943 return this->get(Derived::EntryToIndex(entry) + 1);
5944}
5945
5946// The implementation should be in sync with
5947// CodeStubAssembler::NameToIndexHashTableLookup.
5948int NameToIndexHashTable::Lookup(DirectHandle<Name> key) {
5949 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5950 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(this);
5951 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5952
5953 InternalIndex entry = this->FindEntry(cage_base, roots, key, key->hash());
5954 if (entry.is_not_found()) return -1;
5955 return Cast<Smi>(this->get(EntryToValueIndex(entry))).value();
5956}
5957
5958template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5959Tagged<Object> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Lookup(
5960 DirectHandle<Object> key) {
5961 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5962
5963 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(this);
5964 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
5965 DCHECK(this->IsKey(roots, *key));
5966
5967 // If the object does not have an identity hash, it was never used as a key.
5968 Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetHash(*key);
5969 if (IsUndefined(hash, roots)) {
5970 return roots.the_hole_value();
5971 }
5972 return Lookup(cage_base, key, Smi::ToInt(hash));
5973}
5974
5975template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5976Tagged<Object> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Lookup(
5977 DirectHandle<Object> key, int32_t hash) {
5978 return Lookup(GetPtrComprCageBase(this), key, hash);
5979}

5981template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
5982Tagged<Object> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::ValueAt(
5983 InternalIndex entry) {
5984 return this->get(EntryToValueIndex(entry));
5985}
5986
5987Tagged<Object> RegisteredSymbolTable::ValueAt(InternalIndex entry) {
5988 return this->get(EntryToValueIndex(entry));
5989}
5990
5991Tagged<Object> NameToIndexHashTable::ValueAt(InternalIndex entry) {
5992 return this->get(EntryToValueIndex(entry));
5993}
5994
5995int NameToIndexHashTable::IndexAt(InternalIndex entry) {
5996 Tagged<Object> value = ValueAt(entry);
5997 if (IsSmi(value)) {
5998 int index = Smi::ToInt(value);
5999 DCHECK_LE(0, index);
6000 return index;
6001 }
6002 return -1;
6003}
6004
6005template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6006Handle<Derived> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Put(
6007 Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6008 DirectHandle<Object> value) {
6009 Isolate* isolate = Heap::FromWritableHeapObject(*table)->isolate();
6010 DCHECK(table->IsKey(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), *key));
6011 DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate)));
6012
6013 // Make sure the key object has an identity hash code.
6014 int32_t hash = Object::GetOrCreateHash(*key, isolate).value();
6015
6016 return ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Put(isolate, table, key, value,
6017 hash);
6018}
6019
6020namespace {
6021
6022template <typename T, template <typename> typename HandleType>
6023void RehashObjectHashTableAndGCIfNeeded(Isolate* isolate, HandleType<T> table) {
6024 // Rehash if more than 33% of the entries are deleted entries.
6025 // TODO(verwaest): Consider to shrink the fixed array in place.
6026 if ((table->NumberOfDeletedElements() << 1) > table->NumberOfElements()) {
6027 table->Rehash(isolate);
6028 }
6029 // If we're out of luck, we didn't get a GC recently, and so rehashing
6030 // isn't enough to avoid a crash.
6031 if (!table->HasSufficientCapacityToAdd(1)) {
6032 int nof = table->NumberOfElements() + 1;
6033 int capacity = T::ComputeCapacity(nof);
6034 if (capacity > T::kMaxCapacity) {
6035 for (size_t i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
6036 isolate->heap()->CollectAllGarbage(
6037 GCFlag::kNoFlags, GarbageCollectionReason::kFullHashtable);
6038 }
6039 table->Rehash(isolate);
6040 }
6041 }
6042}
6043
6044} // namespace
6045
6046template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6047Handle<Derived> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Put(
6048 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6049 DirectHandle<Object> value, int32_t hash) {
6050 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
6051 DCHECK(table->IsKey(roots, *key));
6052 DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value, roots));
6053
6054 InternalIndex entry = table->FindEntry(isolate, roots, key, hash);
6055
6056 // Key is already in table, just overwrite value.
6057 if (entry.is_found()) {
6058 table->set(Derived::EntryToValueIndex(entry), *value);
6059 return table;
6060 }
6061
6062 RehashObjectHashTableAndGCIfNeeded(isolate, table);
6063
6064 // Check whether the hash table should be extended.
6065 table = Derived::EnsureCapacity(isolate, table);
6066 table->AddEntry(table->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash), *key, *value);
6067 return table;
6068}
6069
6070template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6071Handle<Derived> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Remove(
6072 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6073 bool* was_present) {
6074 DCHECK(table->IsKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(), *key));
6075
6076 Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetHash(*key);
6077 if (IsUndefined(hash)) {
6078 *was_present = false;
6079 return table;
6080 }
6081
6082 return Remove(isolate, table, key, was_present, Smi::ToInt(hash));
6083}
6084
6085template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6086Handle<Derived> ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::Remove(
6087 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6088 bool* was_present, int32_t hash) {
6089 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6090 DCHECK(table->IsKey(roots, *key));
6091
6092 InternalIndex entry = table->FindEntry(isolate, roots, key, hash);
6093 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
6094 *was_present = false;
6095 return table;
6096 }
6097
6098 *was_present = true;
6099 table->RemoveEntry(entry);
6100 return Derived::Shrink(isolate, table);
6101}
6102
6103template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6104void ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::AddEntry(InternalIndex entry,
6105 Tagged<Object> key,
6106 Tagged<Object> value) {
6107 Derived* self = static_cast<Derived*>(this);
6108 self->set_key(Derived::EntryToIndex(entry), key);
6109 self->set(Derived::EntryToValueIndex(entry), value);
6110 self->ElementAdded();
6111}
6112
6113template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
6114void ObjectHashTableBase<Derived, Shape>::RemoveEntry(InternalIndex entry) {
6115 auto roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6116 this->set_the_hole(roots, Derived::EntryToIndex(entry));
6117 this->set_the_hole(roots, Derived::EntryToValueIndex(entry));
6118 this->ElementRemoved();
6119}
6120
6121template <typename Derived, int N>
6122std::array<Tagged<Object>, N> ObjectMultiHashTableBase<Derived, N>::Lookup(
6123 DirectHandle<Object> key) {
6124 return Lookup(GetPtrComprCageBase(this), key);
6125}
6126
6127template <typename Derived, int N>
6128std::array<Tagged<Object>, N> ObjectMultiHashTableBase<Derived, N>::Lookup(
6129 PtrComprCageBase cage_base, DirectHandle<Object> key) {
6130 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6131
6132 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
6133 DCHECK(this->IsKey(roots, *key));
6134
6135 Tagged<Object> hash_obj = Object::GetHash(*key);
6136 if (IsUndefined(hash_obj, roots)) {
6137 return {roots.the_hole_value(), roots.the_hole_value()};
6138 }
6139 int32_t hash = Smi::ToInt(hash_obj);
6140
6141 InternalIndex entry = this->FindEntry(cage_base, roots, key, hash);
6142 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
6143 return {roots.the_hole_value(), roots.the_hole_value()};
6144 }
6145
6146 int start_index = this->EntryToIndex(entry) +
6147 ObjectMultiHashTableShape<N>::kEntryValueIndex;
6148 std::array<Tagged<Object>, N> values;
6149 for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
6150 values[i] = this->get(start_index + i);
6151 DCHECK(!IsTheHole(values[i]));
6152 }
6153 return values;
6154}
6155
6156// static
6157template <typename Derived, int N>
6158Handle<Derived> ObjectMultiHashTableBase<Derived, N>::Put(
6159 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> table, DirectHandle<Object> key,
6160 const std::array<DirectHandle<Object>, N>& values) {
6161 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
6162 DCHECK(table->IsKey(roots, *key));
6163
6164 int32_t hash = Object::GetOrCreateHash(*key, isolate).value();
6165 InternalIndex entry = table->FindEntry(isolate, roots, key, hash);
6166
6167 // Overwrite values if entry is found.
6168 if (entry.is_found()) {
6169 table->SetEntryValues(entry, values);
6170 return table;
6171 }
6172
6173 RehashObjectHashTableAndGCIfNeeded(isolate, table);
6174
6175 // Check whether the hash table should be extended.
6176 table = Derived::EnsureCapacity(isolate, table);
6177 entry = table->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash);
6178 table->set(Derived::EntryToIndex(entry), *key);
6179 table->SetEntryValues(entry, values);
6180 return table;
6181}
6182
6183template <typename Derived, int N>
6184void ObjectMultiHashTableBase<Derived, N>::SetEntryValues(
6185 InternalIndex entry, const std::array<DirectHandle<Object>, N>& values) {
6186 int start_index = EntryToValueIndexStart(entry);
6187 for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
6188 this->set(start_index + i, *values[i]);
6189 }
6190}
6191
6192Handle<ObjectHashSet> ObjectHashSet::Add(Isolate* isolate,
6193 Handle<ObjectHashSet> set,
6194 DirectHandle<Object> key) {
6195 int32_t hash = Object::GetOrCreateHash(*key, isolate).value();
6196 if (!set->Has(isolate, key, hash)) {
6197 set = EnsureCapacity(isolate, set);
6198 InternalIndex entry = set->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, hash);
6199 set->set(EntryToIndex(entry), *key);
6200 set->ElementAdded();
6201 }
6202 return set;
6203}

6241void JSWeakCollection::Initialize(
6242 DirectHandle<JSWeakCollection> weak_collection, Isolate* isolate) {

6244 weak_collection->set_table(*table);
