6246
6247void JSWeakCollection::Set(DirectHandle<JSWeakCollection> weak_collection,
6248 DirectHandle<Object> key, DirectHandle<Object> value,
6249 int32_t hash) {
6250 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*key) || IsSymbol(*key));
6251 Handle<EphemeronHashTable> table(
6252 Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(weak_collection->table()),
6253 weak_collection->GetIsolate());
6254 DCHECK(table->IsKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(), *key));
6255 DirectHandle<EphemeronHashTable> new_table = EphemeronHashTable::Put(
6256 weak_collection->GetIsolate(), table, key, value, hash);
6257 weak_collection->set_table(*new_table);
6258 if (*table != *new_table) {
6259 // Zap the old table since we didn't record slots for its elements.
6260 EphemeronHashTable::FillEntriesWithHoles(table);
6261 }
6262}
6263
6264bool JSWeakCollection::Delete(DirectHandle<JSWeakCollection> weak_collection,
6265 DirectHandle<Object> key, int32_t hash) {
6266 DCHECK(IsJSReceiver(*key) || IsSymbol(*key));
6267 Handle<EphemeronHashTable> table(
6268 Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(weak_collection->table()),
6269 weak_collection->GetIsolate());
6270 DCHECK(table->IsKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(), *key));
6271 bool was_present = false;
6272 DirectHandle<EphemeronHashTable> new_table = EphemeronHashTable::Remove(
6273 weak_collection->GetIsolate(), table, key, &was_present, hash);
6274 weak_collection->set_table(*new_table);
6275 if (*table != *new_table) {
6276 // Zap the old table since we didn't record slots for its elements.
6277 EphemeronHashTable::FillEntriesWithHoles(table);
6278 }
6279 return was_present;
6280}
6281
6282Handle<JSArray> JSWeakCollection::GetEntries(
6283 DirectHandle<JSWeakCollection> holder, int max_entries) {
6284 Isolate* isolate = holder->GetIsolate();
6285 DirectHandle<EphemeronHashTable> table(
6286 Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(holder->table()), isolate);
6287 if (max_entries == 0 || max_entries > table->NumberOfElements()) {
6288 max_entries = table->NumberOfElements();
6289 }
6290 int values_per_entry = IsJSWeakMap(*holder) ? 2 : 1;
6291 DirectHandle<FixedArray> entries =
6292 isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(max_entries * values_per_entry);
6293 // Recompute max_values because GC could have removed elements from the table.
6294 if (max_entries > table->NumberOfElements()) {
6295 max_entries = table->NumberOfElements();
6296 }
6297
6298 {
6299 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6300 ReadOnlyRoots roots = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate);
6301 int count = 0;
6302 for (int i = 0;
6303 count / values_per_entry < max_entries && i < table->Capacity(); i++) {
6304 Tagged<Object> key;
6305 if (table->ToKey(roots, InternalIndex(i), &key)) {
6306 entries->set(count++, key);
6307 if (values_per_entry > 1) {
6308 Tagged<Object> value = table->Lookup(direct_handle(key, isolate));
6309 entries->set(count++, value);
6310 }
6311 }
6312 }
6313 DCHECK_EQ(max_entries * values_per_entry, count);
6314 }
6315 return isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayWithElements(entries);
6316}

6318void JSDisposableStackBase::InitializeJSDisposableStackBase(
6319 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSDisposableStackBase> disposable_stack) {
6320 DirectHandle<FixedArray> array = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(0);
6321 disposable_stack->set_stack(*array);
6322 disposable_stack->set_needs_await(false);
6323 disposable_stack->set_has_awaited(false);
6324 disposable_stack->set_suppressed_error_created(false);
6325 disposable_stack->set_length(0);
6326 disposable_stack->set_state(DisposableStackState::kPending);
6327 disposable_stack->set_error(*(isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value()));
6328 disposable_stack->set_error_message(
6329 *(isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value()));
6330}

6332void PropertyCell::ClearAndInvalidate(Isolate* isolate) {
6333 DCHECK(!IsPropertyCellHole(value(), isolate));
6334 PropertyDetails details = property_details();
6335 details = details.set_cell_type(PropertyCellType::kConstant);
6336 Transition(details, isolate->factory()->property_cell_hole_value());
6337 DependentCode::DeoptimizeDependencyGroups(
6338 isolate, *this, DependentCode::kPropertyCellChangedGroup);
6339}

6341// static
6342Handle<PropertyCell> PropertyCell::InvalidateAndReplaceEntry(
6343 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary,
6344 InternalIndex entry, PropertyDetails new_details,
6345 DirectHandle<Object> new_value) {
6346 DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell(dictionary->CellAt(entry), isolate);
6347 DirectHandle<Name> name(cell->name(), isolate);
6348 DCHECK(cell->property_details().IsConfigurable());
6349 DCHECK(!IsAnyHole(cell->value(), isolate));
6350
6351 // Swap with a new property cell.
6352 Handle<PropertyCell> new_cell =
6353 isolate->factory()->NewPropertyCell(name, new_details, new_value);
6354 dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *new_cell);
6355
6356 cell->ClearAndInvalidate(isolate);
6357 return new_cell;
6358}
6359
6360static bool RemainsConstantType(Tagged<PropertyCell> cell,
6361 Tagged<Object> value) {
6362 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6363 // TODO(dcarney): double->smi and smi->double transition from kConstant
6364 if (IsSmi(cell->value()) && IsSmi(value)) {
6365 return true;
6366 } else if (IsHeapObject(cell->value()) && IsHeapObject(value)) {
6367 Tagged<Map> map = Cast<HeapObject>(value)->map();
6368 return Cast<HeapObject>(cell->value())->map() == map && map->is_stable();
6369 }
6370 return false;
6371}
6372
6373// static
6374PropertyCellType PropertyCell::InitialType(Isolate* isolate,
6375 Tagged<Object> value) {
6376 return IsUndefined(value, isolate) ? PropertyCellType::kUndefined
6377 : PropertyCellType::kConstant;
6378}
6379
6380// static
6381PropertyCellType PropertyCell::UpdatedType(Isolate* isolate,
6382 Tagged<PropertyCell> cell,
6383 Tagged<Object> value,
6384 PropertyDetails details) {
6385 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6386 DCHECK(!IsAnyHole(value, isolate));
6387 DCHECK(!IsAnyHole(cell->value(), isolate));
6388 switch (details.cell_type()) {
6389 case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
6390 return PropertyCellType::kConstant;
6391 case PropertyCellType::kConstant:
6392 if (value == cell->value()) return PropertyCellType::kConstant;
6393 [[fallthrough]];
6394 case PropertyCellType::kConstantType:
6395 if (RemainsConstantType(cell, value)) {
6396 return PropertyCellType::kConstantType;
6397 }
6398 [[fallthrough]];
6399 case PropertyCellType::kMutable:
6400 return PropertyCellType::kMutable;
6401 case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
6402 UNREACHABLE();
6403 }
6404 UNREACHABLE();
6405}
6406
6407Handle<PropertyCell> PropertyCell::PrepareForAndSetValue(
6408 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary,
6409 InternalIndex entry, DirectHandle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details) {
6410 DCHECK(!IsAnyHole(*value, isolate));
6411 Tagged<PropertyCell> raw_cell = dictionary->CellAt(entry);
6412 CHECK(!IsAnyHole(raw_cell->value(), isolate));
6413 const PropertyDetails original_details = raw_cell->property_details();
6414 // Data accesses could be cached in ics or optimized code.
6415 bool invalidate = original_details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData &&
6416 details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor;
6417 int index = original_details.dictionary_index();
6418 DCHECK_LT(0, index);
6419 details = details.set_index(index);
6420
6421 PropertyCellType new_type =
6422 UpdatedType(isolate, raw_cell, *value, original_details);
6423 details = details.set_cell_type(new_type);
6424
6425 Handle<PropertyCell> cell(raw_cell, isolate);
6426
6427 if (invalidate) {
6428 cell = PropertyCell::InvalidateAndReplaceEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry,
6429 details, value);
6430 } else {
6431 cell->Transition(details, value);
6432 // Deopt when transitioning from a constant type or when making a writable
6433 // property read-only. Making a read-only property writable again is not
6434 // interesting because Turbofan does not currently rely on read-only unless
6435 // the property is also configurable, in which case it will stay read-only
6436 // forever.
6437 if (original_details.cell_type() != new_type ||
6438 (!original_details.IsReadOnly() && details.IsReadOnly())) {
6439 DependentCode::DeoptimizeDependencyGroups(
6440 isolate, *cell, DependentCode::kPropertyCellChangedGroup);
6441 }
6442 }
6443 return cell;
6444}
6445
6446// static
6447void PropertyCell::InvalidateProtector() {
6448 if (value() != Smi::FromInt(Protectors::kProtectorInvalid)) {
6449 DCHECK_EQ(value(), Smi::FromInt(Protectors::kProtectorValid));
6450 set_value(Smi::FromInt(Protectors::kProtectorInvalid), kReleaseStore);
6451 // TODO(11527): pass Isolate as an argument.
6452 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*this);
6453 DependentCode::DeoptimizeDependencyGroups(
6454 isolate, *this, DependentCode::kPropertyCellChangedGroup);
6455 }
6456}
6457
6458// static
6459bool PropertyCell::CheckDataIsCompatible(PropertyDetails details,
6460 Tagged<Object> value) {
6461 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6462 PropertyCellType cell_type = details.cell_type();
6463 CHECK_NE(cell_type, PropertyCellType::kInTransition);
6464 if (IsPropertyCellHole(value)) {
6465 CHECK_EQ(cell_type, PropertyCellType::kConstant);
6466 } else {
6467 CHECK_EQ(IsAccessorInfo(value) || IsAccessorPair(value),
6468 details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor);
6469 DCHECK_IMPLIES(cell_type == PropertyCellType::kUndefined,
6470 IsUndefined(value));
6471 }
6472 return true;
6473}
6474
6475#ifdef DEBUG
6476bool PropertyCell::CanTransitionTo(PropertyDetails new_details,
6477 Tagged<Object> new_value) const {
6478 // Extending the implementation of PropertyCells with additional states
6479 // and/or transitions likely requires changes to PropertyCellData::Serialize.
6480 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6481 DCHECK(CheckDataIsCompatible(new_details, new_value));
6482 switch (property_details().cell_type()) {
6483 case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
6484 return new_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kUndefined;
6485 case PropertyCellType::kConstant:
6486 return !IsPropertyCellHole(value()) &&
6487 new_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kUndefined;
6488 case PropertyCellType::kConstantType:
6489 return new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstantType ||
6490 new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kMutable ||
6491 (new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstant &&
6492 IsPropertyCellHole(new_value));
6493 case PropertyCellType::kMutable:
6494 return new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kMutable ||
6495 (new_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstant &&
6496 IsPropertyCellHole(new_value));
6497 case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
6498 UNREACHABLE();
6499 }
6500 UNREACHABLE();
6501}
6502#endif // DEBUG
6503
6504int JSGeneratorObject::code_offset() const {
6505 DCHECK(IsSmi(input_or_debug_pos()));
6506 int code_offset = Smi::ToInt(input_or_debug_pos());
6507
6508 // The stored bytecode offset is relative to a different base than what
6509 // is used in the source position table, hence the subtraction.
6510 code_offset -= BytecodeArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag;
6511 return code_offset;
6512}
6513
6514int JSGeneratorObject::source_position() const {
6515 CHECK(is_suspended());
6516 DCHECK(function()->shared()->HasBytecodeArray());
6517 Isolate* isolate = GetIsolate();
6518 DCHECK(function()
6519 ->shared()
6520 ->GetBytecodeArray(isolate)
6521 ->HasSourcePositionTable());
6522 Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode =
6523 function()->shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate);
6524 return bytecode->SourcePosition(code_offset());
6525}
6526
6527// static
6528Tagged<AccessCheckInfo> AccessCheckInfo::Get(Isolate* isolate,
6529 DirectHandle<JSObject> receiver) {
6530 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6531 DCHECK(receiver->map()->is_access_check_needed());
6532 Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = receiver->map()->GetConstructor();
6533 if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(maybe_constructor)) {
6534 Tagged<Object> data_obj =
6535 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(maybe_constructor)->GetAccessCheckInfo();
6536 if (IsUndefined(data_obj, isolate)) return AccessCheckInfo();
6537 return Cast<AccessCheckInfo>(data_obj);
6538 }
6539 // Might happen for a detached context.
6540 if (!IsJSFunction(maybe_constructor)) return AccessCheckInfo();
6541 Tagged<JSFunction> constructor = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
6542 // Might happen for the debug context.
6543 if (!constructor->shared()->IsApiFunction()) return AccessCheckInfo();
6544
6545 Tagged<Object> data_obj =
6546 constructor->shared()->api_func_data()->GetAccessCheckInfo();
6547 if (IsUndefined(data_obj, isolate)) return AccessCheckInfo();
6548
6549 return Cast<AccessCheckInfo>(data_obj);
6550}
6551
6552Address Smi::LexicographicCompare(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<Smi> x,
6553 Tagged<Smi> y) {
6554 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6555 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
6556
6557 int x_value = Smi::ToInt(x);
6558 int y_value = Smi::ToInt(y);
6559
6560 // If the integers are equal so are the string representations.
6561 if (x_value == y_value) return Smi::FromInt(0).ptr();
6562
6563 // If one of the integers is zero the normal integer order is the
6564 // same as the lexicographic order of the string representations.
6565 if (x_value == 0 || y_value == 0) {
6566 return Smi::FromInt(x_value < y_value ? -1 : 1).ptr();
6567 }
6568
6569 // If only one of the integers is negative the negative number is
6570 // smallest because the char code of '-' is less than the char code
6571 // of any digit. Otherwise, we make both values positive.
6572
6573 // Use unsigned values otherwise the logic is incorrect for -MIN_INT on
6574 // architectures using 32-bit Smis.
6575 uint32_t x_scaled = x_value;
6576 uint32_t y_scaled = y_value;
6577 if (x_value < 0) {
6578 if (y_value >= 0) {
6579 return Smi::FromInt(-1).ptr();
6580 } else {
6581 y_scaled = base::NegateWithWraparound(y_value);
6582 }
6583 x_scaled = base::NegateWithWraparound(x_value);
6584 } else if (y_value < 0) {
6585 return Smi::FromInt(1).ptr();
6586 }
6587
6588 // clang-format off
6589 static const uint32_t kPowersOf10[] = {
6590 1, 10, 100, 1000,
6591 10 * 1000, 100 * 1000, 1000 * 1000, 10 * 1000 * 1000,
6592 100 * 1000 * 1000, 1000 * 1000 * 1000};
6593 // clang-format on
6594
6595 // If the integers have the same number of decimal digits they can be
6596 // compared directly as the numeric order is the same as the
6597 // lexicographic order. If one integer has fewer digits, it is scaled
6598 // by some power of 10 to have the same number of digits as the longer
6599 // integer. If the scaled integers are equal it means the shorter
6600 // integer comes first in the lexicographic order.
6601
6602 // From http://graphics.stanford.edu/~seander/bithacks.html#IntegerLog10
6603 int x_log2 = 31 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(x_scaled);
6604 int x_log10 = ((x_log2 + 1) * 1233) >> 12;
6605 x_log10 -= x_scaled < kPowersOf10[x_log10];
6606
6607 int y_log2 = 31 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(y_scaled);
6608 int y_log10 = ((y_log2 + 1) * 1233) >> 12;
6609 y_log10 -= y_scaled < kPowersOf10[y_log10];
6610
6611 int tie = 0;
6612
6613 if (x_log10 < y_log10) {
6614 // X has fewer digits. We would like to simply scale up X but that
6615 // might overflow, e.g when comparing 9 with 1_000_000_000, 9 would
6616 // be scaled up to 9_000_000_000. So we scale up by the next
6617 // smallest power and scale down Y to drop one digit. It is OK to
6618 // drop one digit from the longer integer since the final digit is
6619 // past the length of the shorter integer.
6620 x_scaled *= kPowersOf10[y_log10 - x_log10 - 1];
6621 y_scaled /= 10;
6622 tie = -1;
6623 } else if (y_log10 < x_log10) {
6624 y_scaled *= kPowersOf10[x_log10 - y_log10 - 1];
6625 x_scaled /= 10;
6626 tie = 1;
6627 }
6628
6629 if (x_scaled < y_scaled) return Smi::FromInt(-1).ptr();
6630 if (x_scaled > y_scaled) return Smi::FromInt(1).ptr();
6631 return Smi::FromInt(tie).ptr();
6632}
6633
6634// static
6635bool MapWord::IsMapOrForwarded(Tagged<Map> map) {
6636 MapWord map_word = map->map_word(kRelaxedLoad);
6637 if (map_word.IsForwardingAddress()) {
6638 // During GC we can't access forwarded maps without synchronization.
6639 return true;
6640 }
6641 // The meta map might be moved away by GC too but we can read instance
6642 // type from both old and new location as it can't change.
6643 return InstanceTypeChecker::IsMap(map_word.ToMap()->instance_type());
6644}
